title: barbecued ribs
directions: Rub ribs with curry powder until yellow.
Then rub with chili powder until red.
Place in crock-pot.
Add onion and then catsup. Cook on medium until tender, about 5 hours.
Skim fat.
If sauce is too thin, remove cover and cook on high to reduce.
Sauce is good on mashed potatoes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Scald
tomatoes and skin them.	Combine all ingredients in a large pot; cook (simmer) for 12 hours.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: german chocolate pies
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cocoa in bowl.
Stir in evaporated milk, vanilla, eggs and melted butter.
Blend well.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Turn batter into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set around edges.
Can be frozen.

title: beef stew
directions: Place meat in crock-pot. Mix flour, salt and pepper and pour over meat. Stir to coat meat. Add remaining ingredients. Stir to mix well. Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours. Stir stew thoroughly before serving.

title: chocolate "no bake" cookies
directions: Boil sugar, oleo, cocoa and Milnot about 1 minute. Add peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well. Add oatmeal. Mix well. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper; let set until hard.

title: broccoli-lima bake
directions: Cook vegetables until barely tender.
Blend mushroom soup, sour cream and onion mix.
Stir into cooked vegetables.
Add water chestnuts.
Spoon into a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with Rice Krispies that have been browned lightly in butter.
Cover loosely with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple frosting cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix box; add yolks. Bake in 4 layers.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Cook sugar and pineapple over slow heat until thick.
Pour hot mixture over egg whites, stirring it together.
This makes enough to frost 4 layers.

title: shrimp chinese(casserole)
directions: Combine celery, onion and water in saucepan.
Simmer, covered, until onion is soft; drain.
Brown mushrooms lightly in butter. Combine celery-onion mixture, mushrooms, green pepper, cashews, pimentos, water chestnuts and shrimp.
Mix well.
Combine with white sauce and season to taste.
Layer bottom of greased 6-quart baking dish with 1 can of the noodles.
Cover with shrimp mixture. Top with remaining noodles.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Add flavors.
Make a paste of food coloring and cocoa and blend in.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vinegar with last half of buttermilk. Beat only until smooth.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and frost with no-cook icing.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mixture will be thick.
With teaspoon, dip out small amount of dough.
Roll in powdered sugar. Bake at 350° to 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
Add oysters, crushed crackers, salt and pepper.
Stir in half and half mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered in 375° oven until hot, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Coat chocolate chips lightly in flour to prevent them from sinking to the bottom of the pan while baking; set aside.
Mix all ingredients together except chocolate chips.
Add chocolate chips last.
Bake in a greased Bundt pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and let cool.
Pull meat into pieces.
Mix cream of chicken soup, mixed vegetables and chicken meat.
Put in pie shell, take other pie shell and put on top.
Pinch together and cut splits in top.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: pork stir-fry
directions: Brown pork in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add 2 tablespoons soy sauce. Set aside.
Steam vegetables in 1 tablespoons oil and 1/2 cup water.
Add pork back to vegetables.
Sprinkle Sloppy Joe, ginger, garlic salt and seasoning salt over and mix well.
Add rest of soy sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Line an 8-inch Pyrex pie pan with ladyfingers.
Mix butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Beat in eggs; beat 5 minutes after each egg at medium speed.
Pour in pie shell for 3 hours.
Cover with whipped cream, grated nuts and chocolate.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add and beat in 4 eggs.
Stir in cubed bread and the can of crushed pineapple.
Mixture will look curdy before baking.
Bake in 2-quart casserole at 350° for 1 hour.
May be prepared ahead and baked later.

title: cheesy zucchini
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in
greased
2 quart, uncovered, casserole at 300° for 1 hour.

title: crispies
directions: Melt chips in double boiler. We use our old Presto cooker, it's larger, heavier and we can add all the other ingredients in that pan.

title: classic karo pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla flavor until well blended; stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry pie shell.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken until done; set aside to cool.
Cook rice as directed on box.
Take chicken off bone; cut into bite size pieces.
Add chicken to rice.
Mix well.

title: baked stuffed clams
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl and toss lightly to mix.
Spoon into 8 scrubbed clam shells.
Place filled shells onto baking sheet.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes or until hot and golden.
Add pat of butter on top of each.
Makes 8 appetizers.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
In a large bowl, beat eggs well.
Add whole kernel and cream-style corn, sour cream, butter or margarine, green chiles, green onions and salt; mix well.
Add corn muffin mix and stir just until moistened and well blended.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes or until top is set and a knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve immediately.

title: peach cooler
directions: Put skinned peaches, lemon juice, yogurt and milk into a blender or food processor and process until completely smooth. Fill tall glasses with ice cubes and pour over peach cooler. Garnish the sides of the glasses with thin slices of peach. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Add margarine and cut in with fork until well mixed.
Stir egg and orange juice together.
Add juice to dry ingredients; stir well. Fold in cranberries and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or when toothpick comes out clean.

title: quick peach melba
directions: Place cakes on dessert plates. Drain the peaches, reserving 2 tablespoons of syrup; spoon 1 1/2 teaspoons of syrup over each cake. Place peach halves, hollow side up, on the cakes. Put a scoop of the ice cream in each peach. Heat jam; drizzle over ice cream. Sprinkle with nuts and serve immediately.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in refrigerator. Grease muffin pan well and spoon ingredients in.
Bake at 425°. May be kept in refrigerator for several days.

title: graham delights
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.

Line with whole graham crackers. Put ingredients in pan and cook, stirring constantly, until boil. Cook 6 minutes more while you continue stirring. Pour mixture over graham crackers and top with whole graham crackers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with icing.

title: delicious sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly and pour into buttered baking dish.

title: melt-in-your-mouth sugar cookies
directions: Combine butter, oil and sugars in a large mixing bowl; beat well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar in a medium mixing bowl; add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: sweet potatoes with butterscotch sauce
directions: Pour butterscotch syrup over potatoes in casserole after you have diluted it with 2 tablespoons of hot water.
Heat in baking dish after you have coated all the pieces of potatoes in a slow oven until warm and seasoned.
Particularly good with ham.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
Transfer to warm serving platter.
Add chives or green onions, lime juice and brandy, if used, parsley and mustard to pan.
Cook 15 seconds, whisking constantly.
Whisk in broth.
Stir until sauce is smooth. Whisk in remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken. Serve immediately.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Put milk and salt into a saucepan and when warmed, add rice. Bring to a quick boil and then allow to simmer for 15 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Add the raisins and let it all simmer for 5 minutes longer.
Stir in 1/4 cup of the cream and simmer for 3 more minutes, stirring constantly.
Combine the frothy beaten eggs in a mixing bowl with the sugar, vanilla and rest of the cream. Blend well and stir in a tablespoon of the hot rice mixture.
Dump the contents of the mixing bowl into the saucepan and simmer until it thickens.
Serve cold.

title: potato hash
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, place potatoes, chopped onion, parsley, beef broth cube and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover potatoes with water 1/4-inch above the potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are soft. In a 3-quart casserole dish, place mixture.
Add can of corned beef hash.
Thicken this mixture with flour and water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt into a bowl. In a separate bowl, cream margarine and brown sugar.
Beat in egg. Beat in yogurt, lemon juice and 1 teaspoon of lemon rind.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Pour refried beans into
the
bottom
of
a Pyrex dish. Sprinkle taco seasoning over beans.
Spread guacamole dip over the beans, then spread the
sour
cream.
Sprinkle the rest of the ingredients layer by layer with cheese on top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix yeast and warm water; set aside.
Work with finger or pastry blender 4 cups of flour, salt, 6 tablespoons sugar and 1 cup margarine, until small particles are formed.
Add egg, milk and yeast mixture.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning, divide dough and press out on 2 large cookie sheets.
Pare and slice apples and layer on top of each coffee cake.
Sprinkle cinnamon liberally over apples.
Combine 1 stick margarine with 2 cups sugar and 1/3 cup flour.
Mix with pastry blender and spread over coffee cake.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef. Add taco seasoning mix, onion, water and diced tomatoes. Stir to mix well. Bring to a boil. Turn off heat. Using a 9 x 13 pan, place crushed tortilla chips in bottom of pan. Spoon half of meat mixture on top of chips. Sprinkle half of both cheeses on top. Spoon remaining meat mixture on top of cheese. Top with the rest of the cheese. Bake in 350° oven 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: chicken, pasta and broccoli
directions: Skin and debone chicken.
Saute chicken, onion and mushrooms in the tablespoon of oil.
Saute until the chicken is done and the onion is tender.
Add both cans of soup.
Cook the pasta.
Drain. Add the soup mixture.
Cook the broccoli.
Add to the soup and pasta mixture.
Add everything else.
Sprinkle the cheese on top.

title: ma's soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix sugar, lard and molasses.
Dissolve baking soda in hot water, then combine both mixtures.
Sift flour, salt and ginger together.
Combine with molasses mixture.
Roll out on floured board to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake in a 350° to 375° oven.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Take
skin
off	and
chop
chicken into little squares.
Mix soups, onion, celery and Ro-Tel together. Put chips in	bottom	of
a
9 x 13-inch pan. Cover chips with chicken. Pour mixture over chicken and top with cheeses. Bake until cheese melts good or about 1 hour.

title: rolling acres special
directions: Brown meat well in oil and butter; drain excess, then add a little more butter.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Do not allow to brown.
Add mushroom soup and bouillon cube, which has been diluted in 1/2 cup hot water.
Let simmer until well seasoned, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or grits.

title: mush
directions: Mix cornmeal and other dry ingredients with 1 cup cold water and stir into the 3 cups of boiling water.
Turn heat to low and cook about 1 hour.
Pour into loaf pan.
Cover with Saran Wrap; cool overnight in refrigerator.
Slice and fry.
Serve with favorite syrup.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water in saucepan and cook until mixture forms a hard ball.
Have ready the egg whites beaten stiff and cream of tartar and add syrup mixture until all is used (slowly). Beat for about four minutes and add vanilla.
Can add pecans now if adding, chopped.
When mixture holds its shape, drop from teaspoon on waxed paper and top with pecan halves or maraschino cherry halves (that have been drained on paper towel).
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen pieces.

title: grilled vegetable kabobs
directions: In small bowl, combine dressing, parsley and basil.
Cover and chill.
Alternate vegetables on 8 skewers.
Coat grill rack with spray and place over medium coals.
Place kabobs on rack and cook 15 minutes or until tender, turning frequently and basting with dressing mixture.

title: country biscuits
directions: Mix baking powder, salt, shortening and 1 cup flour, then add 1 cup milk.
Add enough flour to make batter stiff, about 2 1/2 cups. Pat out onto floured board.
Cut and bake in hot oven (400°) on lightly greased pan.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Place ribs in shallow roasting pan, meaty side up.
On each piece, place a slice of unpeeled lemon and a thin slice of onion. Roast in very hot oven at 425° to 450° about 30 minutes.

title: happy day cake
directions: Cream shortening. Sift	dry ingredients and mix together.
Add milk and beat for
2 minutes.
Add eggs and remaining milk and beat slowly 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into pie plate sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Mix in other ingredients.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Carefully prepare a glass of wine for the chef.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, eggs and pumpkin.
Combine dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture and blend well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until loaf tests done.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: cherry or apricot salad
directions: Mix well the Cool Whip, Eagle Brand and lemon juice.
Stir in other ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
May be frozen.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake in a 375° oven until cheese is melted and pie is hot.
Let sit for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl.
Stir in milk and shortening.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in a 9-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over batter and bake for 45 minutes.
During baking, cake mixture rises to top and chocolate sauce settles to bottom. Invert square of pudding on dessert plates.
Dip sauce from pan over each, or the entire platter.
Serve warm, with or without whipped cream.
Makes 9 servings.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts. In another bowl, combine sweet potatoes, sugar, oleo and vanilla. Add flour mixture and mix well.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter and
place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheesy dill bread
directions: Cut flour, margarine and baking powder together.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in greased bread pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes, until done.

title: okra omelet
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon drippings in a bowl.
Pour drippings or vegetable oil in a pan.
Pour mixture in and flatten. Place pan in preheated 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn omelet and bake 5 to 10 minutes.
Cut to serving sizes and serve warm.
Makes 4 to 6 portions.

title: a leprechaun's secret recipe
directions: Mix 1/4 cup Magic Moo (green stuff) into a baby food jar.
Add 1 tablespoon of Magic Powder (white stuff).
Screw the lid on carefully and shake until thick.
Remove the lid and enjoy!

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and place in baking dish.
On top, crumble 1 tube of Town House crackers.
Melt margarine.
Pour over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: You're supposed to put some meat in it.
Then you're supposed to squish bread on it.
Then you put in the stove and you let it set in there 3 hours.
Then you take 'em out then you eat them. If you don't want to eat it you can save it.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until thick and transparent, stirring constantly; cool.
Spread pie shell with softened cream cheese.
Stand whole strawberries in cream cheese to completely cover pie shell.
Spread cooled sauce over strawberries. Cover with whipped cream to which almond extract and powdered sugar have been added.
Chill.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: corn chowder
directions: After cooking potatoes, drain.
Add all ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Heat slowly until hot.

title: lime cucumber pickles
directions: Soak clean cucumbers in lime and water mixture for 12 hours or overnight (in crockery or enamel ware).
Remove cucumbers from lime water and wash 3 times in fresh cold water.
Soak cucumbers 3 hours in ice water. Combine sugar, vinegar, salt and mixed pickling spices. Bring to low boil.
Stir until sugar is completely dissolved.
Remove syrup from fire and add sliced cucumbers. Soak 5 or 6 hours or overnight.
Boil slices in syrup 35 minutes.
Fill sterilized jars with hot slices. Cover with hot syrup, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Cap jars.
Process pints 10 minutes, quarts 15 minutes in boiling water.

title: golden potatoes
directions: In greased casserole alternate potato, cheese and soup mixture. Top with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Melt chocolates and Eagle Brand together in microwave.
Mix in other ingredients and chill.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Mix sausage and cream cheese.
Stuff mushrooms with cream cheese mixture.
Place on baking pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Press crescent rolls in a 9-inch pie plate.
Add meat mixture. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Brown zucchini and onion in margarine.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add parsley and spices.
Beat eggs in a large bowl and add cheese to egg mixture.
Add zucchini mix.
Line 13 x 9-inch baking dish with rolls.
Spread on mustard.
Pour in zucchini mixture and cook 20 minutes at 375°.

title: fake fries
directions: Take three large Idaho potatoes and slice them lengthwise into thin pieces.
Dry with a paper towel after soaking in cold water. Beat two egg whites until they are frothy.
Dip the potato slices to coat lightly.
Place on a lightly oiled baking sheet; sprinkle with a little salt.
Bake in a preheated oven at 425° for 40 minutes or until golden crisp and tender.
Serves 4.

title: confetti punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large container.
Stir gently.
Makes 8 servings.
Also add ice.

title: refrigerator roll dough
directions: In a small bowl measure lukewarm water and yeast.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes, until yeast is dissolved.
To the milk add sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add and stir in about 2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add egg and softened yeast.
Add and stir in about 2 1/2 cups more of flour.
It may take more. Turn dough out on lightly floured board; knead until smooth and satiny.
Place in a greased bowl and brush top with margarine.
Let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, until double in size (about 1 1/2 hours).
Form rolls and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti and drain.
Stuff with raw meat mixture.
Pour some sauce over the top and bake in a greased and covered dish for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Add more heated sauce after baked. Sprinkle the top with Parmesan cheese.

title: milk chocolate and peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine peanut butter and butter; beat until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla extract.
Beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup Nestle Toll House milk chocolate morsels.
Spread into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until edges begin to brown.
Sprinkle with remaining Nestle Toll House morsels. Let stand for 5 minutes or until morsels become shiny and soft. Spread chocolate evenly over top.
Cool completely.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch bars.

title: great meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Then shape mixture into 16 meatballs.
Brown the meatballs in a Pam-sprayed skillet. Next, add 1 bottle of T. D. W. spaghetti sauce (96 calories) and 1/3 bottle of water.
Let simmer.

title: tomato aspic soup
directions: Heat soup and juice with cream cheese.
Melt and beat lumps out.

title: corn bake
directions: Mix together all ingredients, stirring well.
Put in buttered dish and bake at 375° until golden brown (about 40 minutes).
So good - hot or cold.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Fix cornbread as directed on package and bake.
Chop tomato, onion and bell pepper in bowl.
Crumble baked cornbread in same bowl.
Mix.
Add mayonnaise and bacon bits.
Top with bacon bits and grated cheese.

title: melanzane ala mozzarella(eggplant with mozzarella)
directions: Lightly sprinkle the eggplant slices with salt on both sides. Place them between two plates and top with a weight.
Let eggplant drain for about an hour.
Salt the tomato slices and let them drain 1 hour.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix granulated sugar, oil, vanilla and chocolate.
Mix in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt. Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls into powdered sugar; roll around to coat. Shape into balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake until almost no indentation remains when touched, 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: frozen chocolate mousse pie
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press on bottom and up side to rim of lightly buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Chill.
In large mixer bowl, beat chocolate with sweetened condensed milk and vanilla until well blended.
Chill 10 to 15 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared crust.
Freeze 6 hours or until firm. Garnish as desired.
Freeze leftovers if any!

title: mom's 8-layer casserole
directions: Cook beef until brown; drain fat.
Stir in next 6 ingredients. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes. In bowl, combine sour cream, cream cheese, milk and onion.
In greased 2-quart casserole, layer half of noodles.
Then add 1/2 of meat mixture, then 1/2 cream cheese mixture and all of spinach. Repeat layers of meat and noodles.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Chill the rest of cheese mixture until casserole has baked.
Remove from oven and spread cheese mixture over top of casserole and sprinkle with 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini puff
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and then add remaining ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch lightly floured and greased pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cut into squares.
May serve warm or cold.

title: mexican chalupa dish
directions: Place all ingredients in a large pan or crock-pot.
Cover with water and cook slowly for 6 to 8 hours.
Stir and break up meat.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Stir together and press onto bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° or until brown.
Let cool.
Sprinkle pecans on top of crust, if desired.

title: carrie's baked chicken
directions: Wash and arrange chicken in baking pan.
Lightly season with onion salt and seasoning salt and pepper.
Add onions and bell peppers over chicken.
Add chicken broth and water.
Bake at 375° for 30
minutes
of
each
side or until golden brown. Serves 5 to 10 people.

title: polka dot cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour and salt. Stir in chocolate chips and raisins.
Bake in a 350° oven until lightly browned, about 12 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: zebra brownies
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients until creamy and fluffy; set aside.
Prepare brownie mix according to package directions. Spread half of brownie mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Pour/spread cream cheese mixture over brownie mixture.
Dollop remaining brownie mixture over cream cheese.
Pull knife through from side to side of pan to create marble effect.
Bake according to package directions.

title: mother's bread pudding
directions: In a 2-quart rectangular casserole, beat together the eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla with a fork.
Place the 6 slices of bread, buttered side up, on the egg mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 375° and cook for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Combine sour cream, flour, sugar, vanilla, salt and egg; beat 5 minutes at medium speed or until smooth.
Fold in blueberries. Pour filling into pastry shell; bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven.
Combine remaining ingredients; stirring well. Sprinkle over top of pie and bake 10 more minutes.
Chill before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: maple fruit dip
directions: In bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients. Cover and refrigerate until serving. Serve with fruit. Yield: 1 cup.

title: chewy bread
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
(I use Pyrex.)
Pour brown sugar into mixing bowl; add melted margarine over the sugar.
Mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: heavenly rice
directions: After rice is cooled, add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.
You can freeze.

title: saucy meat loaf
directions: Combine first nine ingredients; mix well.
Add ground beef and mix thoroughly.
Shape into loaf.
Bake in shallow greased pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit. Reserve 1/2 cup pineapple juice and combine with oranges and pineapple; mix. Add sliced bananas and sliced kiwi.

title: turkey and rice casserole
directions: In a saucepan, bring soda to a boil.
Remove from the heat; stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Stir in strawberries and lemon juice.
Pour into jars or plastic containers.
Cover and refrigerate up to 3 weeks.
Do not freeze.
Yield:
1 3/4 cups.

title: raspberry watermelon slush
directions: In blender or food processor, mix all ingredients thoroughly. Serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 325° to 350°.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare 9 or 10-inch pie plate by spraying Pam to coat, then lining pie dish with separated biscuits on bottom and sides of pie plate; set aside.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Cook
chicken; debone and cut in pieces.
Combine soup, milk, onion and green chilies along with chicken broth and mix well. Grease casserole and add in layers:
liquid first, then chicken, cheese
and
tortilla wedges, ending with liquid and cheese
on top.
Use
2-quart
casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate fudge cookies
directions: Melt chocolate bits and butter; add flour, nuts and milk. Drop on greased sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 325° oven.
May need 9 minutes.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Roast nuts in shallow pan at 400° for 7 minutes.
Be careful not to burn.
Stir in beaten egg white.
Put nuts, sugar, cinnamon and cloves in bag and toss.
Return nuts to pan and reheat for 3 minutes.
Cool completely, then store in a covered container. This makes a nice Christmas gift.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Put pie filling in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over fruit.
Pour melted margarine over whole cake. Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 - 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.
Yummy!

title: fillets of fish with dill
directions: Wash fillets in cold water and pat dry.
Place in flat baking dish, sprayed with Pam.
Melt margarine and mix the lemon juice with it. Pour over the fillets, followed by sprinkling the dill, then the paprika.
Put into the broiler and broil for 10 minutes for each of the thickest parts of the fillet or until the fish flakes.
Serving for one.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400° (moderate hot).
Mix all ingredients until blended.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake for 15 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Brown ribs 15 to 20 minutes.
Place on top 3 thinly sliced onions.
Add other ingredients.
Cook at 325° or until done.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine sugar, turmeric, salt, mustard seed and vinegar. Bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage, onion and green pepper. Refrigerate.
Will keep for weeks.

title: veggie bars appetizers
directions: Press rolls into a 17 1/2 x 14-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.
Mix and spread cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing on pressed rolls.
Sprinkle chopped vegetables evenly over spread mixture.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: white pie
directions: Put cornstarch in 1/2 cup.
Fill rest of cup with flour.
Mix this with sugar.
Add salt and mix.
Add milk, a little at a time, until you get it mixed.
Cook until thick and add vanilla and butter.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and beat until mixed.
Fold hot filling into egg whites.
Mix until well blended.
Put in a baked, cooled pie crust.
Put in refrigerator. Whip 1/2 pint cream with 3 tablespoons sugar.
Put on pie and sprinkle with nuts.

title: cheese garlic rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar and butter.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to sugar mixture.
Add egg; stir in flour, then garlic powder and cheese.
Cover bowl and refrigerate.
Dough will rise in refrigerator.
It can be baked immediately, but it's better refrigerated a few hours or overnight before using.

title: doughnut holes
directions: Fix doughnut holes and shake them in a bag of sugar.
When you are finished shakin' them, then when you eat them, they get really messy and that's all.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix well first three ingredients; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan; sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Dice chicken.
Add to broth.
Bring to a boil.
Add okra, undrained tomatoes, onion, sugar, pepper and 1 teaspoon salt. Cover and simmer until okra is tender, about 45 minutes.

title: made rites
directions: Cook hamburger, pepper and mustard together in double boiler until hamburger is done.
Add salt after cooking.
Steam buns. Spread buns with mustard, dill pickle and chopped onion.
Add hamburger mixture.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Combine orange juice and rind with egg.
Pour into dry ingredients, mixing just enough to dampen.
Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Spoon into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Spread corners and sides higher than center.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Good spread with cream cheese.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Add Cool Whip.
Drain pineapple and add to mixture.
Add pecans.
Pour into two pie crusts and chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: microwave peanut patties
directions: Microwave sugar, water, syrup and salt for 7 minutes.
Stir and add peanuts and cook for another 11 minutes.
Stir and add butter, vanilla and food coloring.
Stir until creamy, then quickly spoon onto wax paper.

title: copper penny carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots without salt; drain and slice.
Mix carrots, onion and green pepper together.

title: chocolate chess pies
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs, butter, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until the filling is set.
Makes 2 pies.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Mix all and mash, knead and squeeze.
Then form into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Butter bottom of small glass, dip in sugar and mash the balls flat.
Re-dip glass for each ball.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 250 cookies.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil and strawberries.
Mix well.
Mix flour, soda, salt and sugar together.
Add egg mixture and mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour 2 cups batter into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan; bake 15 minutes. Meanwhile, in saucepan over low heat, melt caramels, butter and milk, stir until smooth.
Spread evenly over cake that has been baked, the caramel mixture.
Top with nuts, add remaining cake mix.
Return to oven and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes longer or until cake springs back when touched.

title: rice-chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole; cover.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Toss potatoes in 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar and 1/2 cup water.
Grease crock-pot and make layer of potatoes, onion slices, ham and cheese.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Repeat with remaining potatoes and ingredients.
Sprinkle flour over top and then add the cream of mushroom.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or cook on high for 3 to 4 hours.

title: bean chowder
directions: Soak and cook beans.
Add brown sugar.
Brown meat and onion. Drain. Add to the beans.
Combine remaining ingredients and simmer about 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour either muffin tins or loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake muffins 45 minutes and loaf 1 hour.

title: cajun fish
directions: Cut fins off thawed fish; split fish down stomach and remove bone.
Wash fish and drain.
Season fish with seasoned salt, black pepper, red pepper and paprika.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Heat Crisco in skillet.
Beat eggs in a bowl; pour milk into eggs slowly and beat.
Pour corn meal in separate bowl.
Dip fish into milk, egg wash and immediately roll fish in corn meal.
Place fish in hot oil.
Cover pan with lid and let fry until brown.
Turn onto the other side and brown.
Return fish to first side and remove lid. When fish is as crisp as desired, remove fish from skillet and drain on paper towel and serve with side dishes.

title: peanut butter roundups
directions: Mix together the oleo and sugars, then beat in eggs.
Blend in peanut butter.
Sift together all dry ingredients and stir in. Add oats.
Roll dough into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Press with fork or glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: blender broccoli soup
directions: Combine broccoli, onion and broth.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Put in blender and blend until smooth.
Melt butter in pan.
Blend in flour.
Stir in broccoli mixture, cream, salt, pepper and basil. Heat slowly until just boiling; simmer 1 minute, stirring.
Serve with sprinkle of almonds.

title: auntie's jelly roll
directions: Drop eggs in mixing bowl.
Beat well.
Add sugar; continue to beat.
Add water and sifted dry ingredients.
Add flavorings. Bake in 1/4-inch deep sheet cake pan, lined with heavy brown paper that is well greased, at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn out on damp tea towel.
Spread with jelly (grape or blackberry).
Roll and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Serve with warm lemon sauce.

title: hot water gingerbread
directions: Add water to molasses and then add dry ingredients.
Add oleo and beat well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Serve plain or top with Cool Whip.

title: gazpacho soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand for approximately 4 hours at room temperature.
Chill and serve; garnish with chopped cucumber.

title: frozen sweet pickles
directions: Wash real good and boil 2 hours.
Take out the paws and clean. Peel off the skin.
Make any good pickling solution.
Layer in large jar with sliced onions.
Pour cool solution over meat and let set overnight then ready to eat.

title: fried rice
directions: Boil rice; set aside.
Brown sausage; add hot dogs, bell pepper and set aside.
Saute the clove of garlic; add rice and cook 2 minutes.
Mix or add sausage, hot dog, bell pepper, green peas, salt, pepper and egg.
Cook for another 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: microwave peanut butter candy
directions: Put sugar, peanut butter, butter and milk in glass bowl. Place in microwave for 2 minutes.
Remove and stir until blended. Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan.
Chill 20 minutes in freezer.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water (with little salt or none since soup is salty).
Drain and rinse.
Combine other ingredients except crumbs.
Top with the buttered crumbs.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350° or until lightly browned in greased dish.

title: dirty mashed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes. Do not peel.
Cut into 1-inch cubes. Boil until just tender.
Mash the potatoes with butter and milk to desired consistency. Microwave spinach (in package) on High for 3 minutes; drain. Add spinach and salt to mashed potatoes.

title: hidden valley ranch pinwheels
directions: Mix well.
Spread on tortillas and roll up.
Chill and then cut into circles.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed in package.
Pour batter into pan.
Mix remaining ingredients, except chips.
Drop by tablespoonsful onto batter.
Cut through batter with a knife for marbled effect. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Pour milk into blender. Add flour and salt. Blend slightly. Add eggs, one at a time, blending each. Spray muffin or popover pans well. Fill each cup 3/4 full. Bake for 20 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 15 minutes or until golden brown. Do not open oven door while baking.
You may bake 5 minutes longer for a drier popover.

title: darrell's "forget the cookies just give me the batter" chocolate
directions: Melt butter.
While hot, add sugar and brown sugar.
Stir. Let cool.
Beat egg lightly, then add egg and vanilla to butter. Stir.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix with batter mixture. Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Stir.
Cool in fridge for 1 hour. Cook in 375° oven for 12 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix cocoa in hot water; add remaining ingredients; beat well. Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven, cool slightly and frost.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Make sure you mix it well.
Then roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press down, making crisscrosses with a fork.
Cook about 10 minutes or until brown.
Bake at 350°.

title: chili relleno
directions: Split chilies and rinse out seeds.
Lay flat in lightly greased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Grate cheese and spread over top of chilies.
Beat eggs and add sour cream.
Mix well.
Pour over top of cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or when knife comes clean when inserted in center.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Crumble graham crackers in a casserole dish to form the crust.
Set aside.	Pour juice from the peaches into a cup and set aside for later use.
Melt butter in a medium saucepan on medium heat.
Add cornstarch and stir.
Add the juice from the peaches to the butter and cornstarch, stirring well.
Add the water and sugar.
Stir.
Continue cooking until mixture is thick.
Reduce heat.
Add peaches and sour cream and cook on low heat for five to eight minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat and pour mixture into graham cracker crust.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown around the sides.
Remove from heat and allow to cool. Casserole may be refrigerated and reheated.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco, sugar and egg yolks. Add stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into three 9-inch greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: williamsburg orange cake
directions: Measure all ingredients into bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed.
Beat for 3 minutes at high speed, scrape bowl constantly. Pour into pan.
Bake at 350°.
(May be made in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or tube pan or two 9-inch pans.)
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 to 50 minutes and layers about 30 minutes.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients and put in closed 1-quart container. Set out on countertop for 5 hours or until ferments.

title: "baptist" cranberry whip
directions: Grind cranberries. Add sugar and let stand overnight. Add pineapple, nuts and marshmallows. Fold in Cool Whip. Chill until ready to serve. Will keep for days in icebox!

title: raisin sauced beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/3 cup liquid.
In medium saucepan, combine reserved beet liquid and raisins.
Cover.
Simmer until raisins are plump, about 5 minutes.
Combine sugar and cornstarch. Stir into raisins in pan.
Add lemon juice and butter.
Cook and stir over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Stir in beets and simmer until mixture is heated through, about 5 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Combine with soup and sour cream in bowl.
Add potatoes, cheese, salt and pepper, stirring well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Toss corn flakes with 1/4 cup melted margarine. Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: thanksgiving cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except pecans. Beat at medium speed 5 minutes.
Add nuts and mix well; pour batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes. Let cool in pan 10 minutes, then loosen center and sides with plastic spatula.
Invert and tip on wire rack to cool.
Can ice with cream cheese icing or use Cool Whip to serve.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine corn, flour, salt and sugar. Beat eggs, milk and butter. Combine mixtures and pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: almond-chicken casserole
directions: Cook beans and noodles separately according to package directions; drain well.
In bowl, combine yogurt, mayonnaise, wine, salt, parsley, dill, garlic powder and dash of pepper.
In 3-quart casserole dish, layer half of the noodles, beans, chicken, almonds, cheese and yogurt mixture; repeat.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy quiche
directions: Slice about 8 large leeks (white part only), washing first very well.
Saute in a bit of butter until tender.
Place in a pie shell and top with lightly cooked bacon.
Add salt and freshly ground pepper to taste.
Top with another layer of crust that has been pricked with fork.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: macaroni tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Stir in soup, tuna and milk.
Pour into a
greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: stir-fry chicken and melons
directions: Lightly brown chicken in oil, stirring for 5 to 7 minutes. Remove from pan.
Add sherry, cornstarch, honey, lemon juice and ginger. Stir until smooth. Add melon.
Keep stirring lightly for a few minutes. Add chicken. Cover for a couple of minutes. Serve over pasta or Chinese noodles.

title: buttered fettuccine with shrimp
directions: Melt butter and garlic in small saucepan over medium heat. Pour over fettucine and toss.
Add shrimp, cheese and parsley. Season with pepper and toss.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: carrot pineapple cake with nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add sugar and oil; beat until well blended.
Stir in flour and cinnamon; blend thoroughly.
Stir in carrots, undrained pineapple and pecans.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Spread with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: diet stew
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add all ingredients except Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer until well done.
Add Worcestershire sauce.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix soups and mushrooms.
Mix with at least 2 cups broth.
In a casserole dish, layer spaghetti, chicken and broth mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Cook in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey-meatball stew
directions: In large bowl, combine turkey, bread crumbs and egg, mixing gently until well combined.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
In large saucepan or Dutch oven, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add as many meatballs as will fit into pan (do not crowd) and cook, turning to brown on all sides.
As they are browned, remove meatballs to paper toweling to drain.
Discard fat.
Add gravy mix, water and bay leaf and bring to a boil.
Add meatballs and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add carrots and beans and simmer, covered, 8 minutes more.
Stir in corn until heated through.
Discard bay leaf and serve over hot noodles.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook or steam zucchini until tender; drain.
In large bowl beat eggs, stir in mayonnaise, onions, green peppers, herbs and add zucchini.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheddar baked potato slices
directions: 1. In a small bowl, combine soup, paprika and pepper.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Move oven rack to low position so that top of pan will be in center of oven. Heat oven to 350°. Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans. Mix zucchini, sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs in large bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into pans. Bake 8-inch loaves 50 to 60 minutes or 9-inch loaves 1 hour and 10 to 20 minutes.

title: early american coffee cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Set aside 3/4 cup of this mixture for topping.
To rest, add salt, soda and eggs.
Beat well by hand and add buttermilk.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured angel food pan.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup reserved crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes in pan on wire rack.
Using sharp knife, loosen sides from pan.
Invert onto plate and invert again to get right side up.

title: heaven's delight
directions: Whip the cream and set aside.
Drain and cut cherries in half.
Combine 2/3 of the cherries, pineapple, sugar and marshmallows.
Mix together, then mix in 2/3 of the whipping cream.
Smooth the top and put on the remaining whipped cream. Then decorate with the remaining cherries.
Can also use chopped pecans in mixture and to decorate the top.
Refrigerate overnight. Rich and delicious!

title: no-bake blueberry cheese pie
directions: Mix
sugar and cornstarch in medium-size saucepan. Stir in water
until blended.
Add 1 cup of the blueberries.
Stir over medium
heat until mixture thickens and comes to a boil. Reduce heat
and
simmer 2 minutes, stirring constantly until berries release
their
juices.
Remove
from heat and stir in remaining berries.
Cool
to	room
temperature. Beat cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla in bowl until blended.	Spread over bottom of
pie crust. Cover with berry mixture. Refrigerate 2 hours or until chilled.

title: vegetable stir-fry
directions: Blanch broccoli and cauliflower for 3 minutes.
Heat oil in skillet, then put broccoli and cauliflower in hot oil along with other vegetables.
Stir continuously until peppers are tender but still crisp.
Add soup and ginger and heat a few minutes longer. Heat until the soup and ginger are of liquid consistency.
Makes approximately 3 servings.
(Chicken breast, raw shrimp or turkey breast may be added to make one skillet meal.
Chop and cook meat first, then add the vegetables.)

title: chicken & stuffing casserole
directions: Cut up Chicken into cubes or small pieces.
Slice up Onion and saute.
Mix in bottom of cooking pan.
Pour Soup over Chicken.
Mix Stuffing Mix and top it over the Chicken and Soup.
Put in oven and cook for 30 minutes or until stuffing is beginning to crust.

title: yummy salad
directions: In large pot, add water and marshmallows.
When marshmallows are melted, add jello.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Add juice, cabbage and pineapple.
Chill until thickened.
Add whipped topping, mayonnaise and nuts.
Stir gently.
Chill until firm. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: welsh raisin bread
directions: Cover raisins with water and boil for 10 minutes.
Drain, reserving 1 cup of liquid and return to boiled raisins.
Add the shortening and set aside to cool.
When cool, add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to raisin mixture.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake for 1 hour.
Turn out on rack to cool.
Can cut 20 to 22 slices.
Serve buttered.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: dorothy waddington's stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off top of each pepper.
Remove seeds.
Cook 5 minutes in boiling salted water.
Drain; set aside.
Combine meat, rice, 1/4 cup of tomato sauce and remaining items.
Stuff peppers and place in small baking pan.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over stuffed peppers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Baste peppers twice with drippings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until brown.
Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute.
Remove to cooling rack.

title: hot! hot! buffalo wings(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cut chicken wings into sections; discard the tips.
Wash chicken parts thoroughly in water.
Drain on paper towels or strainer.
Put chicken in bowl. Add seasoning salt and pepper to taste.
Stir with large spoon to coat all chicken pieces.

title: grape catsup
directions: Cover grapes with vinegar and let stand all night.
Cook grapes and strain through sieve.
Cook until creamy.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and onions in 1/4 cup salt and ice water for 2 or 3 hours.
Drain and rinse well.
Pack in a gallon container. Combine vinegar, sugar and spices and pour mixture over cucumbers and onions.
Refrigerate.

title: pretzel strawberry salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar. Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 7 minutes.
Watch closely.
Let cool.
Mix together cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over first layer.
Mix jello with boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Refrigerate until mixture begins to congeal, then pour over second layer.
Return to refrigerator until completely congealed.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Beat egg lightly.
Add water, then salmon, bread crumbs, chopped onion, salt, pepper and melted butter.
Mix well.
Mold in loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: jack's tarts
directions: Have cream cheese and butter at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients and form into 1-inch balls.
Press hole into ball with thumb.
Fill with apricot preserves and bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain.
Separate crescent rolls. Place in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with point toward center. Press over bottom and sides to form a crust.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes; top with cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan over all.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cougar punch
directions: Add sugar to hot tea.
Stir until dissolved.
Add juices. Serve hot or cold.
Say "Cougar Cheer" after enjoying this delicious treat!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cover with grated cheese.
Sprinkle Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: *May substitute 2 cups shredded Cheddar cheese for this topping.

title: tangy mushrooms
directions: Marinate button mushrooms in creamy Italian dressing several hours or overnight.
Serve in dressing with toothpicks.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine flour, butter, salt, sugar, eggs and sour cream.
Add yeast mixture.
Blend well.
Divide dough into 2 pieces.
Roll each part to 1/4-inch thickness as for jelly roll.
Spread with layer of soft butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Roll as for jelly roll.
With sharp floured knife, cut into 2-inch slices.
Place on greased pan and allow to rise until light or doubled in bulk.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes.
May be sliced to 1-inch if smaller rolls are desired.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix and pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: french dressing
directions: Beat all ingredients together with rotary beater or shake well in tightly covered jar. Keep in covered jar in refrigerator. Shake again to mix before using as it separates on standing.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Put initial starter in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days; you can feed on the third, fourth or fifth day with listed ingredients. Mix well; add to starter and let stand out of refrigerator for 8 to 12 hours (all day).
When bubbly, take out one cup for bread. Return starter to refrigerator.
Wait 3 to 5 days to feed again. If you don't make bread after feeding 3 times, discard one cup or give to a friend.
This is to avoid deflating starter. supper time and then bake.

title: mushroom stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until soft.
Add mushrooms and cook until they are soft.
Add lemon, tarragon, paprika and mix well.
Blend vegetable stock and tahini.
Pour over mushroom mixture and mix well; remove from heat, add tomatoes and season, if necessary, with fresh ground pepper and some tamari.
Spoon over noodles and garnish with parsley.

title: beef and tater tots casserole
directions: Pat out ground beef in bottom of baking dish.
Cover with onions, celery soup, cheese and top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until meat is done.

title: venison bake
directions: Cook venison in slow cooker 8 to 10 hours, adding bay leaf, beef fat, garlic and 1 onion.
When cooked, remove meat.
Remove from bone.
Cut meat into 2 or 3-inch pieces, removing any fat or membrane from meat.

Place in a large baking dish in single layer. In stew pot, add approximately 1 quart of the broth the meat was cooked in, then add 1 onion, chopped, golden mushroom soup, onion mushroom soup and sliced mushrooms.
Cook over low heat until all ingredients are mixed well.
Pour over meat and bake 45 minutes until bubbly.
Remove bay leaf, onion and beef fat after cooking meat.

title: cheesy chicken crescent supper
directions: Combine chicken and 2 tablespoons cheese. Separate crescent dough. Place 2 tablespoons chicken mixture on wide end of each triangle. Roll up starting at shortest side of triangle and roll to opposite point.

title: tomato soup
directions: Boil tomato juice.
Turn to low heat.
Mix up flour and milk in a separate container until all lumps are gone.
Add slowly to tomato juice, stirring constantly.	Add butter, salt and pepper. Cook for 20 minutes on low heat.
I add 1 teaspoon sugar!

title: braised salmon with roasted almonds(makes 4 servings)
directions: In a mini processor, finely grind the almonds. In a large skillet, heat 3 tablespoons of the olive oil. Stir in the almonds, the onion, cilantro, garlic, anchovies and cayenne and season with salt and pepper. Add the salmon to the skillet and spoon some of the almond mixture on top. Season the salmon with salt and pepper and drizzle with a little olive oil. Cover the salmon and cook over moderate heat for 5 minutes. Reduce the heat to moderately low and cook until the salmon is just opaque throughout, 8 to 10 minutes longer.

title: brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add chocolate, flour and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: cream of onion soup potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into quarters.
If potatoes are very large, may need to cut in smaller pieces.
Place potatoes in a large casserole dish, cover with onion soup mixture and cover with a lid.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 to 1
1/2 hours.
Stir only once, if possible.

title: carob-banana malt
directions: Blend in blender until creamy.
Makes 1 serving.

title: honey bran muffins
directions: Microwave molasses and buttermilk in oven for 2 1/2 minutes. Add butter pieces and stir until melted. Add cereal and stir. Add honey and beaten egg.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir dry mixture into bran mixture.
Stir in raisins. Fill cupcake paper lined tins 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs and flavoring.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt alternately with milk to mixture.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve 1 package yeast in 3 tablespoons warm water.
Set aside.
Beat eggs, sugar, shortening, salt and 1 cup warm water. Add the yeast mix and flour.
Mix well.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight or longer.
Three hours before baking, roll out dough 1/4-inch thick.
Brush with melted butter.
Cut in wedges and roll up.
Let raise 3 hours.
Bake in very hot oven (500°) for 5 minutes.

title: lemon pecan fruit cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo until smooth.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Mix well.
Combine 2 cups flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add lemon extract and mix good.
Coat pecans, pineapple and cherries with the other 2 cups flour.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold into batter the beaten egg whites.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Next day, bake in floured and greased tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan melt butter.
Add onions and saute until soft, about 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in flour and cook on medium heat for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Slowly add milk, parsley and seasonings.
Cook until sauce thickens, stirring frequently.
Stir in cottage cheese and cook, stirring constantly until smooth.
Combine noodles, vegetables and sauce.
Cover and bake 25 minutes.
Remove cover, sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 more minutes.

title: strawberry pleasure
directions: Place
crumbs
in
oblong
dish and pour margarine over them. Mix
well
and press into dish.
Beat cream cheese in a bowl until soft and stir in milk until blended.
Mix in lemon juice and spread over crumb crust.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; stir in berries and pour over cream cheese mix.
Chill until firm.
Serve topped with whipped cream or Cool Whip, if desired.

title: basil zucchini boats
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact; chop pulp.
Place zucchini shells, cut side down, in a shallow baking dish.
Add 1/2 cup water to dish.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain well; return shells, cut side up to baking dish. Saute pulp, red pepper, peas and garlic in olive oil over medium-high heat until pepper is crisp-tender.
Remove from heat; stir in basil.
Spoon mixture evenly into zucchini "boats."
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Broil 6 inches from heat about 1 minute to thoroughly heat.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Serves 4.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until smooth.

title: cornbread good as cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into large iron skillet containing 1/4 cup vegetable oil.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Butter a pan and line with Grape-Nuts.
Beat eggs and sugar, then add vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Add milk and pour mixture into pan.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook cut-up zucchini until tender; drain.
Saute carrots and onions in margarine.
Add tuna or chicken, half the stuffing, soup and sour cream.
Stir in the zucchini.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix everything except cheese crackers.
Put ingredients in buttered casserole dish and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Slit chops to bone; salt and pepper chops and brown on both sides.
Saute onion, celery and parsley until tender-crisp in butter.
Moisten bread cubes with milk.
Add onion mixture and 1/2 teaspoon of sage.
Mix well and stuff each chop.
Mix soup and milk; pour over stuffed pork chops and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: navy - red s.o.s.
directions: Brown the ground beef, salt, pepper and cumin.
Saute and combine the onion, celery and green pepper.
Add flour (for making sauce). Add the tomatoes, tomato sauce and mace.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over toast with hash brown potatoes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: chip beef dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Slice chip beef in small strips.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown onion, pepper and ground meat in 1 tablespoon of margarine.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream and cottage cheese.
Spread half noodles in greased casserole. Cover with cheese mixture and add remaining noodles.
Pour meat mixture on top.
Pour remaining margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; add strawberries and stir until melted.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream over chilled mixture and remaining gelatin mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: salad supreme
directions: Cook spaghetti until done, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain. Add 8 ounce bottle salad dressing (Italian) and coat spaghetti. Add 4 tablespoons Salad Supreme.
Add raw vegetables.

title: instant cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of pan.
Add berries (if berries are extremely sour, a little sugar may be added directly to berries). Pour flour, sugar and milk mixture over berries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: frosty rainbow pie
directions: Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Beat in sugar.
Beat in egg yolks.
Beat in Dream Whip.
Beat in juice.
Pour into pie shell and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: date nut cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, add Crisco, milk and vanilla; beat 2 minutes.
Add 2 eggs and beat 2 minutes more.
Mix in thoroughly, dates and nuts.
Put into pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: batter for deep frying
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix with a fork.
Add egg whites to mixture and beat until smooth. Add enough water to make a smooth and creamy batter.
Dip food into batter and deep fat fry.

title: noodles and cabbage(low-fat)
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package and drain. Shred cabbage.
Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add cabbage and onion and brown well, turning often. When browned, cover skillet and cook 5 minutes longer. Add noodles, salt, pepper and caraway seeds.
Heat through, mixing well. Serve hot. Serves 4.

title: no bake bars
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to boil over medium heat; remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in oats and coconut.
Spread in greased pan.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut into bars.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 36 bars.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Melt jelly in frypan.
Add butter; stir until melted and hot. Add cherries and heat through.
Pour Kirsch over cherries.
Ignite with long match.
Let burn until flame dies.
Spoon hot cherries over ice cream and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: carnation five minute fudge
directions: Combine milk and sugar in a saucepan; heat to boiling.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, chocolate bits, nuts and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Garnish with walnut halves.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: cabbage marinara
directions: Brown onion and ground beef and drain. Mix with rice, cabbage, soups and sugar. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with caraway seeds. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: guacamole spread
directions: Peel and mash avocados.
Combine with tomato, onion, chilies, taco sauce, salt and pepper.
Spread small amount on crispy tortilla chips.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat in a 325° oven for 5 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 1/2 cups spread.

title: milk chocolate brownies
directions: Melt butter and add to rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: stir-fry shrimp, cauliflower and snow peas(chinese)
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets and parboil 2 minutes in boiling water.
Drain and pat dry.
Heat wok.
Add oil.
Stir-fry shrimp until just turning pink.
Add cauliflower.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Add rest of vegetables.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Blend soy sauce with cornstarch.
Stir into wok along with garlic and ginger root.
Stir-fry 1 minute more.
Serve with crunchy bread or over white rice.
Serves 4.

title: barbecued pork tenderloin
directions: Blend together; pour over tenderloin.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator or 3 hours at room temperature.
Roast on rack at 375° for 1 hour or until done.
Baste with marinade at least 2 times.
Slice thin.
Serve with toasted sesame seed, hot mustard and ketchup.

title: quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a deep dish pie shell and bake at 350° until done.

title: waffles
directions: Mix everything together and beat.
Last fold stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix soup and water in large pot; add onion and carrots. Simmer.
Combine ground beef, egg, milk, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.
Make balls; brown.
Add meat balls to soup mixture. Simmer until carrots and onion are tender.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.
Serves 6.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: In 2-quart microwave casserole, cook meat on High 5 minutes; stir after 2 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Mix meat and taco seasoning in separate bowl.
In bottom of casserole, spread beans.
Cover with beef mixture.
Pour soup over meat to within 1 inch of sides. Sprinkle with cheese and olives.
Cook on High 15 minutes or until cheese melts and mixture is bubbly.
Place chips around edge and serve with sour cream.

title: easy fudge
directions: In a small saucepan heat together butter or margarine and water just to boiling, stirring to melt butter or margarine.
Sift together powdered sugar, dry milk powder, cocoa powder and salt into a large mixer bowl.
(If powdered sugar mixture seems lumpy, sift again.)
Add melted butter mixture.
Stir until well blended. Stir in chopped nuts.
Turn into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Chill several hours.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: ham loaf(eight servings)
directions: Combine ingredients; pack into a loaf pan, 10 x 15 x 3 1/2-inch or shape into a loaf in a dripping pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool. Blend cream cheese and sugar with mixer.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread on cooled crust. Chill.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, egg and shortening. Add enough water to make a very stiff dough.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Roll out on floured surface very thin.
Cut into 2 or 3-inch squares.
Deep fry in very hot oil, turning once.
They should puff out when frying.
When cool, serve with honey or your favorite topping.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add onion, Parmesan cheese, parsley, oregano, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add Bisquick, oil and zucchini.
Spray pie pan with Pam lightly.
Spread mixture in pan and top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: mexican appetizer
directions: Blend or mix cream cheese and cottage cheese.
Spread on bottom of platter.
Sprinkle with 1/2 package of taco seasoning. Place onions on top, then green peppers, then tomatoes.
Spread remaining taco seasoning on tomatoes.
Put shredded cheese on top. Garnish with sliced black olives, if desired.

title: two in one peanut pie
directions: Cream
butter
and sugar.
Add syrup, well beaten eggs, peanut butter and vanilla, mixing well.
Turn into pie pan and sprinkle on whole peanuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Let set until cold.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Bake 1 (9-inch) pie crust at 400° for 10 minutes.
Saute onions in bacon drippings; crumble bacon.
Line bacon, onions and cheese on pie crust.
Mix eggs (slightly beaten) with milk and seasonings.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 375° on lower shelf.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl, reserving 1/4 of cheese for top.
spread evenly in large casserole dish and sprinkle with remaining cheese on top evenly.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let cool a bit before serving to allow casserole to become firm.

title: fried apple rings
directions: Wash and core apples.
Do not peel.
Cut into rings.
Saute in butter in a skillet until tender.
Remove from skillet and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: fudgie scotch ring
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch morsels with condensed milk in top of double boiler over hot water.
Stir occasionally until morsels melt and mixture thickens.
Line bottom of a 9-inch pie pan with a 12-inch square of foil.
Place 3/4 cup walnut halves in bottom of pan forming a 2-inch wide ring.
Spoon chocolate on top of nuts in small mounds to form a ring.
Decorate with remaining nuts.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: fruit coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg.
Beat.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and add alternately with milk.
Turn into buttered 9 inch pie pan.
Top with fruit.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake 350 degrees for 20-30 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift together flour, cornmeal, salt, sugar and baking powder in a large bowl. Add milk and egg. Beat one minute. Add 4 tablespoons oil; mix well. Put 2 teaspoons oil in 8-inch square cake pan. Pour in batter. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: worm farm cake
directions: Crush cookies in food processor or blender until mixture looks like dirt; set aside.
Cream the cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Mix pudding mixes and milk for 1 to 2 minutes, until well blended.
Fold pudding mixture into cream cheese mixture, then fold in Cool Whip.

title: apples and dip
directions: For Apples:
Soak apples in pineapple juice overnight.

title: camp stew
directions: Mash meat and partially brown.
Pour off fat, then cover meat with water.
Cover, then finish browning, approximately 30 minutes.
Add corn.
Let simmer another 15 to 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, catsup and Worcestershire and let simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry chutney mold
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Heat cranberry sauce and ginger to	boiling
and use to dissolve gelatin.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Pour	into
large	mold
or several molds until firm.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together
flour,
margarine and nuts and press into bottom of 10 x
10-inch
dish or baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool
Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix instant pudding according to package.
Let
set until thickened.
Spread over cream cheeese layer.
Chill
several
hours.
Spread with Cool Whip before serving.
Cut
in
squares.
Top
with cherries or chocolate shavings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and cook in boiling, salted water. Drain.
Mix all other ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and paprika.
Blend well with squash.
Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° until cheese melts and casserole is piping hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Stir in unbeaten eggs and milk; mix well.
Do not beat.
Bake in crust for 20 minutes at 350°. Preheat oven; you may need to add 5 to 10 minutes longer for baking.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Melt margarine, add to crushed crackers, put into bottom of 8 inch pie plate.
Saute onions till clear.
Spoon into crust.
Beat eggs, milk salt and pepper together.
Pour over onions.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or till set.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream margarine in large mixing bowl at high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually add sugar. Continue beating until light and fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour, frosting mix and walnuts until well blended.
Pour batter into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool 2 hours, then remove from pan.
Cool completely before serving.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add tomato sauce and other ingredients.
Blend.
Pour into molds.
Chill until firm.
Place on crisp green lettuce.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook squash for 1 hour.
Stir often to keep from sticking. Drain off all excess liquid.
Add pineapple, lemon juice, and Sure Jell.
Stir and bring to a boil; add sugar and return to a boil for 6 minutes.
Add Jello and pour immediately into jars. Yield: 6 pints.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cover beans with water and soak overnight or 2 to 3 hours. Drain and cook beans in 2 quarts of water for 45 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly for 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together the pudding and pineapple, blending well.
Add the marshmallows and walnuts. Fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour into a salad mold and chill overnight.
Make 1 or 2 days ahead.

title: old-time rice pudding
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart baking dish, combine first 5 ingredients. Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours, stirring twice during first hour and several times during remaining time.
Add raisins 1/2 hour before pudding is done and allow crust to form again during final baking time.
Serve warm or cold with cream, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: congealed blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Combine juices of berries and pineapple.
If necessary, add enough water to make 1 cup. Add cup of juice to jello mixture. Stir in drained fruit.
Pour into 2-quart flat pan. Refrigerate until firm

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Add fruit and nuts and mix well.
Pinch off teaspoon-sized pieces and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring constantly. This is a great flavor on any meats.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugars and eggs well.
Add vanilla, then oats. Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.

title: butterscotch or chocolate dessert
directions: Mix together and put in bottom of pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Prepare cookie mix as directed and spread onto lightly greased large cookie sheet and bake as directed.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and spread over cooled cookie.
Arrange fruit as desired.
Mix jelly with water to thin and spread glaze over fruits to set.
Refrigerate and serve cool.

title: confetti rice
directions: Combine tomato juice and mixed vegetables in medium saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and pepper.
Cover, turn off heat and allow to stand 6 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cut-out sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill for easier handling.
Roll on lightly floured surface and cut with floured cookie cutter.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes or until edges are light golden brown.
Makes 60 to 72 cookies.

title: brownies for the crowd(i've been using this since 1974; very good and very easy.)
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts in bowl and beat easy, then stir in nuts.
Pour in 11 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot country style steak
directions: Roll steak in flour and brown on both sides in skillet.
Put steak and onions in crock-pot.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and water and pour in skillet steak was browned in.
Bring to a boil and pour over steak and onion in crock-pot.
Cook 2 to 3 hours. I cook mine overnight on low.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and potato chips; turn into shallow buttered casserole.
Combine cheese and potato chips and spread over top.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place alternate layers of potatoes, cheese and onion in a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour milk over mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender and brown.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: glazed spicy nuts
directions: Combine all ingredients in large nonstick skillet, stirring to mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar melts and turns a golden color (8 to 10 minutes).
Remove skillet from heat immediately and spread nuts in single layer on baking sheet.
Cool.

title: lentil soup
directions: Rinse and cook lentil peas in large soup pot according to package directions with marrow bone and peeled onion.
Remove onion and bone after 1 hour and discard.
