Add carrots and simmer for an additional hour, adding more water if necessary and stirring occasionally.
Add potato and hot dogs and simmer an additional 30 minutes until desired consistency.
Season with salt, pepper and thyme to taste.

title: chocolate rice krispies delights
directions: Lightly butter a long Pyrex dish.
In a pot, mix peanut butter, Karo syrup and sugar.
Bring to a light boil, then remove from burner.
In a mixing bowl, add the peanut butter mix with the 6 cups of Rice Krispies.
Press the Rice Krispie mixture down firmly in the buttered Pyrex dish.
Melt the package of chocolate chips with the package of butterscotch chips in a separate bowl, then pour it over the Rice Krispies.
Let it set for an hour, cut into squares and serve.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: lasagna supreme
directions: Cook lasagna according to package directions.
Brown ground beef with onions.
Add spices, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, tomatoes and sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Layer 1/3 meat sauce, lasagna noodles, Mozzarella and cottage cheese.
Repeat, ending with meat sauce and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Place thinly sliced cucumbers and onions in container(s).
Mix solution cold; pour on cucumbers and cover.
Refrigerate 5 days, shaking daily.
Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: maple tofu cheesecake
directions: Mix
ingredients
in
blender
until smooth and creamy. Pour mixture
into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until
set.
Serve
cold, topped with maple syrup and pecans or TOFU CREAMY TOPPING.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit. Save 1/2 cup of pineapple juice. Cut fruit in 1/2-inch cubes and combine with marshmallows and ginger. Soften gelatin in cold water. Heat 1 1/2 cups of pineapple juice to boiling. Add gelatin. Stir to dissolve. Add orange juice, lemon juice, sugar and salt. Stir well to dissolve, then chill. When mixture starts to thicken, add fruit mixture and fold in whipped cream and mayonnaise. Spoon into containers and freeze. Makes 18 quarts.

title: cottage cheese and jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese with mayonnaise.
Dissolve jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in cottage cheese mixture, pineapple, a few chopped nuts, cherries, marshmallows.
Drain pineapple.

title: chili
directions: In Dutch oven, brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients except chili beans.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Stir in beans with gravy; simmer another hour.

title: giblet or meat gravy
directions: Measure fat drippings and return to pan.
Stir in liquid and remove from heat.
Mix cornstarch and cold water.
Stir into pan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until gravy thickens and boils.
Season to taste.
Simmer a few minutes.

title: rice and bean stuffed peppers
directions: Halve peppers lengthwise, removing stem ends, seeds and membranes. Immerse peppers into boiling water for 3 minutes. Invert onto paper towels to dry.

title: pink christmas fruit punch
directions: Combine first 3 items; refrigerate.
At serving time add the club soda.
Serve over ice or pour punch over ice in punch bowl. Serves approximately 35.

title: english hot pot
directions: Remove all fat from steak.
Cut steak into 1 1/2 inch cubes. Place in deep 3-quart casserole dish.
Cover steak with sliced onions, separated into rings.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Add enough water to barely cover meat.
Cover onions with sliced carrots.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Peel potatoes and cut into slices (not too thin).
Rinse well. Layer the potatoes on top of carrots, sprinkling the layers with a little salt.
Brush top layer with melted butter.
Bake at 400°, uncovered, for about 2 1/2 hours.
If top layer of potatoes is becoming too brown, cover loosely with foil during last 1/2 hour of cooking.

title: sour cream rhubarb pie
directions: Put rhubarb in a 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Mix cream, sugar, flour and egg yolks.
Pour over rhubarb and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool slightly.
Beat egg whites and add remaining sugar. Spread over pie and bake about 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy clam chowder
directions: Drain clams.
Mix all ingredients.
Heat and serve with crackers.

title: low calorie vanilla shake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender using high speed.
Blend for about 2 minutes or until ice cubes are melted.
Makes 1 serving; 55 calories.
Diabetic Exchange:
Milk 1/2.

title: orange slice christmas cake
directions: Combine the buttermilk and soda.
Add alternately with the flour mixture to butter and eggs.
Mix well and add fruit mixture. Pour into a 10-inch tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
While cake is still hot, pour a combination of 2 cups powdered sugar and 1 cup orange juice (canned, not frozen) over cake.
Let cool, then refrigerate overnight before removing from pan.

title: aunt mary lee's fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Save juice.
Slice bananas and marinate in reserved juice about 5 to 10 minutes. Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl together.
Chill.

title: pistachio green salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir until mixed well.
Chill. Serves 6.

title: ham cheese delight
directions: Cook onion in butter.
Add chopped ham, eggs, cheese, cracker crumbs, milk and dash of pepper.
Mix well; turn into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: butter shortbread cookies
directions: Heat oven to 300° (slow).
Mix shortening and sugars thoroughly.
Measure flour by dipping or sifting.
Mix flour and salt; stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick on floured board.
Cut in desired shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 7 1/2 dozen small cookies.

title: cake glaze
directions: Mix all together in pan.
Cook until dissolved and pour over any loaf or Bundt cake.

title: quick chocolate fudge cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar in a large bowl and set aside. Put margarine, water and cocoa in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Pour over sugar and flour, then add eggs, buttermilk, cinnamon, soda and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel glaze
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil over low heat.
Boil 10 minutes; stir occasionally.
Pour over hot cake.

title: mixed fruit with lemon sauce
directions: Put pudding over pineapple and dissolve.
Add other fruit and mix lightly; chill.
Serve with cake.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together and pour in graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: salmon mousse with dill
directions: In a small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over cold water or clam juice; let stand until softened, about 5 minutes.
Warm over medium heat until gelatin is dissolved; let cool to room temperature.
Stir in dill, onion, lemon juice, salt, Tabasco, yogurt, sour cream and celery.
Refrigerate until mixture begins to set.
Process salmon in a food processor; mix into gelatin mixture.
Spoon into a 4-cup mold.
Cover and refrigerate until firm, at least 3 hours.
Unmold onto serving plate; surround with crackers, Melba toast or fresh vegetables.
Makes 4 cups.

title: glazed nuts
directions: Boil sugar and water until crystallized.
Add nuts and cinnamon.
On a greased cookie sheet, spread apart, to separate. Store in a closed container.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Season meat and brown.
Add onion, tomato sauce and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cooked rice and steamed cabbage.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with cheese.
Allow cheese to melt.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Add soda to tomato soup.
Beat sugar and shortening; add egg and beat well.
Add tomato soup and dry ingredients.
Beat well. Fold in raisins, nuts and grated orange rind.
Bake in greased and floured baking pan at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Cook bacon in a large, deep skillet over medium high heat, until evenly browned.

Drain, crumble and save. Combine the bacon, cauliflower, broccoli, onion, sunflower seeds and raisins. Whisk together dressing, vinegar, and sugar. Pour over the salad and toss to coat. Chill before serving.

title: heavenly delight salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello.
While hot add marshmallows and mayonnaise.
Beat until marshmallows dissolve.
Cool.
When mixture begins to set, add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
When firm, cut into squares.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and vanilla; add eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Form into tiny balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with back of fork to make crisscross.
Dough may be rolled, if desired.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes or until well done.
Yield: 8 dozen cookies.

title: baked bean hamburger casserole
directions: Simmer hamburger and onion, season with salt and pepper, cook until done.
Add baked beans.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, mustard, brown sugar and ketchup.
Add more or less of these ingredients if needed for taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in casserole dish.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Combine popcorn and pecans in a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Mix well and set aside.
Melt butter over low heat in a medium saucepan.
Add brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat; stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour syrup over popcorn mixture, stirring until popcorn is evenly coated. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring after 15 minutes.
Cool completely and break into pieces.
Store in airtight container. Yield:
9 cups.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients. Store in a tightly covered container.

title: drop cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil.
Add peanut butter.
Stir and mix well.
Add corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper. Cool and eat.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, salt, baking powder, 2 tablespoons cocoa, milk and vanilla.
Add to butter and mix.
Then mix 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa in bowl.
Put these dry ingredients over the batter; do not mix.
Put in oven and then pour water over top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
To serve, spoon out and flip so pudding will drizzle over cake.

title: chocolate eclaire cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place a layer of graham cracker squares. Mix pudding as directed on box.
Let sit 5 minutes to set.
Stir in 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 pudding mixture over crackers. Spread remaining pudding into pan.
Top with third layer of crackers.
Carefully spread chocolate frosting over crackers. Chill overnight.
Makes 12.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.

title: miss ola's banana nut bread
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes two loaves.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix cheese and soft oleo; add sifted dry ingredients.
Roll thin and cut into strips or put through a cookie press.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for about 10 or 12 minutes.
You can also roll into small balls and press half a pecan in each.

title: pocketbook rolls
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix in shortening.
Add milk, all at one time, then mix until all ingredients form balls. Knead lightly 2 or 3 minutes.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with floured 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Fold double and press edges together.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Cover; let rise in warm place for 20 minutes.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 10 minutes. Again, brush with butter and bake another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini carrot casserole
directions: Melt first amount of butter in a frying pan.
Slice unpeeled zucchini 1/4-inch thick.
Saute zucchini slices, carrot and onion until tender.
This will need to be done in batches.
Add more butter, if necessary.
Stir in soup, cream, bouillon powder, first amount of crumbs and salt.
Transfer to 2-quart baking dish.
Melt remaining butter in small saucepan.
Stir in remaining crumbs. Scatter over top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for about 25 minutes.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Place chilies in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch casserole. Sprinkle with cheeses.
Pour eggs over the top.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 24 squares.

title: pumpkin blender pie
directions: Blend 1 minute and pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: ben's meat balls
directions: Combine al ingredients and make 2-inch balls.
Brown quickly in hot olive oil.
Cook in spaghetti sauce for 2 hours, slowly. Makes about 10 meat balls.

title: chinese new year rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet or wok over medium-high heat.
Add chicken.
Cook and stir until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook and stir until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet roll cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased and floured long pan.
Mix together 1 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Sprinkle over the top of cake.
Swirl throughout the batter.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: baked bluefish
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Wash the fish and dry them.
Place the fish in a single layer on a large sheet of foil, skin side down.
Place foil in a shallow baking pan.
Season the fish with salt and pepper to taste and sprinkle with the minced onions. Spread a thin layer of mayonnaise over it.
Seal foil over fish. Bake 40 minutes; uncover fish and bake for 10 minutes until browned.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: In 3 quart casserole, stir together sugar, salt and milk mixing well.
Add chocolate and butter.
Cover.
Microwave at High 6 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Stir well.
Microwave at Medium 10 to 14 minutes, uncovered.
Stir well every 5 minutes.
When sufficiently cooked, a few drops of mixture will form a soft ball in cup of cold water (235° candy temperature). Let candy stand without stirring at room temperature until lukewarm.
Add vanilla; beat with spoon or mixer until thickens and loses its gloss. Quickly stir in nuts and pour into 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf dish which has been lined with wax paper or butter sides and bottom.
Cut when set.

title: joe lacey's pie crusts
directions: In a 1 cup measurer combine the egg and vinegar.
Then fill the measuring cup with water to make 1 full cup.
Mix the egg, vinegar and water.

title: army and lou's candied sweet potatoes
directions: In large, covered pot of boiling water, cook sweet potatoes for 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are nearly tender.
Cool until easy to handle.
Peel and cut lengthwise into 3/4-inch slices; arrange slices in a buttered or foil-lined 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine sugars, cornstarch, cinnamon, lemon peel, nutmeg and salt to taste in saucepan.
Stir in lemon juice and water until smooth.
Add butter, heat to boiling over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally.
Pour mixture over sweet potatoes. Bake, uncovered, in preheated 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mom's strawberry preserves
directions: Wash and drain strawberries.
Combine with 1 1/2 cups sugar in large saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add remaining 1 1/2 cups sugar and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 4 minutes, stirring constantly. Spoon into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace; seal with 2-piece lids.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield:
3 cups.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs and corn; beat thoroughly.
Add butter and milk; mix well.
Bake in pan of water in moderate oven until knife blade comes out clean when stuck in middle of pudding.

title: strawberry cake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll dough into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender.
Add rice and soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: banana bread ii
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, sugar and salt together.
Add mashed bananas, orange juice, egg, oil and vanilla; mix well.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers, veggies, etc.

title: chef's garden salad
directions: Combine lettuce, tomato, cucumber, celery and pepper.
Put in a large bowl.
Add 1/2 cup dressing, tossing well.
Arrange ham, chicken, cheese and eggs on salad.
Serve with additional dressing, if desired.

title: berniece's soup
directions: Brown ground meat and onion.

Add salt and pepper to taste. After meat is browned, add other ingredients and cook about 30 minutes. May add a little water if it cooks down too much.	Good served with grated cheese and sour cream on top.

title: divinity
directions: Heat sugar, syrup and water over low heat.
Stir until sugar is dissolved, then cook without stirring to 255°.
Remove from heat.

title: spanish rice
directions: Chop green pepper and onions.
Cook bacon; drain drippings.
In skillet, saute pepper, onions and tomato paste.
Cook Minute rice; add to other ingredients.
Serves 4.

title: carrot-cranberry salad
directions: Place carrots and dried cranberries in a bowl.
In another bowl mix together salad dressing, sugar, and enough milk to reach a salad dressing consistency.
Pour over carrot mixture and toss to coat.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger, ground turkey, cracker crumbs and Lipton onion soup mix.
Roll into medium size meat balls.
Using cooking spray, lightly coat a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place uncooked meat balls in pan. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat balls.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Yields approximately 63 meat balls.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Place bread slices in bottom of baking dish.
Mix together eggs, milk, dry mustard and lemon pepper.
Place the sausage next (over bread), grated sharp cheese and then egg ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, turn oven to 300°.
Add cream of mushroom, celery or chicken soup
mixed with milk.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Place cream cheese in bowl.
Beat with mixer until soft and smooth.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except nuts.
When thoroughly mixed, add nuts.
Press on waxed paper or in well-greased shallow pan and chill until firm.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch dish. Layer whole dish with graham crackers. (Be sure bottom is completely covered.) Mix together instant pudding and milk. Refrigerate for 10 to 15 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip. Put 1/2 pudding on graham crackers, then another layer of crackers and remaining pudding. Top with another layer of crackers. Spread on frosting. Refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: glamour beans
directions: Cook green beans according to package directions and drain. Saute chopped onion in a small amount of butter until tender. Saute pepper separately in small amount of butter until tender. (Onion will become tender before pepper and crunchiness is important.)
Brown almond slivers in butter until tender.
Add mushroom soup to drained beans, then mushrooms, onion, green pepper, sliced water chestnuts, bean sprouts, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Place in casserole; top with crumbs, which have been crushed, then cheeses and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour and oats.
Add salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Last add chips, grated chocolate and nuts.
Roll into balls.
Place 2-inches apart. Bake 8 to 10
minutes at 375°.
Will not look done. Take out and let rest a few minutes, then take off sheet.
Will firm up as they cool.
Makes 200 cookies.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour. Roll out thin.
Cut into squares (approximately 2-inch squares). Put small amount of apricot filling in center.
Fold 2 edges together.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: great garlic chicken
directions: Combine butter, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice. Heat on low until butter is melted.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese on plate.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Dip each piece in butter mix, then in crumb mix.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix together in a saucepan, the sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Stir in beet juice and vinegar.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add beets and butter.
Again bring to a boil, stirring gently.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix in order given.
Fold sliced eggs in lightly.
Pour in greased casserole dish (use spray).
May add pimentos or ripe olives to add color.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Beat eggs. Mix in next 5 ingredients with spoon. Add walnuts. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; cool.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Mash the potatoes.
Add butter, sour cream, cream cheese, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Sprinkle the shredded cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Put the ingredients in a plastic bag.
Close with a bag tie and shake.
Place 2 to 3 heaping teaspoonfuls of mix in a cup. Add boiling water and stir.

title: divinity
directions: Place sugar, syrup and water in a pan over low heat, stir only until sugar is dissolved, then cook until a little piece tried in cold water forms a soft ball.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Continue beating and pour 1/2 of syrup slowly over eggs. Continue beating while cooking the rest of the syrup until if forms a hard ball when dropped in a cup of cold water.
(It should crack when if hits against side of cup.)
Add this syrup gradually to the syrup and egg mixture you are beating.
Add vanilla and continue beating until candy is thick enough to drop from spoon. Place by spoonfuls onto buttered platter.
If desired, nuts can be added just as the candy is ready to spoon.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in salad bowl except Fritos and dressing.
At serving time, toss in crushed Fritos.
Top with Catalina dressing.
Also good with some cooked ground beef added.

title: fried zucchini
directions: Wash each zucchini thoroughly. Cut into 1/2-inch slices. Combine bread crumbs, salt & pepper. Dip each zucchini slice in bread crumb mixture. Fry in oil for 5 min. on each side. Serves 6.

title: chow mein
directions: Brown hamburger and pork.
Saute green pepper and onion, then add to meat.
Add the celery and soy sauce.
Cover with water just to top of mixture.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
When celery is cooked, add cornstarch to water to thicken.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Very easy and delicious!

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts in water and seasonings.
Cook until tender, drain and cut in bite-size pieces.
Set aside 1 cup of chow mein noodles.
In a 3-quart casserole, combine rest of noodles with soup, water, milk, chicken, nuts, celery, onions and mushrooms.
Taste and salt if nuts are unsalted.
Sprinkle reserved noodles over top. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
If it appears too dry, add more milk.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: brownie pie
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until it peaks.
Add sugar gradually until stiff.
Fold in crumbs, nuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly in a lightly buttered pie pan and bake at 325° for about 35 minutes. Do not overbake.
Fill with whipping cream and 1/4 cup sugar.

title: vege-chicken soup
directions: Cook vegetables.
Add soy chicken, noodles and water.
Mix seasonings and cornstarch with a little water in glass until smooth and add to soup.
Cook until noodles are done.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift
all
dry	ingredients
together
except for sugar. Combine
eggs, sugar, oil and molasses.
Add this to dry ingredients.
Add
water and beat until smooth.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased
and
floured pan for 40 minutes in a 350° oven. Serve with lemon sauce.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix as you would any cake by hand. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Spoon batter into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until done.

title: strawberry-rhubarb butter(microwave)
directions: Place strawberries and rhubarb in a 4-cup glass measure. Cover with plastic wrap turned back slightly on one side. Microwave on full power until rhubarb is tender, 5 to 7 minutes, stirring once.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature for approximately 30 minutes.
At the same time, freeze cookie dough.
Slice cookies and layer bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. You may have to cut some cookies in half to line sides.
Let cookies soften while you make the filling.

title: holiday cranberry-jello salad(teacher favorite)
directions: Make jello according to instructions on package, using 1/2 the amount of cold water.
Add pineapple and cherries with juice.
Add pecans and chopped cranberries.
Chill in refrigerator for 4 hours before serving.
Cut in squares to serve.
Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: pasta ala puttanesca
directions: In heavy skillet, put olive oil and garlic; saute briefly. Lower flame.
Add anchovies and mash with fork.
Add tomatoes; cover and cook at high flame for 5 minutes, stirring at least twice.
Add Gaeta olives and capers; cook at medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from flame and add parsley. Pour over cooked pasta; serve hot.
Black pepper may be added to taste.

title: homemade caramel
directions: DO NOT PUT HOLES IN CAN!!
Place can in pot of boiling water.
Boil for at least 3 hours.
Open can and serve.

title: graham cracker treat
directions: Dissolve brown sugar in butter; add pecans, coconut and corn flakes.
Mix well.
Line a cookie sheet with single graham crackers.
Put 1 tablespoon of mix on each cracker.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: german hot bacon dressing
directions: Cook all above ingredients like you make gravy.
Excellent for cold slaw or potato salad.
For potato salad, fry bacon and keep about 2 tablespoons of the grease.
Cut up about 1 cup of celery and saute.
Boil potatoes, cool and slice and put in dish with chopped fine raw onions and refrigerate overnight.
In morning heat sauce and add to potatoes.

title: garlic bread
directions: In 1 cup glass measure, microwave butter on High for 30 to 45 seconds, until melted.
Stir in garlic powder and parsley.
Brush butter on one side of bread slices.
Microwave on High for 1 minute and 30 seconds, or until heated through.

title: chinese cheese wafers
directions: Mix well.
Roll into small balls and press with fork.
Cook at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: coffee liqueur velvet frosty
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender container; blend until smooth.
Serves six.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients; bake in a 2 quart Pyrex dish at 300° for 1 hour.

title: date nut cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Bake 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: south-of-the-border soup
directions: In a heavy skillet, melt 1 tablespoon of butter.
Add ground beef and cook, stirring to break into small pieces.
Drain well. Set aside.

title: sunday chicken-rice bake
directions: In bowl, stir together mushroom soup, milk, dry onion soup mix and undrained mushrooms.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the soup mixture and set aside.
Stir uncooked rice into remaining soup mixture.
Turn rice mixture into a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken pieces on top.
Pour reserved soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle chicken pieces with paprika.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° until rice is tender, about 1 hour.*
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: deep fried fish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Ziploc bag.
Put fish in bag and shake well.
Remove fish and put in deep fryer until golden brown.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut peeled eggs lengthwise into halves.
Slip out yolks; mash with fork.
Mix in salt, mustard, pepper, mayonnaise and relish. Fill halves with mixture.
Garnish with light dusting of paprika. Refrigerate on serving dish, covered.
Serves 6.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown meat in fat; add beef stew mix, onions, water, catsup and paprika.
Cover.
Simmer 2 hours.
Remove cover and simmer 1/2 hour longer.
Serve over noodles.

title: bates avenue chicken
directions: Combine cranberry sauce, salad dressing, soup mix, salt and pepper to taste.
Arrange chicken in 3-quart baking dish; pour sauce over top.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove cover; bake 15 minutes more or until brown.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: easy cheese danish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine cream cheese, vanilla and sugar in a mixer bowl; beat until well blended. Unroll crescent dough from 1 can and place on a greased cookie sheet, sealing the perforations. Spread cream cheese filling over dough; top with jam. Unroll the remaining crescent roll dough and place over jam, sealing edges with a fork. Brush with beaten egg and bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick and easy coffeecake
directions: Combine egg, sugar, milk and shortening. Add flour, baking powder and salt. Mix well and pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with mixture of 1/4 cup brown sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1 tablespoon flour, 1 tablespoon melted butter and 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fiesta roll-ups
directions: Drain green chillies.
In a food processor, mix the cream cheese, taco seasoning mix, green chillies and ripe olives until blended, about a minute.
Spread the mixture on the tortillas and roll up, jelly roll style.
Place the rolls on a plate and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, slice each roll into 1-inch sections.
Use party toothpicks to serve.
Makes about 80 slices.

title: smoked turkey
directions: Pour Morton Tender Quick salt and Morton canning salt in a 5 gallon bucket with a lid.
Add your turkey, then fill with water above turkey.
Soak for 24 hours.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, then turn down to 250° for 2 hours.

title: chinatown chops
directions: In a large skillet, brown pork chops.
Remove chops and brown 1 package fried Rice-A-Roni with butter.
Stir in hot water, mushrooms (undrained) and contents of vegetable sauce envelope. Place browned chops on top.
Sprinkle with soy sauce.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into a pie shell.
Bake the pie shell and let cool or put in graham cracker crust.

title: 30 minute chocolate cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and cocoa.
Set aside.
Bring margarine, oil and water to rolling boil and pour over dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; set aside.
Mix together vanilla, buttermilk and soda; stir until buttermilk foams.
Add to previous mixture.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: peanut butter krispies
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to a rolling boil.
Remove from fire; add peanut butter (chunky or creamy).
Mix well; add Rice Krispies. Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Reserve chicken broth.
Mix together soups and milk.
Grease two 2-quart casserole dishes.
Alternate layer of chicken (in small pieces) with soup mixture, leaving soup mixture on top.
Moisten dressing mix with chicken broth and pat on top of soup mixture.
Cook until brown in 350° oven.
Makes 2 casseroles.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in Crisco until looks like wet meal.
Add water.
Roll out and put in pie pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients except pecans.
Place ball in refrigerator overnight.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or two layers at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: meat loaf 1
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.

title: grilled seafood brochette with orange-tarragon vinaigrette
directions: To make vinaigrette, combine the orange juice and the next 7 ingredients.
Beat in oil; reserve.

title: wild rice chicken
directions: Cook rice.
Combine rice with chicken, water chestnuts, celery and onion.
(Mixture can be stored in 1-gallon freezer bag.)
tags: quick-cooking long grain and wild rice

title: cinnamon apple salad
directions: Dissolve red hot candies in hot water.
Add jello.
Stir well. Add cold water.
Cool until it begins to set.
Add celery, apples and nuts.
Cool until set well.
I have used crushed pineapple instead of celery.

title: festive shrimp dip
directions: Heat cheese and mushroom soup. Dissolve gelatine in 3 tablespoons water. Mix gelatine with cheese mixture. Add balance of ingredients. Mix well. Pour in jello mold. Chill overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: mandarin-grapefruit congealed salad
directions: Pour 2 cups hot water over jello.
Add 1 cup juice from mandarin oranges.
As it cools, add mandarin oranges and drained grapefruit.
Refrigerate.

title: nona's bow ties
directions: Beat together the eggs and sugar in a medium bowl until the mixture is light and fluffy.
Stir 1 1/2 cups of the flour, the vanilla and lemon rind until blended.
Shape into a ball.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in jars and keep in refrigerator.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut steak into bite-size cubes.
Shake with the flour to coat, being sure all flour is used.
Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Brown steak pieces on all sides.
Remove from heat.
Add onion, parsley, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Stir in mushrooms, Burgundy and water.
Heat mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for about 1 hour, or until meat is tender. Remove bay leaf.

title: cheesy fish chowder
directions: Cut fish in 1-inch cubes.
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add onion, carrot, potatoes and celery.
Cook until onion is transparent.
Blend in flour and salt.
Gradually add chicken broth and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add fish.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus.
Reserve liquid.
Alternate layers of asparagus, crushed crackers and boiled egg slices.
Pour reserved asparagus liquid over this.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with black pepper.
Top with mushroom soup.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix; marinate meat at least 1/2 hour.
Great with steak or chicken.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apple slices in buttered 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon, salt and water.
Combine flour, sugar and butter.
Drop this mixture over the apples. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with cream.

title: beef wellington
directions: *May substitute venison tenderloin.

title: chicken-pork adobo
directions: Cut chicken and pork into serving pieces.
Put in a cooking dish and add the rest of the ingredients except salt and oil. Cover and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and cook slowly until the meat is almost tender.
Add salt and oil.
Continue cooking, uncovered, stirring occasionally to prevent scorching.
Remove from fire when chicken and pork are tender and brown.

title: broccoli with orange sauce
directions: Wash broccoli, cook in small amount of salted water until crisp-tender.
Melt margarine in saucepan, blend in flour, cook until bubbly.
Add orange juice, salt, cook stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Pour sauce over hot broccoli; sprinkle with paprika.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: sweet potato cake squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add balance of ingredients.
Pour in long dish, greased.
Bake at 300° for one hour.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix butter, cake mix and 1 egg.
Pat in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs, confectioners sugar and vanilla; pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: Rub seasoning over turkey and put some inside.
Sprinkle pepper all over turkey.
Marinate 24 to 48 hours.
Deep fry 4 minutes per pound.

title: artichoke dip
directions: *Important to use Hellmann's for proper consistency.

title: tea cake cookies
directions: Cream butter to consistency of mayonnaise.
Add sugar gradually while continuing to cream.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat until light.

title: manzo ripieno(stuffed rolled beef)
directions: Slice sirloin or round steak in one piece (approximately 1 pound), butterflied and flattened.
Make omelet from 3 eggs.
Cook raw spinach; squeeze dry or beat frozen spinach.
Cut salt pork into very small pieces; saute until crisp.
Coarse chop parsley. Spread spinach on steak; place garlic (uncooked) on top of spinach. Place omelet on top of spinach.
Sprinkle cheese on egg; place parsley on cheese.
Add pepper and salt to taste.
Roll up, jelly roll style.
Tie with string.
Saute in oil and butter for 12 to 15 minutes.
Add red wine; saute for 10 to 15 minutes, covered.
Slice like jelly roll.
May be eaten hot or cold.

title: carrots (shaker recipe)
directions: Clean the carrots and cut into thin strips.
Cook until tender in salted water, about 10 minutes.
Mix together grated onion, horseradish, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and water.
Pour over carrots.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake about 15 minutes at 375°.

title: linda gorton's pasta salad
directions: Cook the pasta 7 minutes; drain and rinse.
Mix all ingredients together and let sit in refrigerator for a few hours. Stir before serving.

title: spinach custard
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake for at least an additional 20 minutes.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Cut off necks of squash and slice thinly in saucepan with melted butter.
Add onion; cut rest of squash in two.
Scoop out seeds, discarding larger seeds.
Add to saucepan; place squash cut-side down in top of pan, cover, heat slowly and cook about 10 minutes.
Remove squash from top with fork, mash slices to break up, add cracker crumbs, garlic salt and cheese.
Fill squash cavities, put in greased pie pan and bake in oven at 350° about 20 minutes or until browned on top.
Serves 4.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and pasta.
Mix.
Best when served cold.

title: deviled crab
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in crab backs or buttered casserole.
Sprinkle a few crumbs on top.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° until browned.

title: olive-nut sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a small bowl and blend well.

title: home baked beans
directions: Wash beans; cover with water and soak overnight.
Cook slowly until skins burst or until tender.
Drain; reserve liquid.
Place 1/2 the beans in bean pot or casserole.
Bury part of pork in beans and add 1/2 of combined remaining ingredients.
Add remaining beans and seasoning.
Place remaining pork over top.
Cover with bean liquor.
Cover and bake in slow oven (250° to 300°) for 6 to 8 hours.
Add more liquid if necessary.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Put in mixing bowl and beat thoroughly the shortening, brown sugar, granulated sugar, egg, water and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to shortening mixture and mix well.
Blend in oats, then chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chopped beef spread
directions: Chop lunch meat into small pieces.
Slice green onions into small circles.
Blend with cream cheese using a fork.
Sprinkle one teaspoon Worcestershire sauce over mixture and blend again. Serve on crackers.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Saute onion and garlic in melted margarine until yellow; set aside.
Brown ground beef; drain well.
Put meat in pot with all ingredients.
Cook slowly on top of stove, stirring occasionally. Cook 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve on rolls.
Serves 6.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until done. Drain. Add all ingredients except dressing. Add it just before serving.

title: eggless, milkless raisin cake
directions: Cook together brown sugar, water, raisins and oil until it bubbles all over.
Cool, then add flour, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Dissolve soda in warm water and add to mixture, stirring well.
Bake 40 minutes in oven at 350°.
Frost with brown sugar frosting.

title: hershey's fudge recipe
directions: Line 8 or 9-inch square pan with foil.
Butter foil and set aside.
In heavy 4-quart saucepan, stir together sugar, cocoa and salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to full, rolling boil.
Boil, without stirring, to 234° or until syrup, when dropped in very cold water, forms a soft ball, which flattens when removed from water.
(Bulb of candy thermometer should not rest on bottom of saucepan.)

title: sourdough
directions: Mix flour and water.
Sour in a warm place.
Also, add sugar for Herman.
Add salt and soda and thicken with flour and knead and bake.

title: teeny weenies
directions: Put all ingredients in pan and simmer 1 hour.
Use cocktail hot dogs or cut regular hot dogs into 1-inch chunks.
Serve in fondue pot or chafing dish with toothpicks.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Beat together ingredients except pecans.
Mix in the pecans. Pour into pastry lined pan. Bake until set and pastry is browned at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes a 9-inch pie.

title: cauliflower-broccoli medley
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Bake, cool, peel and cube potatoes.
In a large soup kettle or Dutch oven, melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Heat and stir until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until smooth. Add potatoes and onions.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add bacon, cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.

title: paste
directions: Add 1/2 cup flour to 1 cup boiling water.
Stir over low heat until thick and shiny.
Let cool and store in a covered container.

title: mo's famous barbecue
directions: Wash meat in cold water.
Place 5 large sheets of aluminum foil on counter.
Place layer of onion and bell pepper on foil with desired spices.
Place meat in middle of foil.
Pour entire bottle of barbecue sauce on meat.
Wrap foil to completely cover meat.
Smoke meat or oven; cook at 160° to 180°.
If using pit, keep fire on opposite end 6 hours for 5 pounds, 12 hours for 10 pounds and 18 hours for 20 pounds.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugars and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 325° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix in order given and shape into balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour, crisscross.
Bake in 375° oven for 10
to 12 minutes.

title: country salisbury steak
directions: Mix ground beef, flour, salt and black pepper.
Mix green peppers, onions, garlic salt, celery and catsup (or tomato paste and sugar).
Mix with hands into submarine-shaped patties (size of palm of hand).
Cook on a cookie sheet in a 375° oven for 40 minutes or until done.

title: blarney stone bars
directions: Add enough milk to spread.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts or salted peanuts.

title: crispy sweet pickles
directions: Add cucumbers and bring to full boil; boil for 1 minute.
Pack in jars.

title: chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: Cream together margarine, oil, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and water.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cut when cool.

title: momma's pie
directions: Remove label from can of Eagle Brand milk.
Do not open can. Submerge can in saucepan of water; bring to boil.
Simmer 3 hours. Add water to keep can covered.
Cool.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package, except add 1 extra egg and 1/2 vanilla pudding.
When cake is done and while still hot, make holes in cake with fork and pour mixture of Eagle Brand and cream of coconut into holes.
Let cool.
Mix together Cool Whip and remainder of pudding; pour over cooled cake, spread.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fried fish
directions: Roll crackers in a plastic bag until as fine as cornmeal.
Mix egg and milk (lightly beat).
Coat fish with egg and milk mixture. Shake fish in the bag of crackers.
Fry in hot vegetable or olive oil.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix everything together except cheese.
Put some cheese in casserole dish and rest for top of casserole.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion and salt together.
Let stand 2 hours. Rinse and drain.
Add sugar and vinegar; let stand 20 minutes. Put in freezer boxes and freeze.

title: cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Add vanilla and salt. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each egg.
Beat well, adding flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ice cream mix
directions: Mix together. Put in freezer. Add enough milk to fill freezer to 2/3. Refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In a 2-quart 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, combine all ingredients except the stuffing mix and butter.
Toss the stuffing mix with the butter.
Spoon over vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: applesauce pie(makes 2)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until pie seems firm.
Delicious served with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter and flour a 1-quart souffle dish and the top third of a foil collar, then place collar around dish. Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt butter in a saucepan and stir in flour and salt.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk gradually and return to heat.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Add lemon juice, nutmeg and broccoli to sauce.
Beat egg yolks and add to cooled sauce.
Beat egg whites to the foamy stage.
Add cream of tartar and continue beating until whites just bend over.
Gently fold sauce and whites together using a spatula.
Put in souffle dish.
Reduce heat to 375°.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes.

title: hot liqueur sauce
directions: Bring cream, butter, sugar and brown sugar to a boil.
Let cool then add cocoa.
Keep in double boiler to keep warm.
Good on chocolate speckled cake, ice cream, etc.

title: bacon-tomato spinach salad
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp. Remove to paper towels. Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons of drippings. Add the salad dressing, mustard, salt and pepper to the drippings. Cook and stir over low heat until heated through.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, water, butter and salt in saucepan. Cook, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring until syrup forms a brittle ball in cold water.
Add vanilla, stirring only enough to mix thoroughly.
Place popped corn in large bowl.
Pour syrup slowly over popped corn.
Form into balls and place on waxed paper.
Makes 12 balls.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix dressing ingredients.
Select fresh, uncooked vegetables. Add or delete for personal preferences 1 pound of fresh mushrooms and 1 head cauliflower.
Mix and marinate 24 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: butter crunch candy
directions: Put tidbits and peanut butter
in
top	of double boiler over very hot water (do not
let
it boil).
Stir until tidbits melt, add salt and vanilla.
Stir
in
quickly
and
add	corn flakes, mixing until flakes are coated.
Pour into buttered pan and press down and smooth until
pan	bottom is covered.
Place in refrigerator until set.
Cut
before it hardens.
Completely chill before removing from pan.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken asparagus roll-ups
directions: Pound chicken breasts to 1/8-inch.
On each breast, place one slice cheese with 3 asparagus stalks.
Roll-up; secure with toothpicks.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oil cook roll-ups until browned on all sides.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups vegetable juice, onion, garlic, lemon juice and peel. Reduce heat to low, cover.
Simmer 25 minutes or until chicken is tender, turning once.
In cup, stir together remaining vegetable juice and cornstarch; cook until thickened; serve over hot rice.
Makes 6 servings, at 304 calories and 105 mg sodium per serving.

title: 30 minute chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine in a saucepan the butter, water and cocoa.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; pour over flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, milk, soda and vanilla.
Bake in an 11 x 16-inch greased pan for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: tyrolean marbles
directions: In a small bowl gently fold nuts together with egg whites, sugar and lemon juice.
Form into small balls, each about a teaspoon size.
Chill and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour into oiled casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed saltines on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: brunch for a bunch
directions: * Skip if using O'Brien potatoes.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt Parkay and marshmallows over medium heat in cook pot. Completely melt both and then slowly stir in Rice Krispies. Remove from heat and finish mixing.
Spread onto a greased pan or plate.

title: heavenly waffles
directions: Mix the yolks, flour, butter and baking powder together.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold into the batter.
Bake as usual in a waffle iron.

title: mushroom puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend creamed cheese, mushrooms, pimentos, onion and
Tabasco sauce.
Separate crescents into 4 rectangles.
Press
to
seal
perforations.
Spread
with
1 tablespoon mixture.
Start	at
longer side and roll and seal. Cut each into 6 pieces.
Roll
in nuts.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
One can makes 24 puffs.

title: summer squash casserole(serves 6)
directions: Cook squash with onion in boiling salted water; drain well. Combine soup and sour cream; stir in carrot.
Fold in drained squash and onion.
Melt butter or oleo; toss with stuffing mix. Spread half the mixture in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° until heated through; 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jordan's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in microwave-safe dish and microwave about 10 to 15 minutes.
Check for doneness (may take longer in some microwave ovens).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle at least 1/2 cup of grated Cheddar cheese over top of casserole and finish with 1 cup crushed potato chips.
Bake until hot and bubbling.

title: poppy seed ham and cheese biscuits
directions: Slice ham, cheese and rolls.
Put sliced ham and cheese in rolls.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over rolls. Warm until cheese is melted, then serve.

title: shrimp and veggie casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions, drain. Place in an ungreased 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Melt 2 Tbsp. butter in skillet, add shrimp, garlic, salt, and tarragon.
Cook and stir until shrimp is done.
Add shrimp to baking dish of vegetables. Stir to combine.
In small bowl, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan, and 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Sprinkle over shrimp mixture. Broil for 1 to 2 minutes or until browned.
Serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: rice krispie caramel bars
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine with regular marshmallows.
Add Rice Krispies.
Pat 1/2 of mixture into buttered pan.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine, milk and caramels together.
Spread miniature marshmallows over Rice Krispies mixture in pan.
Pour caramel mixture over this.
Cover with other half of Rice Krispies mixture.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt; simmer.
Cook spaghetti; drain and add butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture in a well-greased 10-inch pie pan to resemble crust. Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti.
Fill pie with tomato meat mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 minutes more or longer.
Let stand before cutting to hold shape better.

title: meat cheese roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the beef, egg, bread crumbs, onion, 1/3 cup tomato sauce, salt and pepper; mix well and shape into a flat rectangle, about 10 x 12 inches on a piece of wax paper.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups shredded cheese evenly over meat mixture.
Starting with shortest end, roll up jelly roll fashion and press ends of roll to seal.
Bake in a shallow baking pan for 1 hour.
Drain off excess fat.
Pour remaining sauce over roll. Garnish with remaining 1/2 cup shredded cheese and green pepper rings.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.
Good with sweet peas, creamed potatoes, baked potatoes or just tossed salad.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain can of green beans, kidney beans and wax beans.
Thinly slice onion.
Add onion to beans and add Italian dressing. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: ham and creamy potato scallops
directions: Cool and peel potatoes; slice 1/4-inch thick.
Spread in greased 2-quart casserole.
In saucepan, melt butter and stir in flour until well blended.
Add onion, celery, ham, broth, mayonnaise and cheese spread; cook until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour ham and cheese mixture over potatoes and toss gently.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon custard pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Stir in lemon juice.
Add beaten egg yolks and flour and mix. Stir in milk.
Hastily stir in beaten egg whites.
Bake in unbaked pie shell in slow oven at 325° for about 50 minutes.

title: mexican rice cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour oil in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan and sprinkle with 2 teaspoons of cornmeal.
Stick pan in a 375° oven until hot; remove pan from oven and pour in batter. Return to oven and bake for 45 minutes.
(Could bake in muffin tins.)

title: no bake banana peanut butter fudge bars
directions: Melt oleo in large skillet.
Stir in vanilla.
Add oatmeal and brown sugar.
Heat and stir 5 minutes on low heat.
Set aside 1 cup of this mixture.
Press remaining mixture in 9 x 13 pan (sprayed).
Sprinkle banana over top.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter together on low heat.
Pour and spread over banana. Sprinkle with reserved oatmeal mixture.
Press down lightly. Chill 2 hours before cutting.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Flour and brown pork chops in skillet. Place pork chops in bottom of a 2 1/2-quart glass casserole dish.
Put a layer of potatoes and onion slices on top of pork chops.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Repeat with the potatoes and onion slices and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Spread the soup over the potatoes and onion. Add
1 1/2 cans water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except nuts, at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Add nuts.
Pour into ungreased angel food pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool inverted.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello with water.
Add strawberries and juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Mix well.
Place 1/2 in bottom of greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Let stand.
Cover with sour cream. Spread the rest of the jello mixture over sour cream.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Omit sour cream and use as a dessert.

title: hamburger paprikash with noodles and broccoli
directions: Brown beef in a large skillet over medium to high heat, breaking up large chunks.
Stir in garlic, onion and pepper.
Cook until almost done.
Stir in paprika and thyme.
Add broth, noodles and broccoli; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 8 to 10 minutes, stirring twice, until noodles are tender.
Whisk sour cream and flour until blended; stir into noodle mixture.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes, stirring often until sauce is thick.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Let set in refrigerator for about 1 hour.
Pour cherry pie filling on top.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Crumble
and
brown beef.
Spoon into 8 or 9-inch square pan. Top
with
sauce
and cheese.
Combine Bisquick, milk and eggs; beat
until
smooth.
Pour over casserole; cover evenly. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.	Serves 6.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Salt chicken.
Roll in flour.
Brown in oleo.
Mix onion soup, mushroom soup and water.
Add 1 cup raw rice.
Pour over chicken. Cover and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chess cake
directions: Mix together chocolate cake mix, 1 egg, melted margarine and nuts.
Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press nuts into dough.

title: pina colada ice cream
directions: Pour pineapple soda into ice cream freezer container first, then add the other ingredients.
Freeze according to ice cream freezer directions.

title: spinach salad and dressing
directions: Wash spinach and lettuce; drain.
Mix all other ingredients and shake.
Sprinkle cashews over torn up lettuce.
Add dressing when ready to serve.

title: donna's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add all other ingredients, except the Chee-tos, and mix.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Sprinkle top with Chee-tos, then bake 5 more minutes.
Serves 8.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook all ingredients (except milk, butter, cheese and cream of celery soup) until tender. Then add milk, butter, cheese and cream of celery soup.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, butter, egg, milk and pudding; beat 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate. Drain peaches, place fruit slices on batter.
Beat together cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons of reserved peach juice; continue beating for 2 minutes until smooth.
Spoon over fruit and batter.
Stir together 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over top of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Chill well before serving.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend in well.
Pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: abe's beef burgundy
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch cubes.
Place beef cubes, onion soup mix and wine in oven.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Stir often.
About 15 minutes before cooking time is up, add mushrooms. Serve over rice.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cup up chicken and boil.
(We add celery stalks, onions and seasonings, such as Accent, to give extra flavor to the chicken.) When done, save chicken broth and debone chicken into pieces. Cook spaghetti.

title: spaetzle
directions: Blend ingredients until smooth with wooden spoon then beat for several minutes.
Push through a press into boiling water.
Take a sharp knife and cut off at press.
Stir to separate and boil for approximately 2 minutes or until done.
Spoon out with serrated spoon or screen and rinse with water (warm).

title: three layer bars
directions: In double boiler cook butter, sugar, cocoa and vanilla until blended.
Add slightly beaten eggs and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add remainder of first layer items.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, seasonings and onion.
Drain off grease.
Add tomato sauce and ketchup.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put Cheddar and American cheese on top (enough to cover).
Flatten out canned biscuits.
Put on top.
Bake until biscuits are done.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, granulated sugar, vanilla and nutmeg, mixing until well blended.
Add 3/4 cup strawberry slices. Stir into cream cheese mixture.
Mix whip cream and confectioners sugar together until you reach a stiff peak.
Fold whip cream mixture into cream cheese mixture.
Add remaining strawberries. Spoon into crust.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Melt butter; set aside to cool a little.
Peel, core and dice apples.
Cover with sugar; let stand 2 hours.
Sift flour, soda and spices together.
Beat eggs with fork.
Add to apple mixture. Add cooled butter.
Blend in dry ingredients to mixture.
Add raisins.
Mix with a wooden spoon.
Batter is thick.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: curry dip
directions: Combine all thoroughly and chill at least 6 hours.
Recipe is better if made day before use.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saut onion and celery in butter. Add to broth. Mix sage and pepper with bread mixture, crumble. Add to broth mixture. Add salt and eggs. Mix well. Bake in 400 degree oven 45-55 minutes. You can add more sage if you like. Also add a can of cream of chicken soup to make richer and moister. Can also add milk if you don't have enough broth.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over meat loaf.
Bake 30 minutes longer.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, heat sugar, butter, cocoa, milk, vanilla and salt over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Stir in nuts. Spread mixture quickly in buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cool. Cut into squares.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: bacon-cracklin' cornbread
directions: In a bowl combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder, sugar, salt and bacon.
In another bowl, combine the egg, milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture.
Pour batter into a greased baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: fat-free tuna-mac salad
directions: Mix all together and chill until ready to serve.

title: blue cheese burgers
directions: Reserve 2 tablespoons blue cheese for garnish.
In blender at low speed blend mayonnaise, milk, vinegar, red pepper, salt and remaining blue cheese until smooth.
Set aside.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat on stove until it boils. Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, pour over salad and toss.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients and boil over low heat until it forms a medium-hard ball in water.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Beat until thick and pour in buttered pan.

title: beef-vegetable soup
directions: Set Super Pot cooker at 225° and brown meat on all sides in oil.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and reduce heat to simmer for 2 hours.
Remove meat, peppercorns and bay leaf.
Trim meat from bone and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Return meat to Super Pot.
Skim off fat before serving.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles. Mix all other ingredients together, except 1/4 package crackers and 1/2 of cheese. Pour noodles and mixture in 12 x 24-inch baking dish.
Cover top with remaining cheese and crackers. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese melts and crackers are browned.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all items for cornbread mixture.
Put grease in large skillet (cover bottom).
Heat to 350°.
Saute, with 3 teaspoons bacon fat or grease, a large onion, chopped fine, 3 fresh jalapeno peppers, seeded and chopped and a bell pepper, seeded and chopped fine.
Add 1 pound ground chuck.
Brown all and season with black pepper and salt.
Drain fat.
Pour 1/2 of cornbread mixture into heated skillet.
Add meat mixture.
Add 1/2 pound grated Cheddar cheese.
Top with remaining cornbread mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: b~b~q meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, eggs onions and seasoning.
Add enough crumbs so that mixture will stick together.
Roll into balls and dry in olive oil.
Refrigerate this until about 3 hours before serving. Put meatball in crock pot and add your favorite BBQ sauce.
Cook on high for about 1 hour and turn to low for remainder of time.

title: slow cooked swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into 6 pieces.
Cut onion into 1/4-inch slices. Chop celery into 1/2-inch slices.
Mix flour with salt & pepper. Dredge steak in flour mixture, coating well.
In greased slow cooker, place onion, then steak, then celery, then tomato sauce. Cover and cook on low 6-8 hours until meat is tender.
Serve with baked potatoes or over rice.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and shortening together.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add unbeaten eggs and continue beating, about 2 minutes.
Batter is thin.
Bake in 2 or 3 (8-inch) pans (I use black skillet) at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: breakfast pizza casserole
directions: Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well and set aside.
Unroll crescent roll dough into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Press bottom and sides to form a crust; seal perforations.
Prick with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes on lower oven rack.
Spoon sausage evenly over crust; top with potatoes.
Beat eggs well and pour over potatoes.
Bake uncovered at 350° on lower oven rack 25 minutes or until set. Sprinkle cheese evenly over top; bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Garnish if desired.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice according to package directions.
Mix soup with broccoli and rice.
Place in a baking dish.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pot roast
directions: Salt and pepper roast on both sides.
Place enough heavy-duty foil in baking pan to wrap up roast.
Sprinkle bottom of foil with soup mix before placing roast in pan.
Sprinkle rest on roast and cover with soup.
Fold foil over roast and cook for 3 1/2 hours in preheated 350° oven.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Stir rice, orange juice, soup, mushroom pieces and enough water to equal 2/3 cup in bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking pan until all mixed.
Place cut up chicken on top of rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 375°
oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Take cover off and cook for another 1/2 hour.
Serves 4.

title: pickled vegetables
directions: In large saucepan, cook each variety of vegetable (except zucchini or cucumbers) separately, in boiling water for 2 minutes. Remove with slotted spoon and cool under cold water.
Drain.
Place vegetables in layers in wide-mouth jars or 1 large glass container with tight-fitting cover.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fold into a well-greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour or until middle gets baked.

title: sunshine chicken
directions: Brown chicken in shortening.
Pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients except rice. Cover and cook over low heat 45 minutes or until done. Stir occasionally. Serve over rice.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve with apples slices and ginger cookies to dip.
This recipe make a lot.
You can save half of the dip to serve another time.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Get
milk
and 1 (12 ounce) can of beer steamy hot, not boiling.
Add
Cheez
Whiz,
chicken
broth and Worcestershire sauce.
Get
steamy hot, not boiling.
Add 1 (12 ounce) can of beer
and 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Pour mixture into a large pot and let cook on low for 2 hours.

title: vegetarian lasagne
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water for 10 minutes; drain. Defrost spinach. Saute onion in oil until soft. Add zucchini and mushrooms and cook until tender. Stir in tomato sauce, tomato paste, olives and oregano. Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole. Layer in 1/2 each of noodles, cottage cheese, spinach, sauce mixture and 1/3 of the cheese slices. Repeat, placing remaining third of Monterey Jack on top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: chicken and chiles casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts evenly with salt and pepper and place in a lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine cheese and next 3 ingredients and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with chiles.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Combine ingredients except eggs.
Simmer 10 minutes, covered. Pour over peeled hard-cooked eggs in gallon jar.
Seal eggs in gallon jar.
Seal and store in refrigerator for up to 1 week.

title: the dessert without a name
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.
Slice ice cream about 1 inch thick and lay on crust.
Freeze.

title: grilled leg of lamb
directions: In glass dish large enough to fit lamb, mix mustard, rosemary, ginger, garlic, soy sauce, and oil.
Add lamb.
Marinate overnight, turning after 1 hour.
Remove lamb from marinade.
Place on hot grill over gray coals.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes on each side, depending on size of lamb.
Part will be well-done, part medium-done, and part rare.
This can also be broiled.
Baste during cooking with marinade.
Slice lamb on the diagonal.
Serve with assorted vegetables, grilled alongside lamb.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Mix the salt, flour and coconut. Stir well. Reserve 3/4 cup for topping.
Spread remaining in greased 9 x 11-inch pan. Spread apricot preserves on coconut mixture. Sprinkle nuts over apricot preserves.
Put reserved dough on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool slightly and cut in bars.

title: vegetable pot pie
directions: Heat 1/4 cup olive oil in a large skillet.
Saute first 6 ingredients over medium heat until onion is translucent.
Add tofu and herbs; cook 2 minutes more.
Add salt, pepper and Parmesan. Place vegetable mixture in deep pie dish; add gravy until it reaches the top of veggie mixture.
Cover with rolled pie dough; prick the crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until crust is golden brown.

title: squash fritters
directions: Add salt and pepper to squash and onion and cook together; drain well.
Mix together flour, milk and egg, then add squash, sugar and salt.
Put in crushed red peppers (optional).
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased griddle or frying pan.
Brown on both sides and serve.

title: spiced and saucy shell dinner
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Brown meat with onion and garlic. Drain fat.
In mixing bowl combine egg, bread crumbs, cinnamon, allspice and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Stir in meat mixture and 1/4 cup of the sauce.
Mix well.
Stuff each shell with about 2 tablespoons meat mixture.
Pour half of remaining sauce in casserole dish.
Place filled shells in single layer on sauce and top with remaining sauce.
Heat through in oven or microwave.

title: beef stew
directions: * May use stewed tomatoes but it may be quite spicy.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All well and place in casserole dish.
In small saucepan, melt together 1 stick butter and Cheez Whiz until it makes a sauce.
Fold into Veg-All casserole.
Crush crackers and place on top.
Melt the other stick of butter and pour over top. Bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy chicken
directions: Season chicken with seasoned salt and pepper and place in shallow baking dish.
Mix lime juice, salad dressing mix and butter and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Remove cover 15 minutes before serving.

title: puppy chow
directions: Combine chocolate, butter and peanut butter; melt over low heat.
Pour cereal in large bowl.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal.
In a large paper bag, put 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour in cereal, stir to coat.
Put another 1/2 cup sugar; shake gently to coat. Add additional sugar if you feel it is needed, add gradually.

title: rhubarb preserves
directions: Boil rhubarb, sugar and pineapple for 10 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add strawberry Jell-O.
Stir well.
Put in sterilized jars.
Cover with Parowax.

title: meal in one casserole
directions: Heat first 6 ingredients thoroughly.
Pour in casserole dish. Top with mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: raspberry jello supreme
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 cups of hot water.
Add raspberries, juice and all, bananas and pineapple.
Put half of mixture in mold and let set until firm.
Spread sour cream over set jello and cover with remaining jello.

title: casserole italiano
directions: In skillet, brown beef with onion, garlic and seasonings. Stir to separate meat.
Combine in 1 1/2-quart casserole with soup, water and noodles.
Place cheese around edge.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Blend together and put in 8 x 2-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend milk, coconut and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 1-inch apart on well-greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until delicate brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan at once.
A whole or half candied cherry may be placed in the center of each cookie before baking.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with milk and fold in bananas.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add marshmallows and let them melt.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Mix slaw ingredients, onions and noodles. Refrigerate until serving time. Mix the oil, sugar and flavor packs.
At serving time, mix dressing with refrigerated ingredients.
Add almonds and sunflower seeds.
Serves 6.

title: fireside coffee mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Use 2 to 3 heaping teaspoonfuls per mug.
Add boiling water and enjoy.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Cover pickles with lime water and soak 24 hours.
Drain and wash.
Cover with clean water.
(Do this 3 times.)
Dry cucumbers well.
Heat mixture and pour over cucumbers and let stand overnight.
Next morning bring to boil for 1 hour.
Add teaspoon salt.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear cleansed, crispy lettuce into bite size pieces and place in a 9 x 12-inch greased dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given; add sugar in mayonnaise and spread over top as you would icing on a cake.
Top with grated cheese and refrigerate for 8 to 12 hours or overnight.
At serving time, garnish with bacon bits and parsley (optional).

title: pasta primavera
directions: Add carrots and broccoli to cooking noodles for last 2 minutes of cooking time.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Stir in dressings and remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in large bowl.
In saucepan boil shortening, oleo, water and cocoa.
(Bring all to a boil.) Pour this mixture over the sugar and flour and mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda, salt and vnailla and mix well.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 325° for 30 minutes.
Frost while still hot.

title: blushing punch
directions: Put each ingredient through blender separately.
Keep slushy cold until ready to serve and add ginger ale.

title: dark overnight cookies
directions: In a bowl, cream the shortening. Add sugar gradually. Add eggs and molasses.
Blend.
In second bowl, sift together flour and spices.
Add to creamed mixture and stir well.
Knead dough and shape into rolls.
Chill overnight.
Next day, slice and bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: white chocolate salties
directions: Melt the almond bark in the microwave 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir after 1 1/2 minutes and continue to stir every 30 seconds until melted.
When melted, stir in the nuts and pretzels.
Mix well. Pour into a greased pan and spread out.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Break into pieces.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: In a family of 4, cube potatoes; put in microwave plate. Sprinkle with garlic salt, black pepper, paprika, seasoned salt and parsley flakes on potatoes.
Put 1 tablespoon of butter on each side and the fifth tablespoon in the middle of potatoes.
On High, cook, covered, until the potatoes are done.
Mix butter over all the potatoes.

title: snow ball cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, bake cake as directed.

Let cool. In a bowl let cream cheese set until soft enough to work, then add instant pudding and pour milk over, let stand until milk is absorbed in pudding mix; beat well until thoroughly mixed, stir in pineapple.
Cover cake with mixture.
Using soft Cool Whip, cover the mixture and sprinkle coconut over top.

title: rotini (worm) salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Tupperware bowl; chill before serving.

title: blackberry cobbler(fresh fruit)
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Put in a 1 1/4-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Stir remaining ingredients together and place on cobbler.
Bake in a 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tomatoes stuffed with tuna fish
directions: Blanch tomatoes in boiling water.
Drain, sprinkle with cold water, then peel.
Cut into halves and salt to taste.
Place tomato halves on a sieve to drain.
Mix tuna, margarine, chopped capers and spring onions in a bowl.
Fill tomato halves with mixture.
Top with pitted olive.
Serve a tomato half per person on a bed of lettuce.
Add salt as desired.
Serves 4.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cookie mix; bake in pizza pan.
Let cool.
Mix sugar and cream cheese; spread over cooled crust.
Spread the crushed pineapple.
Slice apple, banana and peaches; sprinkle fresh fruit with a few drops of lemon juice.
Spread over crust in layers. Sprinkle with coconut.
(Can use strawberries or any other kind of fruit.)
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans, coconut and cherries.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Cook together sugars, milk and cream of tartar; stirring constantly until firm soft-ball or 232°.
Add pecans and beat. Drop onto waxed paper by spoonfuls.

title: baked potato soup(great on a cold night!)
directions: Wash potatoes and prick them several times with a fork; bake at	400°
for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool.
Cut potatoes in half
lengthwise
and
then scoop out pulp.
Set pulp aside. Discard
skins.
Melt
butter in a heavy saucepan over low	heat; add
flour, stirring until smooth.	Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually
add
milk;	cook over medium heat, stirring
constantly
until
mixture
is
thickened and bubbly. Add
potato
pulp,	salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons green onions, 1/2 cup
