bacon	and 1 cup of cheese.
Cook soup until thoroughly heated, but do not boil.
Stir in sour cream.
Add extra
milk
if necessary	for desired thickness.	Serve with remaining onions, bacon and cheese.

title: super chalupa dip
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and seasonings.
Add beans and chilies, mix well.
Pat into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese. Sprinkle taco sauce over.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes. Put olives, onion and sour cream on top.
Serve with taco chips.

title: migas
directions: Saute onion and green pepper until onion is clear.
Next, add tortilla bits and stir until tortillas are cooked just a bit.
Put green chilies into beaten eggs and pour over tortilla mixture. Scramble eggs until done; turn off heat.
Add tomato sauce and stir briskly into mixture until mixture is well covered; add Cheddar cheese and let melt.
Serve with picante sauce, if desired.
Good brunch menu item!

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately with milk. Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook sliced
zucchini
in
small amount of salted water until tender; drain.
Cook carrots	and onion until
tender.
Stir in soup, add
zucchini.
Place
in casserole. Top with croutons mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° for minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook mixture of chicken, onion, soup and broth in a saucepan over low heat just until heated through, stirring constantly.
Toss stuffing mix with butter in bowl. Layer chicken mixture and stuffing mixture 1/2 at a time in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 8 servings.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites stiff, gradually adding sugar, salt and vanilla.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Turn off oven.
Place cookies into oven and close door.
Leave undisturbed overnight.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak in strips.
Brown in hot oil.
Add onion and garlic.
Combine mushroom soup, sour cream, mushrooms, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Add to meat; heat thoroughly.
This may be prepared in an electric skillet.
Serve with 6 ounce noodles which have been cooked and drained.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Divide batter in two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned (about 45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: watercress pinwheels
directions: Cut bread lengthwise in 3/8 inch thick slices.
Mix watercress, cheese and salt.
Spread 1/4 cup filling on each slice.
Roll up, wrap in foil and chill.
Slice and serve.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding. Fold in other ingredients.
Chill 5 hours and serve.

title: sweet caramel dip
directions: Cut apples in wedges and dip in caramel dip.
Will keep well in refrigerator.

title: chili
directions: Put the soup in, then put the cheese in, then put the beans in and then put the onions in.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in casserole.
Add rest.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Delicious

title: creamy fettucini alfredo
directions: In a large saucepan, combine cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, margarine and milk.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Add fettucini; toss lightly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add all but last 3 ingredients.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add Velveeta cheese and cook until cheese melts. Cool this mixture.
Cut muffins in halves and spoon cooled mix on the 24 muffin halves.
Top with Mozzarella.
Freeze on cookie sheet until ready for use.
Bake at 350° until heated thoroughly. You may add chopped mushrooms or pepperoni, if desired.

title: chunky cheese queso
directions: Brown sausage in a large skillet, stirring until it crumbles and is no longer pink; rinse and drain. Stir together sausage and remaining ingredients in a 2 1/2-quart slow cooker. Cover and cook at low 2 hours or until cheese melts. Serve with tortilla chips. Yield: 6 cups.

title: terrific tuna casserole
directions: Combine tuna, water chestnuts, nuts, onion and celery; mix together with soup.
Put into casserole dish (which has been sprayed with Pam).
Use chow mein noodles as topping.
Bake in the oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with hot rolls and tossed salad, and you have a simple complete meal.

title: brownie pie
directions: Beat 4 minutes: eggs, sugar, butter, flour, cocoa, vanilla and salt.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 8 inch pie plate. Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: turkey parmesan or chicken
directions: Rinse and skin breasts.
Dip in seasoned milk and coat with almonds.
Put in shallow baking dish and pour sauce over breasts. Top with string cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: molasses crinkles cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Roll dough into small ball and roll in sugar.
Press cookies down with a glass and bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: luther nunn's famous chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper in frying pan.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer as long as possible.

title: hobo stew
directions: Brown hamburger and saute onions in large skillet over medium heat.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes to let flavors blend.

title: beef dip
directions: Cook chuck until brown; drain.
Add next 5 ingredients and simmer 5 minutes.
Then add both cheeses and blend.
Serve warm with sesame sticks.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Stir just to moisten.
Bake in muffin cups at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be stored in refrigerator until ready to bake.

title: st. paul's casserole
directions: Put water, soup and rice together and when mixture begins to boil, boil for 7 minutes; cut up the pepper, celery and onion. Brown sausage and pour off the grease.
Drain well.
Combine the soup and rice mixture, sausage, celery, green pepper, onion and almonds.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: saucy shortribs
directions: Score ribs on both sides 1/3 of the way down.
Do not cut all the way through.
Put ribs in a heavy kettle.
Add the garlic to the soy sauce.
Put in kettle, along with enough water to cover the ribs 3/4 up.
Add scallions (chopped).
Toast seed in salt briefly until rounded and brown; add to ribs.
Bring to boil; lower heat and simmer.
Cover and cook for 2 hours.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: shrimp louisiana
directions: Cook onion in butter until golden brown, stirring constantly. Add flour and milk; cook until smooth.
Add rice and shrimp.
When hot, add seasoning and tomato soup.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine the crackers, hamburger, tomato paste, eggs, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper and mix well. Pat 1/2 of the mixture into the bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Combine crackers, cottage cheese, mushrooms, parsley and oregano. Spread mixture over the meat in the pan and top with remaining meat mixture and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: rice and vegetable salad
directions: Transfer rice to a mixing bowl and pour 1 1/2 cups vinaigrette into rice; toss thoroughly.
Cool to room temperature.
Add remaining ingredients and toss thoroughly.
Taste, correct seasoning and add additional vinaigrette if you like.
Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate up to 4 hours.
Return to room temperature before servings.
Makes 8 to 10 portions.

title: pretzel dip
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Great for parties.
Serve with pretzels.

title: fried wontons
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine egg, cabbage, green onion, soy sauce, grated ginger root, sugar, salt, sesame oil, garlic and a dash of pepper.
Add the ground beef or pork and chopped shrimp; mix well.

title: fun dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for 2 hours to blend flavors.
Serve with crisp vegetables.

title: dolly beck's rice casserole
directions: *See your local store's Mexican food section.
If you don't like chilies, you could substitute 1/2 cup sliced green onions.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to box directions. Punch holes in cake while hot.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut and pour over hot cake.
Let cool completely.
Put Cool Whip on top of cake, then cover with coconut.
Store in refrigerator.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Save 1 cup dry cake mix.
Take remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil and mix together.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend cream cheese, sugar, 3 eggs and cake mix.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
At low speed, add milk, vanilla and lemon juice. Pour into crust.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 55 minutes.
When cool, spread with pie filling on top.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in 1 cup water for 2 minutes.
Stir in sugar. Cook 5 minutes more.
Soften jello in 1 cup cold water; add to hot berry mix and stir until jello is dissolved.
Strain.
Cool. When mixture begins to thicken, add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: mini pizzas
directions: *Use as much as you want!!

title: berry good yogurt sundae
directions: You will also need 2 small bowls, 2 tall parfait glasses, a fork for mashing and a spoon for layering.

title: sweet pretzel salad
directions: Mix broken pretzels with margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Mix cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Fold 2 cups whipped topping in and spread over pretzel crust.
Return to refrigerator. Prepare strawberry gelatin with 2 cups boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries.
Stir and chill until syrupy. Then pour over well chilled cream cheese mixture.
Cut into squares; garnish with dab of whipped topping.

title: sherry pecan sauce
directions: In a medium size saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Bring to a boil while stirring constantly.
Continue cooking five minutes over medium heat.
Cool five minutes and then stir in evaporated milk, sherry and pecans.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes approximately 2 cups of sauce.
Keeps in indefinitely in refrigerator or freeze.

title: chocolate oatmeal drop candy
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in a heavy pot.
Bring mixture to a boil and let boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop spoonfuls of mixture onto waxed paper.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until done; debone and place meat in liquid that chicken was cooked in.
I add canned chicken broth if the liquid needs to be richer.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Cover and let stand for 20 minutes.
Beat butter until creamy.
Gradually add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Add oatmeal mixture and mix well.
Sift together cinnamon, salt, soda and flour.
Add to oat mixture.
Pour in pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Put cooked chicken breasts in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish layered across the bottom.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Put broccoli in baking dish on top of chicken.
Top with large spoonfuls of Cheez Whiz.
Break up bread into pieces and brown in frying pan. Put bread pieces on top of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with baked potatoes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter a cake pan.
Peel and slice apples into pan.
When dish is about half full, sprinkle with 1 cup sugar.
When all apples are in dish, sprinkle with second cup of sugar.
(May need more or less, depending on the apples.) Sprinkle cinnamon over top.

title: fruit freeze
directions: Mix ingredients.
Freeze overnight.
Thaw slightly.
Pour 1 (12 ounce) bottle ginger ale over all and serve.

title: sausage bean casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock-pot; mix well.
Cook on medium until heated through.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add grated zucchini.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to zucchini mixture and beat until blended.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Shape sausage into balls and fry until well done. Combine all other ingredients into saucepan and heat. Add sausage balls. Cover and cook on simmer for 5 more minutes. Let cool. Chill 24 hrs. Reheat to serve.

title: pineapple-pecan cheese balls
directions: Allow cream cheese to come to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Chill until firm, 1 hour.
Form into 2 balls, wrapping each in tinfoil, and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: grilled chicken and vegetables
directions: Prepare grill for barbecuing over medium coals.
Place chicken on rack; brush with soy sauce.
Cook 5 minutes.
Turn chicken over and place vegetables crosswise on rack; brush everything with soy sauce.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes more until chicken and vegetables are fork-tender; turn and brush vegetables once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast and sugar in 1 1/2 cups warm water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Makes 9 loaves.

title: beef roast
directions: Place roast in roasting pan.
Sprinkle half of dry onion soup mix on meat.
Rub to place flavor deep in meat.
Spread on mushroom soup right out of can.
Sprinkle with remaining dry soup mix.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven until half done, usually 1 hour.

title: spinach stuffed shells
directions: Heat spaghetti sauce to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes to blend flavors.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water and set aside about 20 to 25 minutes.
Pour all ingredients into ice cream freezer and fill with milk to half of last notch on churn.
Freeze and enjoy.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small nonstick skillet heat 1 teaspoon margarine until bubbly and hot.
Add onion and saute until clear.
In bottom of 1-quart casserole spread half the macaroni; top with half the cheese, then half the onion.
Repeat layers.
In small bowl combine milk, egg, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pour over macaroni mixture and sprinkle with paprika.
Dot with remaining margarine and bake until set, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brown bag apple pie
directions: Put apples into a bowl; mix with sugar, cornstarch, mace, cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon juice.
Place apple mixture into pie shell and pat apples down evenly.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients at once.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Let cool briefly before removing from pan.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle chopped nuts and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to box directions.
Pour cake batter over pecans and coconut.
Blend oleo, sugar and cream cheese in microwave until smooth.
Gently smooth over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Peel the onions and cut them in half.
Slice each half wafer-thin.
There should be about 12 cups. In a large, heavy, ovenproof casserole or deep skillet, heat the butter and add the onions and garlic.
Cook, stirring, until onions are wilted and start to brown, about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Put the casserole in the oven and bake for 15 minutes.
Remove the casserole from the oven and sprinkle the onion mixture with flour, stirring to coat onion pieces evenly.
Add the water and wine and cook over high heat, scraping around the bottom and sides to dissolve the browned particles.
Add the bay leaf and thyme and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: creamy carrot potato boats(good for diabetics)
directions: Bake potatoes in a 375° oven for 45 minutes or until tender. Cool slightly.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Gently scoop out each potato half, leaving a thin shell.
In a small mixer bowl, combine potato pulp, carrots, cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and pepper.
Beat until smooth.
Add more milk if needed.
Add onions. Spoon potato mixture into potato shells.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes or until heated through. Makes 8 servings.

title: oven-fried okra
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Dredge okra in cornmeal mixture.
Spread oil in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Spread okra evenly in pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring often.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix with hand mixer cream cheese, both sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Serve with apple slices.

title: linguine salad
directions: While linguine is hot, pour dressing and Salad Supreme over linguine in a large bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate caramel cheesecake
directions: Combine caramels and milk in saucepan.
Cook on low until melted, stirring often.
Pour over graham cracker crust in 9-inch spring-form pan.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir in vanilla and melted chips.
Mix well.
Pour over caramels and crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool and refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour into a greased baking pan.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: pretty good chicken salad
directions: Grill chicken breasts.	Chop coarsely across grain.
Combine with all other ingredients in a large bowl and mix.
Hands work well for this.
Add more or less mayonnaise for desired consistency.
Chill for a while before serving.
May garnish with chives or fresh parsley.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and mix until strawberries are thawed.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate until set.

title: christmas cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange; add sugar, mixing well.
Let stand overnight.
Prepare Jell-O according to package directions. Chill.
When half set, add to fruit mixture.
Add walnuts, marshmallows, celery, apple and crushed pineapple to Jell-O and fruit mixture.
Refrigerate until set.
Serve with whipped topping as dessert or with meal instead of cranberry sauce.

title: chipped beef and chicken breasts
directions: Debone and skin chicken breasts.
Lay the cut up chipped beef into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Wrap chicken breasts in bacon; put in over the beef.
Pour cream of mushroom soup (2 cans) and the sour cream over the chicken.
Serve with rice.

title: easy hollandaise sauce
directions: Heat butter until very warm in a saucepan.
Place egg yolks, lemon juice, salt and Tabasco in a blender container.
Cover and blend on low speed.
Uncover immediately and pour the butter in a steady stream.
Turn off blender as soon as all butter is added. Place blender container in a pan of hot water until ready to serve.
Serve over asparagus, broccoli or poached eggs.

title: spicy-sweet chicken salad
directions: Combine picante sauce, mayonnaise and honey in medium bowl. Mix well.
Stir in chicken, celery, grapes, pecans and salt.
Cover and chill.
Sprinkle with green onions.
Add a dab of Pace on top for a little extra kick (optional).
Makes 4 servings, about 4 cups of salad.
Toast pecans.
Put in pie plate, single layer, and put in microwave for 3 1/2 minutes on High.

title: baked rice
directions: Saute celery, mushrooms and onion until tender.
Break chicken soyameat into pieces.
Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: calico dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: best ever chocolate cookies
directions: You will need no stick cooking spray (Pam).

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Fry pork chops to brown.
Slice potatoes into greased baking dish (8 x 10-inch).
Add salt and pepper.
Add the mushroom soup. Place browned pork chops on top of potato mix.
Pour drippings from pork chops on top.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry grand marnier cheesecake
directions: Combine crushed gingersnaps with melted butter; toss crumbs with fork until moistened.
Put into 10-inch spring-form pan. Press mixture evenly over bottom and up sides of pan (won't get too high).
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 5 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Move second rack on second level.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, melt butter and set aside.

title: 4 layer raspberry cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions, adding the almond flavoring. Bake in two 8 inch round pans. Cool completely.

title: no cook mints
directions: Blend butter, syrup, salt and vanilla in large mixing bowl. Add sifted sugar at once.
Mix all together, first with a spoon and then with hands knead in dry ingredients.
Turn onto board and continue kneading until mixture is well blended and smooth.
Makes about 1 1/3 pounds candy.
Store in a cool place.

title: lemon-rosemary chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix rosemary and garlic together. Flatten chicken breasts with the palm of your hand and arrange them on a large sheet of foil.
Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle rosemary and garlic mixture over the chicken breasts. Slice lemons and place 2 or 3 slices on each breast.
Dot with butter and seal the foil into a packet.
Place on a baking sheet and bake in oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked rice(cooked on stove top)
directions: Melt oleo in 4-quart pot. Saute shallots, onions, celery and sweet peppers. Add meat and cook down. Add the consomme soup. Bring to a boil and add 2 cans of water.
Cook for about 10 minutes. Add rice and season to taste.
Make sure you add 3 or 4 squirts of Worcestershire sauce. Cook until most of the liquid is gone.
Lower fire and cook for 25 to 30 minutes (until rice is cooked).

title: sloppy joes
directions: Chop onion and brown with hamburger.
Salt and pepper.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Pour milk into a bowl; add nuts, lemon juice and pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip and pour into pie shells.
Refrigerate. Eat one and freeze one, if desired.
Very good.

title: chunky chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together the flour and baking soda in small bowl.
Set aside.
Put the margarine in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add both kinds of sugar; beat until mixed well (about 1 minute).
Add egg and vanilla to sugar mixture; beat.
Add flour mixture gradually, beating (on low speed) after each addition.
Break chocolate bars into small pieces.
Add chocolate to cookie dough, stirring with a large spoon to blend.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: goulash
directions: Place in electric skillet. Simmer until macaroni is tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: eggnog pound cake
directions: Generously grease a 10-inch Bundt pan with soft butter.
Press almonds against buttered sides and bottom; set pan aside.
Combine cake mix, nutmeg, egg yolks, eggnog, melted butter and rum in large mixing bowl until blended.
Beat egg whites separately until stiff but not dry.
Carefully fold batter into whites.

title: chicken with homemade noodles
directions: Boil chicken in water with salt and pepper until tender.
Let cool.
Remove chicken from bones.
Use broth from chicken to cook noodles.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix together sugar and salt.
Stir in the hot water.
Set aside.
In another bowl, mix yeast and warm water.
Let stand a few minutes.
Stir into salt and sugar mixture.
Add 2 beaten eggs and oil and mix.
Add the flour; mix.
Rub a little oil on top of dough.
Let raise.
Punch down and make into rolls.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain all the beans.
Boil oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Pour on beans.

title: everlasting salad
directions: Pour salted water over the vegetables.	Let stand for 2 hours; then drain well.

title: slushy punch
directions: Mix all in punch bowl; put in freezer for 4 or 5 hours.
Stir every once in a while, like every hour.

title: bulldog brittle
directions: Line a cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Cover bottom of lined cookie sheet with whole graham crackers (break into sections, if necessary, to completely cover bottom of cookie sheet).
Sprinkle pecans over graham crackers.
Melt butter and margarine in boiler. When melted, add sugar and boil for 2 minutes (no longer).
Then pour sugar mixture over pecans and crackers.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg, nuts and 1 stick margarine.
Press into 11 x 14-inch pan.

title: 1-2-3 fresh strawberry shake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Makes 4 cups.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix canning salt, celery seed, sugar and vinegar first.
Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over first ingredients.
Keep in refrigerator in a covered jar.
Do not boil or heat.

title: orange candy slices
directions: Blend wafers until crushed.
Chop candy slices.
Combine all ingredients and form into a roll.
Cover with waxed paper.
Chill. Slice to desired thickness.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1 pint ripe strawberries in saucepan.
Add sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until real thick.
Stir constantly to keep from sticking; let cool.

title: "brunch" casserole anytime
directions: Brush butter and mustard on bread and cut into cubes, line in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs with milk, pour over bread, meat, green pepper, onion and sprinkle with cheese
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, serve hot.
Good with muffins and fruit.

title: spiced tea(servings:  4. preparation time:  35 minutes.)
directions: Bring pineapple juice, lemon juice and water to a boil.
Add sugar and spices and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add tea bags, cover and steep for 10 minutes.
Remove tea bags and strain.
Serve hot or iced.

title: beef mushroom buns
directions: Thaw dough in refrigerator overnight.
Cook beef in frypan; drain fat and rinse beef with hot water to remove all fat.
Add rest of ingredients, except dough.
Cut dough crosswise into 8 slices.
Pat and roll out to 5-inch circles.
Put filling in center; pull all sides up and pinch edges to seal.
Place on greased baking sheet, sealed side down.
Make a large cut on top for steam to escape.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes, or until brown.

title: judy's breakfast casserole
directions: Beat the
eggs
and
milk, then mix in everything else. Place in
greased
x 13-inch pan overnight in refrigerator. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato chowder
directions: In 4-quart Dutch oven, melt butter over medium heat. Add onion, celery and carrots; saute until tender but not brown. Add potatoes, water and bouillon. Reduce heat; cover and simmer until potatoes are tender. Combine flour with 1/2 cup of half and half to form a smooth paste. Stir into potato mixture. Add the remaining 2 1/2 cups of half and half and the seasonings. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching. Reduce the heat to low and add the cheese. Do not return to boil.

title: k & k's gourmet salad
directions: Cut up romaine lettuce into bite sized pieces.
Add sliced fuji apples or sliced strawberries.
Add sliced celery, almonds and crumbled blue cheese.
Toss salad.

title: jolly biscuit roll
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In Bundt pan, melt first 3 tablespoons butter.
Remove and while hot, sprinkle brown sugar all around pan. Place cherries all around pan; set aside.
Mix Bisquick according to mix 2 cups mix and milk (soured).
Make balls.
Mix melted 3 tablespoons butter, sugar and nuts.
Roll dough balls and place in pan to make a circle.
Sprinkle remaining mix on dough balls.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert onto plate and serve.

title: five-flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, beaten until lemon colored.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir flavorings.
Spoon mixture into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Add glaze while hot in pan.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, chill and shake.

title: homestyle deer steak
directions: Season flour with salt, pepper and Mrs. Dash. Beat milk and egg together. Roll deer meat into milk, then into flour. Fry in oil until crisp. Take up and drain out oil but 2 tablespoons of it. Add meat back in pan. Pour Worcestershire sauce over meat, then add tomatoes. Cover with tight lid and simmer for 1 hour over low heat.
Serve with rice.

title: potato supreme
directions: Peel potatoes and grate.
Combine cream, butter and cheese in double boiler and stir until melted.
Add cheese mixture to grated potatoes and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbles.
Top with sour cream, onions and bacon.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: mock strawberry jam
directions: Crush figs and mix all ingredients in large pot.
Cook over medium heat until mixture starts to bubble.
Reduce heat and continue to cook 45 minutes, stirring often.
Seal in sterilized jars.
Makes 4 to 5 pints.

title: marinated corn-bean salad
directions: Mix together in a saucepan sugar, vinegar, oil, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cool.
This is the marinade. Combine the beans, peas, corn, onions and green peppers.
Pour marinade over.
Mix well and refrigerate 4 hours before serving.

title: chicken with raspberry salsa
directions: In shallow dish, mix together flour, salt, pepper & cinnamon. Add chicken to coat well.
In large frying pan, place oil over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook about 5 mins. turning once until brown.
Add salsa & preserves.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 10 mins. or until chicken is cooked completely through. Makes 4 servings.

title: davis fresh deer steaks
directions: In a large cast-iron frying pan, heat grease to hot.
Put steaks in; turn once.
Cover and reduce heat to low.
Fry very slow for 35 or 40 minutes or until tender.
Best served between 3 and 4 A.M. with gravy made with leftover grease and hot biscuits.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: croissant sandwich
directions: Slice rolls open; layer ham and cheese.
Set condiments to the side.
May also use your favorite meat or combine meats.
May also fix ahead.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch dish with chicken; cover with mixture of soups and milk.
Mix stuffing with broth.
Saute onion and celery in margarine for 5 minutes.
Mix with stuffing and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: seafood cacciatore
directions: Cook and stir onion and green pepper in hot oil in a large skillet.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomatoes, shrimp, scallops, wine, basil and oregano.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in the rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple crunch salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in apple juice and cinnamon; chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into an oiled 8-inch square dish; chill until firm.
Yields 9 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine vegetables, cheese and mayonnaise in baking dish.
Top with crackers.
Pour butter over mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Make pudding as directed on box. Fold cool whip into pudding. The rest is easy, just layer as follows: In a trifle bowl begin with vanilla wafers, then enough pudding mixture to cover wafers, follow with sliced bananas, again with pudding mixture. Continue this process until all ingredients are layered. Refrigerate several hours or overnight for best results.

title: pork cabbage soup(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Using a 2 to 3-quart microwave-safe dish, put in all but the noodles and cream of celery soup.
Cover and cook 45 minutes in microwave on Medium power.

title: native american fry-bread with yeast(golden light)
directions: Knead, then let rise until double.
Use a little oil on hands, take 3 inch ball of dough, roll out or spread with hands to 6 to 8-inches across and 1/8 inch thick.

title: pheasant with wild rice
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender; add wild rice, water and salt.
Cover and cook until rice is tender, 35 to 40 minutes.
Add mushrooms and sage.
Season cavity of pheasants with a little salt; stuff with rice mixture and tie legs to tails.
Place bacon over breast.
Roast in 350° oven for 1 to 2 1/2 hours, depending on size of bird.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix milk, sugar, cornstarch and egg yolks and cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Add margarine, vanilla and coconut. Cool and pour into cooked pie crust.

title: take along cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed. Add chips and marshmallows to batter. Pour into 13 x 9 pan. Drizzle butter and sprinkle with sugar and top with nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash, then boil until tender; drain and mash.
Combine all other ingredients, reserving a small amount of cheese and cracker crumbs (about 1/4 cup each).
Pour mixture into a greased casserole; sprinkle with remaining cheese and cracker crumbs. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes, until brown.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, white sugar, oil (for richness use 1 cup oil and 1 cup butter), vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, chocolate chips, oats and cornflakes (or 2 cups cornflakes and 2 cups Raisin Bran).
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: under-the-sea salad
directions: Drain pears, reserving 3/4 cup of the syrup.
Dice pears; set aside. Dissolve Jell-O and salt in boiling water.
Add reserved syrup and lemon juice.
Measure 1 1/4 cups of the Jell-O; pour into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan or 4 cup mold.
Chill until set but not firm, about 1 hour.
Very slowly blend remaining Jell-O into cream cheese, beating until smooth.
Add cinnamon and pears; spoon over clear Jell-O in pan.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold. Garnish with additional pears and maraschino cherry, if desired.

title: curried tuna rice salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; serve over lettuce.

title: clam chowder
directions: In medium kettle, saute bacon until almost crisp.
Add onion; cook until tender, 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook, covered, for 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add clams and liquid, milk and butter and cook 3 minutes. Sprinkle in crackers and heat through.
Do not boil.
Serves 8 small or 4 large.

title: pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla, in heavy pan.
Cook over medium heat about 12 minutes, stirring constantly with wooden spoon.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool 2 to 3 minutes. Stir until it starts to thicken.
Drop by spoon on wax paper.

title: spicy raisin coffeecake
directions: Sift flour once, measure, add sugar, salt, soda, baking powder and spices.
Sift together 3 times, sifting them into a mixing bowl the final time.
Make a well in center, then add oil, egg, buttermilk, syrup and raisins.
Mix only until blended, will be slightly lumpy.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan 2-inches deep.
Sprinkle the 1 tablespoon cinnamon and 1/4 cup sugar, which has been combined, over the top of the coffeecake.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper.

title: miniature meat balls
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large bowl, combine soy sauce, minced garlic and ginger.
Add ground beef and mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Form into balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Arrange on a lightly oiled baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes. Spear with toothpicks and serve hot with salsa or barbecue sauce. Makes 32 meat balls.

title: texas fudge cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, flour and salt together.
Melt butter and cocoa together.
Mix butter mixture into egg mixture and add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
While cake bakes, cut marshmallows in half.
When cake is done, place marshmallows upside-down on cake and put cake in oven long enough to melt them.
Let cool and then frost.

title: beef-mushroom quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prick bottom and sides of pie shell with a fork.
Bake 11 minutes.
For frozen crusts, follow package directions.
Brown meat and drain off grease.
In medium bowl, mix soup, milk, eggs and spices.
Add meat, mushrooms and cheese. Pour into partially baked pie shell.
Bake for one hour or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: easy italian casserole
directions: Cook and stir beef and onion until browned.
Stir in sauce, mushrooms, sugar and spices, stirring constantly and then occasionally for 10 minutes.

title: low calorie pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease or spray a 9-inch pie pan.
Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend 1 minute.
Pour into pie pan and bake for 50 minutes until center is puffed up. Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix Bisquick with seasonings.
Add onions, butter, beaten eggs and salad oil.
Add zucchini.
Mix and spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Good with sliced tomatoes.

title: "corton"
directions: Cover pork with water; add salt and pepper. Cook slowly, stirring occasionally. You cook pork until all water is evaporated. Must stir more frequently at the end. Just 5 minutes before serving, add allspice to taste. Serve in containers and let cool in refrigerator before covering container. Best when served as a sandwich with mustard or with pasta.

title: potato and cheese bake
directions: Gently mix the diced cooked potatoes with the chopped onion, bell pepper, diced Velveeta, salt and pepper.
Place in a large casserole.
Have oven heating to 325°.
In a saucepan, heat bread with milk and butter until blended.
Pour into the baking dish. Top with cornflake crumbs and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes or more.
Yields 8 servings.

title: sour cream
directions: Mix well in food processor.
Makes one cup.

title: spinach filled turkey roll(microwave)
directions: Combine turkey, onion and 1/4 cup spaghetti sauce.
On wax paper, pat out to a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Spread spinach over meat and sprinkle with cheese.
Starting with short end, roll up. Place seam side down in a
10 x 6-inch microwave dish.
Microwave on High for 12 minutes or until thoroughly cooked.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Heat the remaining spaghetti sauce and pour over the turkey roll.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Cook bay leaf, celery and onion in butter until tender. Discard bay leaf.
Add bread cubes and parsley.
Mix thoroughly with butter mixture.
Add eggs, oysters (save liquid) and poultry seasoning.
Next, add salt and pepper.
Add enough milk to oyster liquid to make 1/4 to 1/3 cup.
Add enough of the liquid to moisten stuffing.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown the ground beef, onion, garlic and salt.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Heat in crock-pot.
Serve with chips.

title: quick dinner fix
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, then drain.
Mix Veg-All, corn soup, mushroom soup or tomato soup, beef and onion all together. Combine in round cake pan.
Cover with cheese, then cut biscuits into fourths and put on top.
Bake in a 300° oven for 30 to 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Lay half the chilies in bottom of well-greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Top with 1/2 the tortilla strips and 1/2 the cheese. Arrange tomatoes on top.
Repeat the layers, using up all the remaining ingredients (chilies, tortillas and cheese).
Beat together eggs, milk and spices.
Pour evenly over casserole. Sprinkle lightly with paprika, if desired.

title: cheese biscuits with ham
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cayenne pepper into large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add cheese and toss to mix. Drizzle ice water over dry ingredients and mix lightly with fork just until dough holds together.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board and knead lightly 7 to 8 times.
Roll 1/2 inch thick and cut with 2-inch cutter.
Place 1/2 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.
Makes about 1 dozen.
Cut open and insert ham slices.

title: raspberry crisp
directions: Use topping with peaches, cherries, blueberries, apples, etc.

title: chicken salad amandine
directions: Boil chicken breasts in lightly salted water until meat is tender.
Remove stock for future use.
Let chicken cool.
Separate meat from bone and skin by pulling.
Leave chicken in medium-size strips.
Toss remaining ingredients except almonds with chicken meat.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Garnish with almonds and serve with frozen fruit salad.
Makes 12 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake about 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: brown rice dish
directions: The tradition, or rule, is for the older men to cook the fish. Shortly before he died, Uncle Melvin passed this technique on to some of his nephews.
(My brother shared with me.)

title: barb's corn bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding muffin mix last.
Pour into 7 x 11-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sherry beef
directions: Put meat and soups in casserole.
Add sherry.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or so.
Serve over rice.

title: "do ahead" brunch special
directions: Cut circles (donut) from bread and save holes.
One circle per slice of bread (use large glass and a shot glass for inside).
Put bread scraps in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer cheese over bread, then ham and then broccoli.
Arrange bread circles over top.
Use holes to fill in outer spaces.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over bread mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least six hours.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes. This is an attractive dish; bread circles form a patterned crust when baked.
At Christmas, tree cut-outs can be used.

title: bonnie's favorite pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature. Cream together the butter and sugar. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating constantly. Reduce to blend. Add the sour cream and flour.
Add the baking powder. When all ingredients are blended, bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a loaf or tube pan, greased and floured.
(You can use butter to grease pan.)

title: personal pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease one or two baking sheets. Sprinkle flour on baking counter.
Pull biscuits apart.
Stretch or roll into 4-inch diameter.
Spoon pizza sauce on and spread. Sprinkle each with cheese.
Add favorite toppings.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until crust is brown.
Serve to friends.

title: flip flop bean salad
directions: The title of this concoction identifies the process necessary to produce the flavor of this combination. Need 2-quart storage container with a lid that will seal without a leakage when container is inverted; i.e., turned over, upside down, at least four times in twenty-four hours before serving.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugars, dressing and vanilla with electric mixer; add flour and baking soda.
Set aside 1 cup of the batter.
Spread remaining batter into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Melt caramels with milk over low heat.
Top crust with caramel mixture; sprinkle with chips and pecans.
Spoon reserved 1 cup batter by teaspoonfuls over pecans.
Continue baking 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apple betty
directions: Place apples in a buttered baking dish. Combine flour and cinnamon. Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Sprinkle over apples and bake about 15 minutes in a 450° oven.
Makes 6 servings.

title: granny waldrep's lye soap
directions: Add the ingredients in a large kettle and boil for 1 hour. Put into flat crocks to cool.
Cut it into bars the next day.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream together butter, granulated sugar and 1/2 cup brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add water, vanilla and egg yolks (reserve whites in a separate bowl).
Beat for 2 to 3 minutes. Beat in flour, salt, baking soda and powder.
Spread batter onto lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan or jelly roll pan. Sprinkle on chocolate chips.
Beat egg whites until they form soft peaks, then add reserved brown sugar, blending well.
Carefully spread over chips.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until whites are brown.
Cut with sharp knife while still hot.
Yields 3 dozen bars.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Clean strawberries and slice.
Put in baked and cooled pie crust.

title: jody's italian chicken
directions: Bone chicken breasts and cut meat into 1 or 2 inch pieces. Soak chicken pieces in egg and milk for one hour.
While chicken is cooking, boil the bones for broth.
Roll chicken pieces in bread crumbs.
Brown chicken pieces in margarine.
Put chicken pieces in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and Parmesan cheese. Cover with mushrooms and chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or longer.
Baste with stock while baking and add more lemon juice or cheese to suit your taste.
Serves 4 to 6. Serve with rice and tossed salad.
Can be frozen.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.
Other fresh vegetables may be added to suit your taste.

title: caramel dip
directions: Cream together all ingredients in medium size bowl.
Serve with sliced apples, fruit or nuts.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Add walnuts and raisins that have been rolled in 2 tablespoons flour, taken out of the flour.
Sift flour, salt, soda and spices together.
Stir into the butter mixture; add applesauce.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 or 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: grandma's pizza steak
directions: Place steak in covered baking dish or pan.
Place cheese strips over top of steak along with garlic.
Pour tomato sauce on top, then olive oil, a little salt and pepper and oregano to taste. Rinse tomato sauce can out a little and pour some of the water in the bottom of the baking dish.
Cook at 400° for 45 minutes.
Serve with sliced Italian bread to dip into gravy.

title: williamsburg egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar together.
Add brandy, rum and heavy cream.
Beat 6 egg whites until stiff, beating in remaining egg whites alternately with the powdered sugar.
Fold in light cream; mix together.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.

title: dill carrots
directions: Cook carrots until medium tender.
Drain and pierce several times with a fork.
Mix dressing and seasonings.
Pour over carrots and marinate 24 hours in refrigerator; serve cold.

title: jalapeno baked beans
directions: Mix beans, diced pepper, onion, ketchup, brown sugar and Monterey Jack cheese (grated).
Mix thoroughly and put grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly in 350° oven.

title: curry marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate in refrigerator for 4 hours or overnight.
Can be used for all kinds of meat.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour melted butter into 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Drain peaches and reserve 1/2 cup of juice to boil with peaches in saucepan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, milk, baking powder and salt. Pour over butter.
Arrange peaches on top of batter.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over peaches.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: homemade creole
directions: Batter your steak in flour, then fry it until done.
Chop up fried steak and combine it with the remaining ingredients in a pot.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes on low (or until potatoes are done), stirring occasionally.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees in pyrex dish about 30-45 minutes.

title: deep south beans
directions: Cube tomato.
Section onion.
Deseed and cut bell pepper into small cubes.
Mix beans, tomato, onion and bell pepper with taco seasoning and bake in large casserole dish.
Garnish top with jalapeno peppers and cheese.
(Some cheese may also be mixed with the beans).
Bake at 375° to 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve as entree with Corn Fritters and other vegetables.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Boil together strawberries and 1 cup sugar for 2 minutes.
Add 2 cups of sugar and boil together for 5 minutes.
This needs to be stirred.
Pour into a flat pan and stir occasionally.
Let stand for one day or overnight.
Put into jars and place in the freezer. Good as topping for ice cream.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in orange peel, orange juice and egg just until moistened.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Spread in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, cream margarine and brown sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Blend in flour mixture at low speed alternately with milk until well blended.
Stir in vanilla and rhubarb.
Turn into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
May sprinkle with powdered or regular sugar.
Serve with whipped topping, ice cream or just plain.

title: crab quiche
directions: You will need a 9-inch pie plate.

title: stir-fried cabbage
directions: Heat vegetable oil in heavy large pot over medium-high heat. Add ginger and stir 30 seconds. Add half of cabbage and toss until wilted, about 4 minutes. Add remaining cabbage, green onions and sesame oil. Toss until all cabbage is crisp-tender, about 4 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper and serve.

title: smooth and creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in a small bowl.
Beat slowly with rotary beater until well blended.
Fold in whipped topping. Store frosted cake in refrigerator.

title: bacon-almond cheese sticks(yield: 40)
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Combine all ingredients.
Spread mixture on bread.
Slice bread (with mixture on it) into 4 or 5 sticks per slice.
Bake
on greased cookie sheet at 300° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Place rolls randomly in pan.
Mix brown sugar and pudding mix. Sprinkle over rolls.
Combine granulated sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over the rest.
Place pecan pieces on top.
Pour the melted butter over all.
Let stand overnight, uncovered.
Next morning, bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes before turning out of pan. Pull apart to eat!

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, milk, pumpkin and cinnamon.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix (dry) on top.
Pour melted margarine over dry cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over top.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: In skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook mushrooms, onion and garlic about 5 minutes until tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in zucchini, broccoli and basil.
Cover; cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine melted Crisco, cocoa and salt, then add milk and vanilla.
Mix in sugar in 3 parts.
Mix until smooth and creamy. Add more sugar to thicken or milk to thin for good spreading consistency.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Have margarine at room temperature.
Mix margarine with sugar. Add eggs one at a time.
Add sour cream.
Mix flour, soda and salt together, then add to wet mixture.
After blending well, add coconut and vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: glazed lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix 1 cup baking mix and the powdered sugar.
Cut in margarine.
Press in ungreased square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake until light brown, about 10 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients except Glaze; pour over baked layer.
Bake until set, about 25 minutes.
Loosen edges from sides of pan while warm. Spread with Glaze.
Cool completely; cut into about 1-inch squares. Makes 64 cookies.

title: fresh chili salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a glass bowl.
Cover and allow to marinate at least 2 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle hash browns and cheese over sausage. Beat together eggs, milk and salt; pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until bottom crust is browned and center is set.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: curried lobster
directions: Partially thaw lobster tails.
Using knife, butterfly tails (cut down center of back and open wide, do not cut under membrane). Place on broiler pan, shell side down.
Dash a few drops of bottled hot pepper sauce into melted butter; brush over meat.
Broil 4-inches from heat until meat loses its translucency and can be flaked with a fork, about 17 minutes for a 6 to 8 ounce tail. Loosen meat; serve with butter and lemon.

title: simple salmon loaf
directions: Beat egg slightly and mix with remaining ingredients, until well blended.
Pack salmon mixture firmly in a greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch microproof loaf pan.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook on 70 (Roast) for 25 to 30 minutes or until loaf is firm.
Let stand, covered, 10 minutes before slicing.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Total cooking time:
25 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and milk; cook over low heat until the soft ball stage (240°).
Stir constantly.
Remove from fire and add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme; mix well, until it starts to thicken.
Pour into buttered pan to cool.
Almost fills a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Keeps well and packs well for mailing.

title: ham party rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and spread on rolls.
Top with ham and cheese.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: crowd pleasing crab dip
directions: Pick over the crabmeat to make certain there are no pieces of shell in the meat. Combine all ingredients together and chill well. Serve with dipping size Fritos.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: *If canned sweet potatoes are used, use only 1/2 cup milk.

title: taco salad
directions: Cut the lettuce into very thin pieces.
Chop tomatoes into medium pieces.
Cut the slices of American cheese into thin strips. Add the red kidney beans and onions, then mix in a large bowl. Brown the hamburger.
Drain and add salt.
Serves 8.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, allspice, cloves and nutmeg.
Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla and 2 sticks melted margarine (not hot).
Bake in slow oven of 300° until done.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 2 eggs and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and rice with sherry
directions: Butter a large baking dish.
Spread uncooked rice in the dish. Arrange chicken (skin side up or may wish to remove skin after baking) on the rice.
Pour the mixture of orange juice, sherry and golden mushroom soup over the chicken.
Sprinkle the onion soup over the top.
Cover with lid or foil.
Bake for 2 hours at 325°, then uncover and bake 15 to 20 minutes, until rice is dry and chicken is browned.

title: onion pie
directions: Saute onions in butter and cooking oil until soft, not brown, about 10 minutes.
Cover.
Add diced bacon and salt.
Simmer 10 minutes.
While onions and bacon are simmering, combine eggs and whipping cream, stirring until thoroughly mixed.
Place in refrigerator until ready to use.
Smooth dinner roll dough over a greased 12 3/4 x 9-inch pan or cookie sheet.
Combine onions and bacon with egg and cream mixture.
Spread mixture evenly over the dough.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until golden.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat 1 inch oil in Dutch oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil.
Fry about 1 minute, turning once, until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot. Yields 15 to 20 hush puppies.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients in order.
Put in 9-inch crust and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate anglaise with fruit
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa powder and salt in medium-size heavy saucepan.
Gradually whisk in milk until well blended and smooth. Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until sugar dissolves.
Remove saucepan from heat.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Mix the three pie ingredients together and bring to a boil in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate one hour before serving.
Top with Dream Whip or Cool Whip.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and pineapple (crushed) with juice in pan. Heat until mixture simmers. Add sugar, baby food and cream cheese (diced). Mix well but do not beat. Chill until thickened when dropped from spoon, about 15 minutes. Slowly blend in Cool Whip. Chill overnight.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Heat soup, Ro-Tel and broth to boil. Divide remaining ingredients making layers twice in baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: brie wheel in pastry shell
directions: Follow Pepperidge Farm pastry instructions.
Place cheese in center.
Top with preserves.
Fold edges of dough up to seal Brie inside, corners to center.
Beat 1 egg with water and brush on top. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet or use Pam if desired.
Bake at 425° to 450° until golden brown (oven ranges vary).

title: patty melts
directions: Fry ground beef, made into 3 patties.
Butter each slice of bread on one side.
Place hamburger patty, cheese and onions between 2 slices of bread and grill until golden brown on each side.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Add rice.
Pour soups over rice. Bake 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half and wipe well with paper towel. In large bowl, combine sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, paprika, garlic, salts and pepper.
Add chicken to sour cream mixture, coating each piece well.
Let stand, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove chicken from sour cream mixture and roll in crumbs.
Arrange in large, shallow baking dish.
Melt butter and shortening in a small saucepan and spoon half over chicken.
Bake chicken, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Spoon rest of butter mixture over chicken and bake for 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Serves 12.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs; add sour milk.
Sift flour, soda and salt; stir in nuts, cherries and dates.
Chill.
Drop from spoon on greased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Mix yeast,
water
and	sugar
and
let stand for a few minutes.
In
saucepan,
bring to boil molasses, water, sugar, shortening, salt and anise seed.
Place buttermilk and soda in large
mixing bowl.
Add partially cooled molasses mixture and yeast mixture.
Stir
in rye flour.
Add white flour and knead until dough is not sticky.

title: chuck's party mix
directions: Melt butter, sauces and salt over low heat.
Mix cereals and nuts in large paper sacks.
Divide evenly into large aluminum pans.
Sprinkle sauce evenly over mix.
Stir to coat cereal.
Bake in slow oven for 1 1/2 hours at 250°.
Stir mixture every 15 minutes.
Cool; store in airtight containers.
Makes great Christmas gifts!

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Mix well and pour into greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes its own crust.

title: ginny's pancakes
directions: Beat eggs and sugar good.
Pour
in buttermilk and beat well. Add
flour to desired
consistency.
When
griddle
or skillet has reached correct temperature, fry cakes.
Serve hot with butter and syrup.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix together soup, hash browns and onion.
In 9 x 13 pan, layer potato mixture and cheese.
Continue layering ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cajun lima beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Remove, crumble and reserve.
Add flour to drippings.
Blend well.
Add onions.
Cook and stir until onions are limp.
Add beans and cook until done.
Add seasonings with enough water to cover.
Mix well and cook 10 minutes.
Serve with bacon garnish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cranberry cream pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Combine whipping cream, sugar and vanilla and whip until thickened but not stiff.
Mix with cream cheese and beat until smooth and creamy.
Fold in cranberry sauce and spoon into chilled pie crust.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: curried chicken and broccoli
directions: Place cooked broccoli in casserole dish and top with chicken slices.
Combine other ingredients and heat on low heat.
Pour over top of broccoli and chicken.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Or prepare and freeze; return to room temperature before baking.)

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery, nuts and mayonnaise. Toss. Refrigerate.

title: fresh orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and set in refrigerator until firm.
You may add bananas to this also.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake the chocolate cake and cool.

title: mr. tim's grilled cheese
directions: Take the two slices of bread and spread butter on one side of the bread.
Turn your frying pan on #4 or 3/4 of the way on.
Put one slice of bread on the pan and then take one slice of cheese and put on bread.
After that put the one slice of ham or turkey. Put the last piece of cheese and let cook on each side for about 5 to 10 seconds, if pan is hot.
Do not smash the bread together.

title: "frikadeller" (danish meatballs)(catherine hamilton's kitchen)
directions: Mix meat with salt, pepper and onion juice.
Add flour, eggs and
milk
(small
amounts	at
a time).
Mix thoroughly. Make into
balls
about 2-inches in diameter.
Brown in butter in skillet at high heat.
Turn down and finish frying, turning occasionally, uncovered.

title: boned chicken casserole
directions: Cover the bottom of casserole with chipped beef.
Wrap 1/2 slice bacon around each breast and place in bottom of greased casserole.
Mix undiluted soup and sour cream.
Pour over the chicken.
Cook, uncovered, for 3 hours at 250°.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Dissolve soda in 1/2 cup water.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pinch off dough as needed. Pat out about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Refrigerate rest of dough, covered, until needed.
Will keep about 1 week.
No rising time.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes.

title: black forest trifle
directions: Cool and chill the pudding.
Fold together pudding and Cool Whip.
In a glass bowl, layer 1/2 of cake pieces, 1/2 of pudding mixture and 1/2 of cherries.
Repeat layers.
Chill and serve.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Mix 24 hours before serving.

title: easy glazed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a plastic or paper bag, combine flour and pepper. Add chicken and shake to coat well. Place in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: applesauce puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add applesauce, milk, egg and oil.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Fill greased 2-inch muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake 12 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pan and dip tops in melted butter (2 tablespoons), then in a mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Makes 24.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Mix peas, onion and tomato together.
Add just enough mayonnaise to mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: prisajak (serbian casserole)
directions: Mix together all ingredients in greased casserole dish. Squeeze excess water out of defrosted spinach before adding to other ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: kentucky prune cake
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed.
Put in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until sides shrink and top springs back, 45 minutes or longer.

title: cream of pimento soup
directions: Melt butter; add flour and seasonings.
Blend well.
Add milk, meat stock and pimentos that have been put through sieve.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes, stirring until mixture thickens.
This makes 10 servings.

title: granny's famous chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onions, salt and pepper; drain well.
Add hamburger to all other ingredients.
Bring to slow boil.
Add broken very thin spaghetti (small handful).
Simmer over low heat for at least 1 hour.
Taste test.
Add chili powder and water as needed.

title: old fashion yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Grease muffin tins.
Fill each tin about 1/2 full of batter.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Yields 30 rolls.

title: potato cheese chowder
directions: Place all ingredients, except cheese, in a 2-quart glass casserole.
Microwave, covered, on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in cheese until melted. Microwave, uncovered, on High, stirring every 2 to 3 minutes until desired consistency.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add orange juice, orange rind and egg.
Stir until moist.
Add chopped cranberries and nuts.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour or until done.

title: texas sheet cake and frosting
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar in a large bowl and set aside.
Mix oleo, water, cooking oil and cocoa in a saucepan on low heat. Heat until melted and starts to boil.
Pour over flour mixture. Mix well.
Add eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla and mix well. Bake in a greased oblong cookie sheet pan for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: garden vinaigrette
directions: Spread walnuts on cookie sheet and toast in a 325° oven for 5 to 8 minutes.
Chop walnuts coarsely.
In medium bowl blend walnut and olive oils, vinegar, honey, mustard, pepper and salt. Stir in walnuts.
Pour dressing over vegetables and marinate 8 to 24 hours.
To serve, arrange on large platter and garnish with rosemary.
Makes 24 servings.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Prepare brownies according to directions in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool.
While brownies are cooling, prepare mixture of 10x sugar, margarine, peppermint extract, food coloring and water as needed. Don't make it too runny, make like frosting.
Spread over cooked brownies.
Top with melted chocolate chips and margarine.
Heat in small saucepan to melt until smooth.
Spread to cover all the top. Cool and cut into small squares.

title: lemony blueberry muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In separate bowl, stir together yogurt, eggs, vanilla, oil and milk. Make a well in dry ingredients; add liquid ingredients.
Add frozen blueberries (do not thaw).
Stir just until blended.
Spoon into 12 to 14 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups that have been sprayed with Pam.
Fill 12 cups full if you want large muffins or spread batter over 14 cups for smaller muffins.
Sprinkle tops with a little sugar, if desired.
Bake in 425° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: vicki's summer salad
directions: A small onion is good in this salad also. Best made and served right away.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart microwave bowl, stir in sugar, salt, syrup and peanuts. Cook on High for 4 minutes. Stir and cook 4 minutes longer, then add butter and vanilla. Mix well. Then add soda and stir quickly. Pour out on buttered pans.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: *Whirl oatmeal in blender until powderized.

title: cheddar mushroom macaroni
directions: In a large bowl, mix the first 6 ingredients; mix well. Stir in macaroni while hot and add garlic (if desired). Transfer to a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes at 325° or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and mashed bananas.
Add sour cream which has been combined with baking soda. Mix well and add flour and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 11-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put cucumbers and
onions
in large kettle.
Cover with 1/2 cup salt and
then	with
crushed ice.
Let stand 3 hours. Drain. Mix and
heat
remaining
ingredients.
Bring to boil, but do not boil.
Add	cucumber
and onions.
Place at once in hot sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 8 pints.

title: parsley almond rice(recipe served at club meetings)
directions: Heat chicken broth in medium saucepan over medium-high heat to boiling.
Stir in rice and salt.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer, covered, until rice is tender and all liquid has been absorbed, 13 to 15 minutes.

title: orange glaze
directions: Combine soft butter, powdered sugar, salt, lemon juice, and orange juice.
When smooth, stir in orange rind.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine dry pudding as it comes from the box with all the other ingredients.
Mix very well.
Chill overnight.

title: champignons a'la creme(mushrooms boiled with cream)
directions: In wide frying pan, combine mushrooms, shallots and cream. Place on medium heat and cook, stirring occasionally about 15 minutes.
Increase heat to high and boil, stirring often, until shiny bubbles form (10 minutes).
Stir in parsley and season with salt.

title: chocolate souffle custard
directions: Separate eggs and combine yolks, cornstarch, salt and 1/2 cup sugar in saucepan.
Gradually stir in 2 cups milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and pour into custard cups, 2/3 full.

title: vegetable fruit salad
directions: Heat orange juice and dissolve lemon and peach jello in it; do not boil.
Dissolve Knox gelatine (one envelope) as directed on package.
Mix the two gelatin mixtures together.
Add pineapple. Mix the mayonnaise and sour cream and add to the jello mixture. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and chill until firm.

title: frosted nuts
directions: Mix egg whites, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add pecan halves. Grease cookie sheet.
Drop one pecan half at a time.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: blue cheese deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs; cut lengthwise.
Remove yolk; set aside whites. Mash yolks with cheese; blend in sour cream and vinegar.
Fill egg whites with yolk mixture.
Garnish with pimiento.
Cover and chill.
Serve in lettuce cups.
Yields 4 servings.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients; knead lightly.
Roll out and use round biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° until lightly browned.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning. Layer on beans; add lettuce, onion,
Cheddar cheese, tomatoes, garden pepper and olives.

title: ribs fantastic
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place ribs in a baking pan.
In a medium bowl, combine brown sugar, ketchup, water, vinegar, lemon juice, celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well, then pour over ribs in pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 3 hours, or until tender.

title: spinach pie
directions: Saute onions and spinach (after you drain spinach).
Add tuna and seasonings.
Set aside to cool, then add beaten eggs.
Mix well.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
One half cup nuts may be added.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: orange ice cream dreamers
directions: In blender, or food processor, place ice cream, orange juice and Schnapps or Amaretto.
Cover and blend or process just until smooth.
Pour into champagne or wine glasses to serve.
Garnish with oranges.

title: chicken and black-eyed peas stew
directions: Cook chicken parts over medium heat in oil until brown on all sides in a large, heavy pan or Dutch oven.
Spoon off fat.
Add chicken broth, vegetables, garlic, pepper sauce, salt, thyme and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until thickest pieces of chicken are done, 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix water and flour together until smooth in a small bowl.
Slowly add flour mixture to stew, stirring constantly to prevent lumps.
Cook until mixture thickens, stirring often.
Serve with rice.
Garnish with green onions, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: low-fat thousand island dressing
directions: Mix well and store in covered container.

title: hermits
directions: Grease a cookie sheet.
Combine flour, soda, salt and spices. Beat butter for 30 seconds; add brown sugar and beat until fluffy. Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 36.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix ingredients.
Soak meat 30 minutes to 2 days, then longer the better.
Grill.

title: perky party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale and fruit slices, in a large punch bowl.
Mix well and chill.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale, then float fruit slices on top.
Ice cube trays may be filled with ginger ale, to which a cherry has been added. Freeze and add to punch.

title: jesse's easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onions.
Drain fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients except kidney beans.
Add 1 cup of water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes. Stir in kidney beans.
Heat.
Serve with oyster crackers.
Makes 8 servings (1 cup each).

title: black eyed pea salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl and mix.	Add the peas and the rest of ingredients.
Cover and chill for at least 2 hours. Serves 3-4.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Combine 1/4 cup flour, paprika, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper. Halve chicken breasts and remove bones.
Coat with flour mixture. Brown in butter.
Add 2 tablespoons water.
Simmer and cover for 25 minutes.
Remove chicken to an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Reserve drippings.
Combine 2 tablespoons flour, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and cream.
Stir into reserved drippings in skillet. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Drain sliced mushrooms.
Add mushrooms and lemon juice to sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and chill up to 24 hours.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 60 minutes. Sprinkle the last 5 minutes with cheese until it melts.

title: mexicali macaroni
directions: In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook the macaroni until tender, but still firm, about 5 minutes.
While the macaroni is cooking, brown the beef in a frying pan over high heat, stirring occasionally.
When the meat is brown, drain off the fat.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water; boil until clear.
Add butter and vanilla; blend well.
Cool.
Add berries.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: corned beef mold
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water;
add all other ingredients and mix well.
Chill until set.
Serve with crackers.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in 9 x 13 dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: beef and rice almondine
directions: Shape ground beef into a large patty in a large frying pan. Brown 5 minutes on each side, then break up in chunks.
Stir in chicken soup, instant beef broth or bouillon cube, water, celery, onion, rice, soy sauce and oregano.
Heat to boiling, crushing the bouillon cube (if used) with spoon.
Pour into a greased 8-cup baking dish. Cover. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Uncover. Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until golden brown. Test rice for doneness.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Combine flour and margarine with pastry blender or you can use a food processor.
Add water and sugar.
Work into a dough.
Add nuts.
Shape into small round balls or tiny fingers.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool, then roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 48.

title: sparkling harvest cider
directions: In punch bowl combine cider, lemon juice and sugar.
Chill. Just before serving add ginger ale and serve over ice.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini briefly in salted water and drain.
Saut onion and carrot in butter.
Mix all together and bake in a casserole at 350° until brown and bubbly.
Good as a side dish with chicken. The recipe makes a large amount, so I divide it and freeze portions in plastic containers.

title: hot onion dip
directions: Place in ovenproof bowl and bake at 375° for approximately 20 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: butter pecan squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch square baking pan. In a small bowl, cream the butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour.
Stir in 1 cup of chocolate chips and 1/2 cup pecans.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven.
Immediately sprinkle remaining 1 cup of chips over surface.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes or until chips soften.
Spread evenly.
Immediately sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup pecans over top.
Press gently onto chocolate.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares.
Yields 16 squares.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Spread mixture evenly on flat tortilla.
Roll snug, but with ease.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 2 hours, best overnight.
Slice on an angle in bite-size pieces.
Keep chilled and serve with salsa for dipping.
Makes about 48.

title: reuben brunch casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange bread cubes on bottom. Coarsely shred corned beef. Layer beef over bread. Sprinkle with cheese. Beat eggs, milk and pepper until well blended.
Pour over corned beef mixture.
Cover with foil. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: dole ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges. Combine pineapple, oranges, bananas, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and almonds. Fold in yogurt and chill.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon and remove.
Add onion to fat in pan and brown slowly. Drain fat before adding all ingredients together.
Mix all together in casserole. Add dry crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 or 50 minutes.

title: glazed orange carrots
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
Combine margarine, sugar, orange juice and paprika in skillet.
Heat over medium heat until bubbly. Add carrots.
Cook for 5 to 8 minutes or until glazed, stirring constantly.

title: fluffy meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover bowl and refrigerate several hours. (This makes them fluffier than cooking immediately.)
Form small balls with spoons (not hands) and cook.
