Don't overcrowd in pan. May be kept warm in oven while finishing cooking the other or for serving later.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain juice from orange segments and crushed pineapple.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl; add drained juice until ingredients are moist.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato until tender. Let cool until it's workable. Then mix in powdered sugar, enough until thick. Pinch small amount of dough and pat in palm of hand until oblong. Place oblong dough on piece of wax paper. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Spread dough with peanut butter. Roll up and slice with knife. Refrigerate the candy until firm.

title: raisin nut bread
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add sugar, salt and buttermilk. Allow to cool.
Stir in eggs.
Sift together the flour and salt. Add raisins and nuts; blend well.
Put dough into a loaf pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool; cut in slices.

title: raisin cupcakes
directions: Slice
or
chop
raisins.
Cream
butter and sugar; add beaten egg.
Sift	flour and baking powder and add alternating with milk to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly; add raisins and lemon extract and
blend
well.	Fill greased muffin pans 1/2 full.
Bake 20 minutes
in a hot oven at 425°.
Makes 12 to 14 cupcakes.

title: beef stew marsala
directions: Reminder:
Hot pan, cold oil; meat will not stick.

title: blueberry pineapple sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch; gradually beat in pineapple juice and water.
Add blueberries.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sauce bubbles and thickens.
Yield: 3 cups sauce.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and spices together 3 times.
Cream shortening with sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly. Add sifted dry ingredients and applesauce, alternating in small amounts and beating well after each addition.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: tofu and mandarins
directions: Cut tofu into 1/2-inch cubes.
Gently mix tofu with the mandarins, syrup, marmalade and liqueur in a large bowl.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Serve in dessert dish or as a side dish with poultry or pork.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: In a large soup pot combine beef, chili, tomatoes, onions, carrots, celery, cabbage and chili powder. Salt and pepper. Saut until the vegetables are soft, about 5 minutes. Add water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Makes approximately 1 gallon.

title: popover pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and drain.
Stir spaghetti sauce mix, tomato sauce and water into meat and simmer 10 minutes. Spoon into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix yams, sugars, 1/2 cup margarine and milk.
Pour in casserole dish.
Mix corn flakes, pecans and remaining 1 stick of margarine.
Pour over other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy corned beef hash
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Chop onions and put into pot with salt and pepper.
Cover potatoes with water.
Cover pot and cook until the potatoes start to fall apart and liquid starts to thicken.
Add the can of corned beef (separate into small chunks) and cook for at least 5 minutes.

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Peel potatoes and slice.
Add all other ingredients together and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lasagne
directions: Mix ground chuck, cooked and drained, with spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce.
When mixed together, add Ricotta cheese. Alternate cooked lasagne strips, sauce and Mozzarella cheese into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: all-in-one hamburger casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Put rice on bottom of casserole. Mix hamburger, salt, pepper and onion together.
Put hamburger mixture on top of rice.
Pour can of tomatoes (with liquid) on top of hamburger.
Pour can of corn (with liquid) on top of tomatoes. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Mix vanilla pudding mix and Tang together; drain juice from canned fruit into dry mixture; mix well.
Then add bananas and grapes; mix well and chill.
Slice kiwi fruit on top for looks. Chill and enjoy.
This is supposed to keep in refrigerator for 7 to 10 days.

title: fluffy banana omelette
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch Teflon pan over low heat.
Break eggs into container of electric blender.
Cover and blend on high speed 30 seconds.
Break banana into chunks; add to mixture.
Stir in club soda; turn up heat on butter to medium-high, then pour in egg mixture.
Servings of 2.

title: pineapple astoria
directions: Drain pineapple;
reserve
juice.
Line
a
9 x 13-inch dish with pineapple.
Top pineapple generously with marshmallows. Dissolve
gelatin in boiling water and pour over marshmallows. When cool, refrigerate; add water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Mix
cornstarch
with a little of the liquid. Beat egg well.
Mix	all
together
and
add salt and butter. Cook
this mixture, stirring constantly until thickened, then cool thoroughly.
Whip	cream
and
blend
mixtures.
Top gelatin mixture
with
it.	Top
this with coconut, nuts and a few	cut up	maraschino
cherries.
Refrigerate until serving time.	Serves 15.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill in the refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Yields 6 servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix in a large bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: white corn hominy
directions: Dissolve lime in water in large kettle.
Add corn and boil for 30 minutes or until hulls loosen.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Then wash in cold water until dark tips of kernels are removed.
Rinse again until water is clean.
Use in Posoli.

title: chinese fried walnuts
directions: In a large saucepan over
high	heat,
bring
6 cups of water to boiling.
Add
walnuts
and
reheat to boiling.	Cook for 1 minute.
Rinse under
running
hot	water.	Drain.	In a large bowl, toss walnuts	with
sugar.
Meanwhile, in electric skillet, heat about 1-inch of salad oil to 350°.
With slotted spoon, add about half of the
walnuts	to
the oil.
Fry for 5 minutes or until golden,
stirring often.
With slotted spoon, place walnuts in coarse
sieve
over
bowl to drain.
Sprinkle with salt.
Toss lightly to keep walnuts from sticking together.
Transfer to waxed paper to cool.
Fry remaining walnuts. Let cool at least 1 hour. Store in covered container.
Yields 4 cups.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into long baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° until brown; cool.

title: zachary taylor's special red bean soup
directions: This is believed to be one of the best bean soups of the past.

title: fried rice
directions: In 6-quart pan on a medium stove, pour oil.
Add cardamon, cinnamon and the cloves.
When spicy smells come, add onion and hot pepper.
When onion gets light brown, add ginger and garlic pastes, turmeric powder and salt.
After a few minutes, add water.
Allow the water to boil.
Add the coriander leaves, minced leaves and the rice.
Mix and cover for 7 minutes.
Mix again and put in preheated 300° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and remove all the cardamon, cinnamon, cloves and hot pepper.
Transfer to serving dish.
If you like, garnish with cashew nuts and fried onions and serve it hot.

title: pizzelles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Batter should be like pancake batter.
Makes about 50 cookies.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: dinner in a pumpkin
directions: Cut off the top of pumpkin and thoroughly clean out seeds and pulp.
Paint face on front of the pumpkin with a permanent marker or acrylic paint.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, saute onion in oil until tender.
Add meat and brown.
Drain drippings from skillet.
Add soy sauce, brown sugar, mushrooms and soup. Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cooked rice and water chestnuts.
Spoon mixture into cleaned pumpkin shell. Replace pumpkin top and place entire pumpkin, with filling, on a baking sheet.
Bake 1 hour or until inside meat of pumpkin is tender.
Put pumpkin on plate.
Remove top and serve meat.

title: spicy sausage and rice
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Drain well and place into skillet. Stir in rice and cook over low heat for 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until done, stirring occasionally.
Takes about 30 minutes.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Simmer sausage in 2 cups water 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in half lengthwise; scoop out inside, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Cut scooped out portion into 1-inch squares. Saute in oil 5 minutes or until tender.
Heat spaghetti sauce in pan.
Add Parmesan cheese, mushrooms and bread crumbs.
When heated, add eggplant.

title: creamy tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and garlic powder until well blended. Spread each tortilla with thin layer of beans. Spread cream cheese mixture over beans. Top with olives and cilantro. Roll tortillas up tightly. Refrigerate 30 minutes. Cut into 1/2-inch slices. Serve with salsa. Yield: 10 servings.

title: family favorite baked beans
directions: Brown meats; drain.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add sugars, ketchup, barbecue sauce, mustard, molasses and seasonings. Mix well.
Add beans.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or put into crock-pot set for 1 hour on high, then low for 4 hours.

title: light broiled scallops
directions: Preheat broiler.
In flameproof casserole dish, place scallops in a single layer.
Mix next 4 ingredients together and toss to coat scallops.
Broil until golden, about 2 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: low calorie sour cream substitute
directions: Mix in food processor or blender.
Chill. This will thicken as it chills (about 6 hours).
Will keep, refrigerated, for 1 week.

title: winter chicken bake
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Drain, peel and mash.
Stir in 1/2 the cheese and 1/2 the onions.
Spread potato mixture over bottom and up sides of a greased 2-quart rectangular baking dish to form
a shell.
Combine chicken, vegetables, soup, mustard, garlic powder and pepper; spoon into shell.
Cover loosely and bake in oven at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and onions.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Bake at 350° until brown.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Unwrap tamales, cut in half lengthwise. Line a 1-1/2 quart casserole with 1/2 of the tamales, chili, onions, chips and cheese. Repeat layers. Bake covered in a 350° oven for 25 minutes. 4 servings.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 400° until brown in large skillet.

title: chicken wrapped with bacon
directions: Spiral a slice of bacon around each chicken breast and place in a glass baking dish. In a medium mixing bowl, mix soup, sour cream and flour. Spoon mixture over top of chicken breasts. Can be topped with cut up green onions. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: grilled marinated chicken
directions: Mix Italian salad dressing and buttermilk.
Place chicken breasts in a Ziploc bag or flat container with lid and pour mixture over chicken; refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Turn over at least once to make sure chicken is covered, then grill for 20 minutes.

title: ginger chicken with ham-fried rice
directions: Combine soy sauce, sugar, ginger root and garlic in a large zip-top heavy-duty plastic bag.
Place chicken in bag and secure tightly.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours, turning bag occasionally. Remove chicken, reserving marinade.
Arrange chicken pieces in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish with thickest portions towards outside of dish.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 5 minutes. Reduce to Medium-high (70% power); cover and microwave for 20 minutes, rearranging pieces and topping with marinade after 10 minutes.
Serve over Ham-Fried Rice.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; season to taste.
Stir in frozen peas and celery soup.
Put mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread the Cheddar cheese soup on top.
Arrange Tater Tots on top to cover.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Sort and wash peas.
Place in a 6-quart pressure cooker.
Add water, 1 tablespoon oil and next four ingredients.
Stir well. Close lid securely to bring to high pressure over high heat, about 7 minutes.
Adjust heat to medium or level needed to maintain high pressure.
Cook 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool under cold running water.
Remove lid.
Drain mixture, reserving 2 cups cooking liquid.
Set aside.

title: strawberry jello delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Pour half of mixture in a mold and place in refrigerator to set.
When firm, spread with a tasty cheese spread and pour remaining Jell-O mixture over it.
Chill until firm.

title: kentucky pumpkin cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat Ricotta until smooth with electric hand mixer.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time. Sift together flour, cinnamon, allspice, ginger and salt and add to mixture.
Beat in pumpkin, half and half and bourbon.

title: sweet chocolate custard cake
directions: Beat one of the eggs and combine with 1/2 cup of the milk and 2/3 cup of the sugar.
Cook and stir over medium heat for about 2 minutes.
Add the chocolate; reduce heat and cook until chocolate is melted and mixture thickens.
Cool to room temperature. Meanwhile, cream margarine; add remaining cup of sugar gradually. Cream until light and fluffy.
Add remaining eggs, one at a time and beat well after each.
Sift flour; measure and sift again with soda and salt.
Combine milk and vanilla, then add flour mixture and milk alternately to the creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in cooled chocolate mixture and beat until well blended.
Pour into three 8-inch round layer pans which have been greased and floured on the bottom.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: georgia peach pie
directions: Prepare your favorite pastry recipe.
Preheat oven to 425°. Shape pastry into balls, one slightly larger than the other; flatten into disks.
On lightly floured surface, roll larger disk into 11-inch circle.
Fit loosely into 9-inch pie plate.

title: the best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; then add eggs and mix.
Add rest of ingredients and blend.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Drain and add rest of ingredients, except tomatoes.
Simmer for one hour.
Add 1 cup tomatoes, mashed, and cook for 15 minutes more.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Add chili Fritos right before serving.

title: florida peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk, and add peaches, including juice, in 2 1/2-quart ovenproof glass bowl.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Add spoon of shortening on top of mix.
Do not mix into the batter.
Bake another 30 minutes or until top is golden brown. Top will be crusty.

title: chicken and broccoli alfredo(serves 4)
directions: Prepare fettuccine according to package directions. Add broccoli for last 4 minutes of cooking time. Drain.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press points of rolls to center of 12-inch pizza pan.
Pat to seal perforations.
Brown sausage.
Drain.
Spoon over crust. Sprinkle hash browns and cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over pizza.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: jello slush punch
directions: Prepare all juices and jello as directed on packages (do not cool the jello).
Combine these in large container.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Freeze overnight.
Thaw about 3 1/2 hours before serving.
Makes a slush.
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Heat margarine in skillet.
Add meat and fry until richly browned. Add onion, garlic, green peppers, celery, pepper and 2 to 3 cups water.
Cover and cook 20 to 50 minutes or until meat is tender. Add water as necessary. During the last 10 minutes, add beef bouillon. Blend cornstarch with 2 tablespoons water and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture and cook, uncovered, 5 minutes longer. Serve on rice.

title: french rice
directions: Mix soup and margarine and stir.
Drain mushrooms and reserve liquid.
Add enough water to the mushroom liquid to make 1 1/2 cups total.
Add mushrooms, liquid and rice to soup mixture and stir well.
Pour into a 10 x 6-inch (about) baking dish.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Add to the eggs the salt, pepper, cracker crumbs, pimento, cheese and milk.
Stir in asparagus.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart (7 x 11-inch) casserole.
Pour butter over top.
Bake, uncovered, in moderate oven (350°) until custard has set, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: day ahead roast beef
directions: Mix soup, water and soup mix together in bowl.
Put roast in pan; pour mix over.
Seal with foil and put lid on.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour for each pound of roast.
Cool and refrigerate overnight.
Don't open foil.
Skim fat off top.
Slice beef and heat at 300° for 1 hour.

title: mrs. nannie's yeast rolls
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; work in 1 cup of Crisco. Dissolve yeast in about 2 tablespoons of warm tap water; set aside.
Pour buttermilk into flour mixture; add yeast.
Mix and knead well.
Form into a ball; cover and let rise until doubled in size.
Punch down and refrigerate covered overnight.

title: funnel cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine eggs and milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add that to egg mixture; beat until smooth.
In skillet, heat oil to 360°.
Covering spout with finger, pour 1/4 cup batter into funnel.
Remove finger and release batter into oil in a spiral, starting in center and winding out.
Fry until golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pat out onto cookie sheets (usually 2).
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares.
Fry until brown. Place browned meat in layers in a casserole dish or in a crock-pot.
Cover each layer with mushroom soup.
Bake for 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: sour cream noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package. Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Mix noodles and sour cream. Add 1/2 cup cheese. Put into casserole. Sprinkle top lightly with 1/4 cup more Parmesan cheese.
Bake about 1 hour at 225°.

title: corn fritter batter
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Beat egg with milk; stir into flour mixture.
Beat until smooth and well blended.
Fold in corn.
Deep-fry in 375°
fryer using a tablespoon of batter for each fritter.
Turn to brown evenly. Makes about 20.

title: tangy casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
In skillet, brown sausage and ground beef with onion.
Drain well.
Add beef/sausage mixture to macaroni, along with tomatoes, tomato sauce, soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes, or until bubbly.
Top casserole with grated cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.
This freezes well.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Prepare vegetables as package directs, but only cook 4 minutes. Drain and put in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Mix soup and canned milk together and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; top with onion rings.
Return to oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and 1/2 cup water.
Cook 3 minutes on High.
Stir.
Cook another 6 to 8 minutes on High or until hard boil (250°).
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Add syrup slowly.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all and whip.
Makes 1 quart.
For best results, use a blender.

title: onion chip dip
directions: Mix the following with a mixer: room temperature cream cheese, sour cream and onion soup mix.
Let stand and chill for a while.

title: pink jello salad
directions: Mix jello according to directions.
Let partly congeal.
Mix all rest.
Whip into jello and let chill thoroughly.
Serve.

title: tuna pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and press into ungreased pie pan.

title: chicken bog
directions: Put all ingredients back in a heavy pot and bring to a boil. Then simmer until rice is done (about 45 minutes).
You may need to stir from time to time.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl beat cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk, blend thoroughly.
Stir
in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours
or
until
set. Top with pie filling.

title: western beans
directions: Lightly fry bacon.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.

title: spinach grits
directions: In large saute pan, combine all ingredients except potatoes; bring to a boil.
Add potatoes; cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes until tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Melt margarine and mix together with pretzels and sugar. Press in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust that has been baked at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix jello, water and strawberries until mixture begins to gel.
Spoon gently over second layer and refrigerate overnight.

title: meringue puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add vanilla, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Turn off oven; put puffs in oven, then let the oven completely cool before removing puffs.

title: pork stir-fry
directions: Combine sherry, cornstarch, cumin, garlic and seasoned salt in a medium bowl.
Add pork slices and stir to coat well.
Heat oil to medium-high.
Add pork mixture and stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes. Add pepper, onion and tomato pieces.
Cover pan and simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: sausage-grits souffle
directions: Stir-fry sausage until cooked and brown.
Drain well; set aside.
Cook grits in a large Dutch oven according to package instructions.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Slowly stir into grits.
Add margarine and 1 1/2 cups of cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Add sausage; mix well.
Bake in 3-quart round casserole at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese on top; return to oven just until cheese melts.
Serves 10 to 12.
Great!
Great!

title: watergate dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients, put in casserole dish and chill.

title: hard rock candy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients to hard cooking stage.
Add oil and coloring.
Pour into pans (very thin).
Let cool completely, then break into small pieces.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Break 1/2 angel food cake in pieces.
Mix 1 cup milk with package of vanilla pudding.
Soften ice cream and mix with the pudding until melted.
Pour over the broken pieces of cake. Dissolve strawberry jello in hot water.
Add strawberries cut in pieces.
When syrupy, pour over the cake.
Refrigerate.

title: sour-cream noodles
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Stir in sour cream, poppy seed and salt.
Heat to serving temperature.
Drain noodles and, while they are still very hot, return to pot they were cooked in.
Place over low heat and add the sour cream mixture.
Toss to coat noodles thoroughly.
Serve immediately.
A great side dish.

title: meatballs with noodles
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, mixing well; shape into 12 balls. Heat oil in a large heavy skillet.
Add meatballs and brown on all sides.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until soft; while still hot, cut off tops and scoop out potato into a bowl.
Put empty skins in a baking pan to be filled later.
Mash potatoes with butter and American cheese. Beat in milk with a hand mixer; you may not need all the milk. When whipped to desired consistency, fill potato skins and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fluffy french toast
directions: Beat flour, sugar, salt, milk and eggs with rotary beater until smooth.
Soak bread in batter until saturated.
Heat butter in skillet.
Carefully transfer each bread slice to skillet; do not overcrowd.
Cook bread over medium heat for 12 minutes on each side or until golden brown.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: In a large kettle, cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid and setting vegetables aside.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; stir in sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes or more until done, firm and brown on top.

title: creole coconut pie
directions: Beat the sugar and butter to a light cream, and then add the wine and the essence of vanilla.
Gradually add the coconut, beating in as lightly as possible.
Add the scalded milk, which has been allowed to cool, and finally beat in the whites of the eggs, which have been whipped to a very stiff froth.
Do this latter with a few swift strokes, so that the coconut may stand out fresh and flaky, like snow.
Bake in pie crusts which have already been set in the oven.
Serve cold, sprinkling over white powdered sugar. This is a famous Creole pie.

title: ham and corn chowder
directions: Saute ham, celery and onion in margarine in a heavy pan.
Stir in next 5 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce flame and simmer 20 minutes.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: bean and pasta salad(low-fat)
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.
Serves 2 with 300 calories and a trace of fat.

title: foolproof bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat thoroughly in chafing dish.
Use corn or tortilla chips.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all together..
Chill until ready to use.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes in conventional oven or 6 minutes in microwave, stirring twice.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients with hands.
Shape into small balls. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 100 cocktail size balls.

title: peppermint stick homemade ice cream
directions: Beat Milnot until very stiff.
Add oil and beat about 1 minute. Add syrup, flavor and few drops of red food color.
Beat until blended.
Fold in crushed peppermint candy.
Freeze in freezer tray; smooth without stirring.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla well.
Add egg.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Roll on floured surface to 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut out.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool.
Decorate.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sugar free cheese cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together till mixed well and fluffy. Pour into glass baking dish and cook on 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes or till golden brown on top.
Take out of the oven, cool, place in freezer till completely cool.
Slice and put a spoon of sugar-free strawberry jelly on top or use canned whipped cream.
If you feel that you would like a crust, you can use chopped nuts (pecans, walnuts, or peanuts).

title: banana crush punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water; add juices.
Stir bananas into juices well.
Pour into 2 containers and freeze.
When ready to serve, take containers out and pour 7-Up over frozen mixture; stir until slushy.
Let containers sit for 30 minutes before mixing in 7-Up. Serves 60 (6 ounce) servings.

title: gold candy bar
directions: In saucepan, combine first 3 ingredients.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, stir in butter and flavoring.
Pour into bowl.
Beat with mixer 4 to 5 minutes until thick and no longer glossy.
Stir in pecans.
Fill buttered plastic ice cube tray half full.
Refrigerate until firm.
Remove candy and wrap in foil wrappers.

title: country fried steak
directions: Mix all together.
Roll out onto floured board until 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into squares.
Brown in skillet.
Put in oblong cake pan.
Make gravy with drippings.
Pour over meat squares.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pizza rounds
directions: Cook ground chuck and sausage; drain.
Add cheese and oregano; stir until cheese is melted and well blended.
Serve on party rye bread.
May be frozen and heated in oven when ready to serve.

title: heavenly orange fluff
directions: Mix jello, hot water and frozen orange juice.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop beef.
(Food processor works great.)
Chop onion.
Reserve 1/3 of chopped beef.
Mix remaining beef, cream cheese, onion, Accent and sauce; form into a ball.
Roll in reserved beef. Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Heat milk and marshmallows.
Mix in other ingredients.
Press into bread tin.

title: baked halibut
directions: Lay halibut in bottom of a baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover with a thin layer of mayonnaise, 1 to 2 pats of butter, green chilies and Mozzarella cheese. Set aside. In a small bowl, melt butter and add crushed Ritz crackers. Spread mixture over the top of the halibut. Bake 30 minutes or until fish is done.

title: senate salad
directions: Drain off juice from cans of vegetables.
Simmer together vinegar, sugar and oil.
As soon as it boils and sugar is dissolved, remove from heat and let cool a bit.
While it is cooling, mix all vegetables together.
Pour the still warm (but not boiling) vinegar mixture over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: refreshing lemonade
directions: Mix lemonade, sugar and 3 1/2 quarts
water.
Add orange juice concentrate.
Mix well.
Add more water to make 1 gallon. Very tasty summertime drink!

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until onion starts to look clear.
Place broth in 3-quart pan. Add onions, water and bouillon cubes. Simmer 30 to 45 minutes. Pour soup into ovensafe bowl; add croutons. Place in 325° oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet treats
directions: Mix the pudding as directed on the box.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 of the pudding mix over the crackers.
Make another layer of crackers and pour the rest of the pudding over this layer.
Add another layer of crackers and put frosting on top.
Let set in the refrigerator for 2 hours before you eat it.
The longer it sets, the better it is.

title: pepper barbecue sauce
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in pan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer covered for 5 minutes.

Remove from heat, add remaining ingredients (which must be shaken vigorously in a quart jar to dissolve and mix thoroughly) to the pot and return to low heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.

title: my favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar, eggs, vanilla and brown sugar. Combine flour, salt and soda.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: dream pie
directions: Mix and cook in an unbaked pie shell at 325°.

title: red beans and sausage
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight.
In a large stewing pot, put oil and soften the onion for 1 minute.
Use same soaking water and put with beans in kettle.
Cook over low flame.
Cover kettle in such a way that only a little steam escapes for at least 1 hour or until beans begin to get soft.

title: bean salsa
directions: *The dressing comes in a 10 fluid ounce bottle, can use more or less, depending on taste.

title: sharon's pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put stick of margarine in large microwavable bowl and melt thoroughly in microwave.
Add eggs, Karo, sugar and vanilla.
Mix and put mixture in microwave or on stove top until it is hot and completely mixed together.
(Don't overheat.)
Add pecans and pour into pie shell.
Cook until crust is brown and middle is not liquid (about 50 minutes).

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Grease a Bundt pan. Place all ingredients into the pan in listed order. Put in pan the night before serving. Cover loosely with foil. Bake the next morning at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix butter, celery and onion with stuffing mix until crumbly. Layer 12 x 7-inch baking dish with 1/3 of stuffing mix, then 1/2 of chicken, another 1/2 of stuffing mix, another 1/2 of chicken, then rest of stuffing.
Combine soups and broth.
Pour over layers and pierce with fork so liquid will saturate.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Let set 10 minutes.
Combine all ingredients and knead on floured board for 10 minutes.
Place in large bowl.
Grease top of dough and cover.
Place in warm place and let rise to double its size.
Punch down and let rise again. Turn out on floured board and divide in 3 parts.
Place in greased loaf pans and let rise double in size.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for first 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake about 30 minutes longer.
Turn out on rack to cool.
Brush tops with butter.
Let completely cool before wrapping.

title: marinade
directions: Marinate meat overnight in sauce. Really good on the grill.

title: lobster newburg
directions: In double boiler top, over low heat, melt butter.
Stir in flour, lobster, nutmeg, paprika, salt and sherry.
Beat yolks slightly; add cream.
Mix well.
Slowly stir egg yolks into lobster.
Cook over hot water, stirring, until just thickened. Serve at once over toast in patty shells or place in individual baking dishes.
Top with buttered fresh bread crumbs.
Brown under broiler.
Makes 6 servings.

title: frosted fruit bars
directions: Mix liquid ingredients, then add dry ones.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
Use 2 greased pans (9 x 13-inch or 8 x 8-inch).
While still warm, frost with glaze.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries very fine.
Combine with marshmallows and sugar. Mix well.
Cover and chill overnight.
Add apples, walnuts, grapes, and salt.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Garnish with green grapes.

title: chicken scampi
directions: Brown garlic in oil, butter and margarine.
Cut chicken into strips and coat with flour.
Add to garlic and brown.
Sprinkle in the cayenne and oregano (more or less to taste).
Once browned, add the bouillon cubes and cover for 3 to 4 minutes.
Smush bouillon cubes into oil mixture and add the white wine.
Cook, covered, for 20 minutes and uncovered for 10 minutes.
Serve over pasta, rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: spanakopeta
directions: Rinse spinach well in cold water.
Drain thoroughly and cut into small pieces.	Salt
spinach,	then
squeeze
out the water as well as possible and
set aside.
Saute the white and green onions until limp, using 1/2 cup of the butter.
Add the spinach and continue to
saute
all
together.
Add
the dill, parsley, salt and pepper;
continue	to
simmer
lightly until the moisture of the
spinach
has
evaporated.
Take
off
the fire.
Add the milk to cool the spinach a little.

title: goofy frosting
directions: Beat and cook the flour, milk and sugar until thick and smooth. Set aside to cool.

title: peach dessert
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch sheet cake pan at 350°. Pour half of the cake mix over melted butter.
Pour both cans of peaches and syrup over cake mix.

Pour the other half of the cake mix over the peaches. Sprinkle brown sugar over top of cake mix real good. Sprinkle a little granulated sugar, if you want. Sprinkle cinnamon over top of sugar. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick corn relish
directions: Chop all vegetables until fine; add to corn.
Combine oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Stir thoroughly and pour over corn and vegetables.
Let stand several hours or overnight to mellow.

title: meatball-vegetable skillet
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Place beef in mixing bowl; add salt, pepper, nutmeg, onion and milk mixture.
Mix well, divide meat into 12 balls.
Roll meatballs in flour.
Brown on both sides in oil in skillet.
Add the vegetables and water.
Sprinkle with additional salt and pepper, if desired.
Cover tightly.
Turn skillet to low heat.
Cook for about 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown the turkey and onion. Add the remaining ingredients.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown the meat.
Drain.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and pour in casserole dish.
Simmer in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: strawberry nut dessert bread*
directions: By hand mix all ingredients together at one time.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: deviled crab
directions: Melt margarine; add flour.
Mix well.
Stir in milk (makes a thick sauce).
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into balls or patties.
Fry, bake or broil.

title: cheesy chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix 1/3 cup Cheez Whiz, sour cream, onion and chili powder and stir in chicken.
Spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture onto flour tortilla and roll up.
(Tortillas may work better if slightly warmed in microwave.)
Place filled tortilla seam side down in 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Top enchiladas with 1/2 cup salsa.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Microwave remaining Cheez Whiz in jar on High 30 to 45 seconds or until smooth when stirred.
Pour over enchiladas immediately when they are taken out of oven.
Serve with additional salsa.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Prep time:
20 minutes.
Cooking time:
30 minutes. Microwave cooking time:
12 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Butter sides of 1-quart casserole.
Place eggs around side and on bottom.
Place asparagus in casserole; cover with soups diluted with milk.
Sprinkle stuffing on top.
Bake 20 minutes in 300° oven.

title: cheddar meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg and salt; shape into 16 meatballs.
In skillet, brown meatballs (use shortening if necessary); pour off fat.
Stir in soup, water and parsley. Cover; cook over low heat 20 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and bake at 350° until heated through. Put your favorite cheese and the flavored taco chips over the top just before serving.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut cookie dough into slices.
Arrange these on an aluminum foil covered 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Cool on rack.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar in double boiler until warm.
Add vanilla and lemon rind.
Place in mixer and beat until light and silky. Gently fold in the combined flour and cornstarch.
Place in 7-inch cake pan which has been buttered and dusted with flour.
Bake at 350° to 375° until springy to touch.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust and bake until done.

title: punch
directions: If frozen strawberries are used, omit the sugar.
Crush strawberries and add sugar.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Add lemonade and water as directed on the can.
Stir in chilled ginger ale just before serving.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine in saucepan over low heat. Add milk and vanilla and remove from heat. Beat until smooth.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoon on well-greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: baked chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic, salt and pepper.
Place rib side up in low baking dish.
Combine lemon juice, soy sauce and basil. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 400°, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Turn over and baste top.
Sprinkle with olives or mushrooms and bake 20 more minutes at 400°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix color and cocoa and let stand.
Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, buttermilk, salt, soda, flour and color mixture.
Mix well.
Then pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: In hot oil, cook over medium heat the garlic, potatoes, onions and celery, stirring occasionally, for about 10 minutes. Add broth and seasoning.
Bring to a full boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until all is tender. Stir in milk.
Heat through.
Add cheese and parsley. Stir to melt cheese.
Serves 4.

title: health cookies
directions: Mix in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed the granulated sugar, brown sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
In another bowl, sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture and mix well with a wooden spoon.
Add oats, bran cereal, corn flakes and coconut; mix well.
Roll cookie dough to form walnut size balls and place on well-greased sheet.
Flatten with fork and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cookies freeze well in a tightly covered container.

title: chicken rice soup(low-fat but delicious)
directions: Cook boneless, skinless chicken breasts in water.
Remove chicken from water.
Throw water away.
Cut chicken into small pieces.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Chop spinach into very small pieces.
Beat together cream, cheeses, eggs, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Layer spinach on bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over spinach.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: baked custard
directions: Caramelize the sugar and pour into milk.
Stir until dissolved. Add the vanilla and eggs.
Pour into custard cups, set in pan of boiling water and bake at 300° until silver knife comes out clean.

title: quick cheese pancakes
directions: Place milk, egg and cottage cheese in blender container; cover container and switch blender on and off 3 or 4 times, until cottage cheese is in small pieces.
(Or beat with mixer.)
Pour into a bowl.
Add pancake mix; stir just until moistened.
Stir in butter or margarine and shredded orange peel.
Bake on hot, lightly greased griddle, using 1/4 cup batter for each.
Serve with fresh orange slices and coconut.
Makes 12 pancakes.

title: freezer spaghetti sauce
directions: Bring slowly to boil, stirring often.
Lower heat; simmer 30 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Cool slightly.
Measure 3 cups at a time into a blender; whip 1 minute at high speed.
Pour into freezer container, leaving 1 inch on top.
Yields 16 cups.

title: savory spinach
directions: Clean spinach thoroughly and drain well.
In large saucepan, combine green pepper, pimientos and onion with oil.
Saute for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add spinach and salt.
Cook, covered, until spinach is crispy-tender, about 10 minutes.
Add lemon juice and serve. Serves 6.
